title: mock pecan pie
directions: Cream the butter to soften.
Add sugar and cream until fluffy. Add syrup and salt.
Beat well.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat well after each egg.
Stir in coconut and oatmeal.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until it tests clean with a knife.
Cool and serve.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook spirals according to directions.
Grate cheese, but do not add until right before serving.
Cube all other ingredients and add to cooled, drained spirals.
Marinate overnight in Italian dressing.
Add cheese before serving.

title: pickled beets
directions: Cook beets until tender.
Allow 45 to 60 minutes for young beets, more for older variety.
Skin when cool enough.
Slice; set aside.

title: white fruitcake
directions: Drag pecans, cherries and pineapple in flour.
Set aside.
Mix rest of ingredients until creamy.
Add to pecan/fruit mixture. Place in an ungreased angel food cake pan.
Bake at 300° for 2 hours.

title: rosie's chicken
directions: In Dutch oven, in hot oil, brown chicken on all sides. Sprinkle with salt, pepper, oregano and thyme.
Add bouillon cubes in 1/2 cup water, onions and potatoes.
Simmer, covered, for 45 minutes, until tender.
Serve with green beans.

title: bean salad(from 1975 edition)
directions: Drain beans and run water over them.
Add sugar, oil, salt and pepper; also vinegar.
Let marinate for at least 24 hours before using.

title: grilled potatoes
directions: Heat up the grill.
Place all ingredients on a large piece of heavy-duty foil.
Fold it shut so nothing will escape, especially the juices.
Place on the grill.
Cook for about 20 minutes.
You will have the most wonderful tasting veggie plate ever.
Serve with grilled burgers or sirloin steak.

title: good salad
directions: Mix and serve cold.

title: chinese chicken salad
directions: Add all ingredients together and store in refrigerator until just before serving, then pour ginger dressing and toss.
Serves 4. Preparation time:
about 45 minutes.

title: moist meat loaf(microwave)
directions: In medium bowl, combine all ingredients.
Mix well and shape into 8 x 4-inch microwave dish.
Microwave at Medium-high for 15 to 20 minutes or until beef is no longer pink.
Rotate dish a half turn halfway through cooking.
Remove from microwave, cover with aluminum foil and let stand for 5 minutes.
Remove from dish and serve.

title: amazing rice
directions: Mix rice and soups in casserole dish with a tight fitting lid. Put the butter in the middle; don't stir.
Cover and bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
Before you serve, fluff with a fork.

title: chocolate frosting
directions: Cream butter.
Add salt and part of sugar.
Beat in chocolate, egg and vanilla.
Add rest of sugar alternately with milk, beating until smooth.
Frosts two layers.

title: snickerdoodles cookies
directions: Mix together shortening, sugar and eggs.
Sift together flour, cream of tartar, soda and vanilla.
Make dough, chill and roll into balls the size of a walnut.
Roll in mixture of 2 tablespoons each of sugar and cinnamon.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Place in a 400° oven and bake 10 minutes.

title: jogging in a jug
directions: Mix together.
Refrigerate.
Drink at least 2 ounces per day.

title: cream of potato soup
directions: Melt butter in a heavy saucepan over low heat; add flour, stirring constantly.
Gradually add
milk; cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened and bubbly.
Stir in potatoes, salt and pepper.
Cook 5 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
(So simple even Jerry and Wayne could do it!)

title: deviled crab
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Place in crab shells or a buttered casserole.
Sprinkle a few crumbs on top.
Dot with butter and bake at 375° until brown (until it bubbles on top).

title: bunny slipper
directions: Blend in medium bowl honey, orange juice and lemon.
Add milk and apricot nectar.
Beat with electric egg beater until foamy. Chill in refrigerator.
Beat again before serving.
Makes 4 servings.

title: dill beans - canned
directions: Cover beans with water and boil 15 minutes.
In separate pot, bring water, vinegar, salt, mustard seed and red pepper to a boil. Pack beans into jar, cucumber-fashion.
Put a small piece of dill weed and 1 small clove of garlic in each jar.
Fill jar with the hot mixture and seal.
Put in hot water bath for 10 minutes.

title: applesauce raisin bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Add eggs, salad oil and applesauce. Stir until well combined.
Stir in raisins and fill greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
(Note:
A cracked top is normal.)

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Combine in order listed, except vanilla, in large (3-quart) heavy saucepan over medium heat.
Stir until smooth and melted. Do not boil.
Reduce heat to low and beat for 7 minutes with electric mixer, adding vanilla.
Start with low heat and increase to medium-high.
Cool 30 minutes.
Store in family-size containers.
Keeps refrigerated about 3 weeks or in freezer indefinitely.
Heat in microwave or double boiler when ready to serve.

title: shepherd's pie(makes about 4 servings)
directions: Combine meat, gravy and onion.	Line bottom of buttered baking dish
with well-beaten mashed potato.
Add thick layer of meat mixture, then cover with layer of potato.
Bake in hot oven, 400°, about 1/2 hour or until potatoes are well-browned on top, and food is thoroughly heated through.

title: hamburg delight(from 1975 edition)
directions: Brown hamburg; add rest of ingredients and simmer for about 10 to 15 minutes.

title: veal scallopini
directions: Pound veal; dredge in flour.
Brown in a mixture of butter and olive oil.
Add sliced mushrooms, garlic, parsley, basil and wine. Simmer on low heat for 1 1/2 hours.
Take veal out of pan; pour sauce over veal and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: flounder skillet
directions: Melt 1/4 cup margarine in skillet; stir in dill weed.
Layer potatoes, onions and green beans in skillet.
Top with flounder. Sprinkle with water, lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Dot with remaining margarine.
Cover and simmer until potatoes are tender, about 20 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: audrey's baked beans
directions: Pour beans into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add remaining ingredients; stir in mix.
Bake for 2 hours at 275°.

title: applesauce or jam cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and applesauce.
Beat thoroughly.
Sift flour; measure and sift with baking soda, salt and spices.
Add alternately with milk to first mixture.
Beat thoroughly and pour into well-oiled loaf pan.
Bake in a moderate 375° oven about 45 minutes.

title: mop sauce
directions: Combine consomme and water and bring to a boil.
Add remaining ingredients and let stand overnight at room temperature.
Makes 2 quarts sauce.
This is used for basting meats for barbecue.
It is applied with a wooden handle dish mop soaked in sauce.

title: donna's applesauce cake
directions: Blend all ingredients, except fruit and nuts, for 1/2 minute on low speed, scraping bowl frequently.
Then mix 3 minutes on high and scrape bowl often, adding fruits and nuts the last 1/2 minute. Pour into tube pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: milk shake mixture
directions: Soak 3 packages
gelatin
in 1 1/2 cups cold water.
Heat 8 cups milk hot enough to
dissolve the gelatin.
Add 2 1/2 to 3 cups sugar, 1 teaspoon salt and
teaspoons
vanilla; cool, then add 2 cups whipped cream.
(If using
Dream
Whip,
use
water and not milk.) Set in cool place until thick.
Freeze.

title: zucchini cookies
directions: Mix together first five ingredients.
Sift together dry ingredients and mix into shortening mixture.
Drop on greased cookie sheet and bake at 325° for 12 minutes.

title: fruit peanut salad
directions: Blend together honey and peanut butter.
Gradually stir in yogurt.
Mix until well blended; chill.
Pare melons.
Cut each into 3 crosswise slices with jagged edges.
Remove seed.
Chill. Combine orange sections, apples, pineapple, banana and peanuts in a large bowl.
Toss gently with half the prepared dressing mixture just until fruit is coated.
Place melon slices in center of luncheon plates; surround with shredded lettuce.
Fill center of each melon slice with 1 cup of fruit mixture.
Serve garnished with cherries.
Serve remaining honey-peanut butter mixture separately.

title: fruit mumbles
directions: Mix together margarine and sugar.
Add flour, salt and soda to sugar mixture.
Then add oats and mix until the consistency of cookie dough.
Grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Pat 1/2 cookie dough mixture into bottom of pan, top with fruit mixture.
Crumble remaining dough over top.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: rice casserole
directions: Put uncooked rice, onion soup mix, oleo and mushrooms in an ovenproof dish.
Pour over the hot water and stir until the oleo melts.
Put in oven and bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: punch
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients and freeze solid.
Serve like slush. Take out of freezer at least 2 hours before serving to thaw.
Add 7-Up to slush.
Makes 2 one-half gallon milk cartons full.

title: creamy potato bake
directions: Prepare potatoes without butter. Add cream cheese and beat well.
Stir in egg, onion and parsley; blend well.
Place mixture in greased baking dish.
Dot top with butter and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 45 minutes or until molded and browned.

title: crock-pot vegetable-beef soup
directions: Combine meat, tomato juice, onion, seasonings and about 6 cups water in crock-pot.
Simmer on low for about 6 hours, according to pot directions.
Cut meat from
bone in cubes.
Strain broth; let cool until fat congeals.
Skim off.
Add meat, tomatoes and soup vegetables to broth and return to crock-pot.
Simmer on low until vegetables are tender.

title: pork tenderloin in cream sauce
directions: Dip patties in egg mixed with a bit of water and then dip in crumbs mixed with salt and pepper.
Brown on both sides in 3 tablespoons butter.
Mix together soup and sour cream.
Pour over meat.
Cover and bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Serve over noodles.

title: three bean casserole
directions: Fry or microwave bacon, hamburger and onion separately.
Mix with other ingredients in crock-pot or casserole.
Cook 3 hours on high in crock-pot or bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Bring to boil in saucepan 1 1/4 cups water, sugar, corn syrup and salt.
Mix cornstarch with remaining 1/4 cup water and stir into boiling mixture.
Simmer until clear.
Add strawberry Jell-O. Stir well and remove from heat.
Chill until glaze begins to thicken.
Wash, hull and drain strawberries on paper toweling. Spoon little glaze on pie shell.
Arrange layer of berries, cut side down, and cover with glaze.
Repeat layers and glaze.
Serve chilled with Cool Whip.

title: 7-up pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease 12-cup Bundt pan.
Combine flour and salt in bowl.
Combine remaining ingredients except soda in a large mixer bowl; beat at medium speed until light and fluffy, scraping sides occasionally, 5 minutes.
Reduce speed to low; add dry ingredients and soda, beginning and ending with dry ingredients.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours or until a toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan 15 minutes.
Invert onto wire rack, remove pan and cool completely.
Makes 16 servings.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together, then add rest of the ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan or 2 (9-inch) round pans.
Bake at 350° for about 50 minutes.

title: linguine with asparagus and prosciutto
directions: In a heavy skillet, cook garlic and thyme in the oil and butter over moderate heat.
Add asparagus and Prosciutto; cook mixture, stirring for 2 minutes.
Cook linguine for 8 to 10 minutes.
Remove sauce from heat; add water, lemon juice, linguine and the Parmesan cheese.
Toss and serve.

title: caramel nut frosting
directions: In saucepan, heat and stir evaporated milk, egg, brown sugar and butter until bubbly and thick.
Chill until cold and thick. Beat in vanilla and coconut.

title: "christmas delight"
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add berries, stirring occasionally, until thawed.
Add pineapple and bananas.
Pour half of mixture into an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Chill until firm.
Spoon sour cream over chilled gelatin in an even layer.
Pour remaining gelatin over and chill.

title: hot chicken salad sandwiches
directions: Combine chicken, onion, celery, pepper, salad dressing and salt and pepper to taste.
Grease 14 x 9-inch pan.
Place 6 slices of bread in pan.
Spread with mixture and top with 6 slices bread. Beat eggs and add to milk; pour over sandwiches.
Cover and chill overnight.

title: chocolate chip cookie surprise
directions: Pour milk into a pan (size doesn't matter).
Put a few cookies in milk and let soak for 5 seconds, then place the soaked cookies in pan (size of pan depends on how many you are serving).
Once bottom of pan is covered, spread a layer of whipped cream over cookies.
Continue this process for 3 to 4 layers.

title: chocolate chip brittle
directions: Mix butter and vanilla until creamy.
Add sugars and mix well. Stir in flour, then add chips.
Spread out on small cookie sheet and pat down.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: potato salad
directions: Wash the potatoes.
Heat 1-inch salted water (1/2 teaspoon salt to 1 cup water) to boiling.
Add unpared potatoes.
Cover tightly; heat to boiling and cook 30 to 35 minutes or until tender.
Drain; cool and peel.
Cut potatoes into cubes; combine in a bowl with the onion. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Mix with Italian salad dressing. Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours. Just before serving, add mayo; toss until potatoes are well coated.
Stir in celery and eggs.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Mix all together and put into 13 x 9-inch baking pan.

title: cherry carnival
directions: Cream shortening and sugar until fluffy.
Blend in well beaten eggs.

Sift dry ingredients together and stir into creamed mixture alternately with milk. Blend in well drained cherries and nuts. Bake in 9 x 13-inch greased pan about 50 minutes in 350° oven. Serve warm with Hot Cherry Sauce.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Saute onion with oleo.
Add cooked broccoli and rice.
Add 2 cups mushroom soup and Cheez Whiz.
Stir well.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole dish or 2 medium size dishes.
Bake for 35 minutes at 350°.

title: wampanoag clam pie
directions: Mix clams, beaten eggs, onion, crumbs and liquid. Add all of drippings, stir well. Add seasonings and butter. Line a 10 inch pyrex pie plate with pastry. Sprinkle 1/2 of pork scraps in bottom. Put in clam mixture and rest of pork scraps. Cover with top crust.

title: date and nut bread
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients; let this mixture cool.
Cream sugar and shortening; add eggs.
Combine flour, baking powder, vanilla and walnuts.
Add date mixture alternately with flour mixture.
Pour into loaf pan and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: watergate cake
directions: Bake about 40 minutes at 325°.

title: shoo-fly cake
directions: Mix flour, brown sugar and butter.
Take out 1 1/2 cups and set aside for top of cake.
Mix syrup, water and baking soda until blended.
Add dry mixture and mix.
Sprinkle 1 1/2 cups of crumbs on top of cake.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cherry cheese pie
directions: Beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Add milk and mix thoroughly. Stir in lemon juice and vanilla; combine well.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Chill for 3 hours.
Top with cherry filling.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar together. Add sour cream, eggs (one at a time) and vanilla; mix well. Add flour and baking powder. Put in greased 9 x 13 pan.

title: lemonade stand pie
directions: Beat lemonade concentrate in large bowl for 30 seconds. Gradually scoop in ice cream; blend well. Gently stir in whipped topping until smooth. Freeze (if necessary) until mixture will mound. Spoon into crust. Freeze 4 hours, until firm. Let stand at room temperature or in refrigerator about 30 minutes or until pie can be easily cut. Garnish with strawberries. Store leftovers in freezer.

title: pineapple stuffing(good with ham)
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add pineapple and then bread crumbs.
Bake in greased casserole dish at 350° for about 60 minutes.

title: ada's cajun beans
directions: Soak beans overnight in water; rinse and start cooking.
Cook ham for a while, then add the rest of the ingredients and simmer for a couple of hours or until beans are tender.
Make Hot Water Cornbread and pig out!

title: rolled wheat cake
directions: Pour hot water over rolled wheat and let stand.
Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, flour, soda and cinnamon.
Mix and then add rolled wheat.
Bake 40 minutes or until done at 350°.
This will make a 19 x 13-inch cake.
(I use a 9 1/2 x 13-inch pan.) Serve with Butterscotch Sauce.

title: snow-capped green beans
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spread butter on bottom of 1-quart casserole dish.
Top with mushrooms.
Spread green beans over mushrooms.
Sprinkle with salt and basil.
Spoon sour cream over top.
Cover loosely with foil.
Bake 20 minutes or until mixture starts to bubble around edges.
Serve immediately.

title: green tomato chocolate cake
directions: Cream together butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Stir in vanilla and orange rind.
Set aside.
Combine cocoa, flour, baking powder, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Alternately stir flour mixture, buttermilk and tomato into egg mixture.
Fold in pecans.
Bake in Bundt pan at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool.
Glaze.

title: pineapple lime mold
directions: Preparation time: 15 minutes, plus chilling.

title: brownies or wesson oil cookies
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Beat sugar into eggs.
Mix in Wesson oil, chocolate and vanilla. Add flour all at once.
Mix nuts.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: pork adobo
directions: Cut
pork
into
serving pieces.
In a skillet, combine pork, garlic,
bay leaves, vinegar, salt and peppercorns; let stand
for 10 minutes.
Add enough water to nearly cover meat. Cover and simmer until water is evaporated, about 1 1/2 hours. Brown meat in skillet, adding more fat, if necessary.

title: cranberry delight
directions: Rinse cranberries and orange.
Cut up orange with skin on. Mix together in food processor, then put into bowl.
Add pineapple and sugar.
Mix well and chill.
Excellent for the holidays!

title: strawberry pie
directions: Boil water, sugar and cornstarch until thick.
Add jello; let cool.
Wash and slice strawberries into jello mixture.
Pour into pie crust.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Brown the meat and onion together.
Drain fat.
Add the tomato juice and raw vegetables.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Add macaroni and canned vegetables.
Cook another 10 or 15 minutes.

title: buckeyes
directions: Mix the margarine, powdered sugar, peanut butter and vanilla together in food processor, large mixer or mix by hand.
Form into balls the size of buckeyes.
Chill.
Melt the chocolate chips, shortening and paraffin in the top of a double boiler or in the microwave for 1 1/2 minutes.
Insert toothpicks into the balls and dip into the chocolate, leaving a small area at the top plain to look like buckeyes.
Place on waxed paper and refrigerate to set the chocolate.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook sugar, syrup and water until it spins a thread when poured from a spoon.
Add peanuts, stirring continuously on medium heat until mixture turns light brown (peanuts will look cooked).
Remove from heat, add soda and stir well.
Pour on buttered cookie sheet. Cool.
Break into small pieces.

title: never fail homemade noodles
directions: Combine all ingredients with a fork until it forms a very stiff dough.
Roll out on a floured board until very thin.
Let stand for 20 minutes.
Cut as you desire.
Spread out and let dry for 2 hours.
Cook as you would any noodles.

title: lemon poppy seed cake
directions: Grease well a 10-inch tube pan.
Sprinkle lightly with flour. Combine all ingredients and pour into prepared pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until cake springs back lightly when touched. Serve with fruit in season or frost with lemon glaze.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Beat the cream cheese until fluffy.
Add mayonnaise, green onions and shrimp.
Continue to beat until shrimp are as broken or fine as you like.
Refrigerate 8 hours before serving.

title: jasper pancakes
directions: Mix together.
Can be kept in refrigerator for a while.

title: spicy red beans and rice
directions: Brown meat in large skillet.
Add onions and chopped peppers, dash of chili powder; cover and simmer for a couple of minutes. Add tomato paste.
Stir in kidney beans.
Cover and simmer for 15 minutes.
Serve with prepared rice.

title: german potato salad
directions: Slice cooked potatoes in bowl.
Mix vinegar, oil, sugar and parsley flakes.
Pour over potatoes.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Sprinkle bacon pieces on top.
Cover and let sit 1 hour. Serve warm.

title: no can no seal pickles
directions: Dissolve salt in water.
Have cucumbers washed clean.
Put cucumbers in glass, stone or plastic container with salt water. Soak for 4 days.
Keep well covered.
Take cucumbers out of water and slice.
Dissolve alum in 2 gallons of fresh water.
Put cucumbers in alum water.
Soak 2 days.
Take cucumbers out of alum water.
Pour vinegar in container.
Put cucumbers in vinegar.
Soak 1 day and 1 night.
Remove cucumbers out of vinegar and rinse.
Put pickling spice in cloth and put in bottom of container.
Start with a layer of cucumbers, then a layer of sugar.
Repeat this until all cucumbers and sugar are in container ending with a layer of sugar on top.
The sugar makes a syrup.
In 24 hours a sugar syrup should cover all cucumbers.
(May add green food coloring if desired.) Leave in syrup until ready to eat.
Best if taken out of syrup and chilled before eating.

title: hot chicken sandwiches
directions: Prepare chicken and set aside.
Combine butter, flour, salt, mustard and milk in top of double boiler to make sauce.
(Stir often.)
Add the cheese and cook until melted.
Place chicken slices (and ham slices if using) on toast and pour sauce over. Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° to 400° on ovenproof plates for 10 minutes.
Top with tomato slices and bacon.
If desired, garnish with chopped green chilies.

title: oven fried potatoes
directions: Wash unpeeled potatoes.
Cut lengthwise into 4 wedges.
Place potatoes in pan.
Combine remaining ingredients and brush over potatoes.
Bake.
Brush with oil and cheese mixture every 15 minutes.
Bake at 375° for 60 minutes.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix margarine, eggs and powdered sugar for 15 minutes with mixer.
Spread on top of crackers.
Add layers of bananas and pineapple.
Top with layer of Dream Whip, chopped nuts and cherries.

title: pork roast
directions: Combine all the ingredients.
Make slits and place mixture into slits in the roast.
Roast in baking pan, uncovered, at 275° for 3 hours, then at 425° until dark brown.

title: dumplings(italian style)
directions: Mix milk and cornmeal in a pan.
Cook and stir over medium heat until thick.
Stir into eggs.
Add salt, pepper, onion and 1 cup cheese.
Pour into baking pan so mixture is about 1 1/2 inches thick and chill.
Remove from pan and cut into pieces.
Place on greased baking sheet; brush with butter and sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° about 20 minutes, until lightly browned.
Makes 6 servings.

title: lemon squares
directions: Use pastry blender to mix butter, 1/3 cup powdered sugar and 1 1/2 cups flour well.
Pat into pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: grandmother's irish soda bread
directions: In a bowl, sift the flour, sugar, salt and baking powder.
Mix in caraway seed.
With a pastry blender or knife, cut in shortening to the consistency of cornmeal.
Add raisins.
Stir in combined buttermilk, egg and soda.
Mix until just moistened. Turn out on a lightly floured board and knead gently until smooth. Form a round loaf.
Place dough in a well-greased pan.
Cut a cross about 1/2 inch deep.
Bake until golden at 375°, 1 hour or longer.
Smother the outside of the loaf with butter or margarine while still hot to give it extra flavor.
Yield:
1 round loaf.

title: soybean hamburger casserole
directions: Brown
meat,
celery,
onion
and
green pepper in oil. When meat
is
brown
stir
in
salt,
pepper,
seasoned salt, soybeans,
tomato
soup, tomato sauce, bouillon cube and rice. Serves 6.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Preheat oven to 350°. Saute in
large heavy skillet.
Heat and simmer a few minutes. Place in
greased
casserole and bake 45 minutes.
Remove from oven and
top
with
cup
grated cheese or cheese slices. Return to oven a few minutes until cheese has melted.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients; set aside until syrup forms. Bring to a boil; reduce heat to low and cook 10 minutes or until tender.
Remove from heat; add vanilla and butter.

title: seasoned pretzels
directions: Mix all ingredients together and then add pretzels.
Let soak for 3 to 4 hours.
Stir every now and then.
Put on cookie sheet and bake at 250° for 20 minutes.

title: sunken treasure cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease and flour 13 x 9-inch baking pan.

Prepare cake mix batter according to package directions. Pour into prepared pan. Gently place Nestle Treasures over batter about 1 1/2 to 2-inches apart (creating five rows of three). Bake for 30 to 40 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool completely in pan on wire rack. Frost cake. Cut into pieces (each piece should have a sunken Nestle Treasure).

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Drop by spoon or roll into little balls and place on oiled cookie sheet, then flatten slightly.
Bake at 350° until done.
(This recipe works better if dough is refrigerated before forming into little balls.)

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Cream sugar and oleo; add apples, flour, eggs, soda and baking powder, cinnamon, nuts and vanilla.
Mix well.
Bake in 9 1/2 x 13-inch pan for 40 minutes at 325°.
Serve with ice cream, whipped cream or plain.

title: old settler baked beans
directions: Brown and drain bacon (crumble), hamburger and onion.
Drain kidney and butter beans.
Combine all ingredients.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: liptauer spread
directions: In a medium bowl mix instant minced onion and dry mustard with 2 Tbsp of warm water and let stand for 10 minutes.
Meanwhile cream the butter, add cream cheese, blending well.
Add onion, mustard mixture, anchovies, capers (if desired), caraway seeds and pepper.
Mix well.
Pack into 2 glass cups, chill until firm. When serving sprinkle with paprika and parsley.

title: simple shepherd's pie
directions: Take hamburger, drain and add peas.
Cover and simmer.
Season as wanted.
Make bowl of mashed potatoes and make a hole in the middle.
Add peas and hamburger in hole when ready to serve.

title: streusel caramel bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, combine flour, brown sugar and egg.
Cut in 1/2 cup margarine until crumbly.
Stir in nuts.
Reserve 2 cups crumb mixture.
Press remainder firmly in bottom of greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake 15 minutes.

title: big cookie
directions: Mix dry ingredients with peanut butter; add vanilla and syrup. Make five 6-inch cookies.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: plantation cookies
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°. Line 2 heavy-duty baking sheets with foil. Using the flat beater, beat 1 cup of the sugar and all of the butter in the bowl of an electric mixer until the mixture is light in color. Beat in the egg. Scrape down the sides of the bowl and beat in the sorghum or molasses. Beat in 1/2 cup of the peanuts. In a bowl, sift together the flour, baking soda, ginger, cinnamon, cloves and nutmeg. Add to the dough and mix well, scraping down the bowl at once.

title: easy chicken pot pie
directions: Place contents of vegetable/seasoning packet and butter in bowl.
Add water and stir to partly melt butter.
Add stuffing crumbs; stir gently to mix.
Mix soup and milk in 2-quart casserole.
Stir in chicken, vegetables and thyme.
Spoon stuffing over chicken mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Makes 4 servings.
tags: Stove Top chicken flavor stuffing mix

title: zucchini-sausage-pie
directions: Cook loose sausage; drain off fat.
Mix all ingredients in bowl and pour into pie dishes or quiche pan.
It will form its own crust.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: millionaire candy
directions: Melt caramels and water over boiling water.
Add pecans and margarine.
Cool and drop spoonfuls on waxed paper.
Melt paraffin and Hershey bars.
Stick toothpick in candy and dip and cover candy with chocolate.

title: ice cream sandwiches
directions: Line a 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan with aluminum foil. Grease.
Melt marshmallows and margarine until smooth.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour over cereal; mix well.
Spread into prepared pan. Cool completely.
Cut cereal mixture in half, crosswise.
Cut ice cream 3/8-inch thick slices.
Arrange one-half pan of cereal mixture.
Top with remaining half.
Freeze until firm.
Cut into 12 sandwiches.
Store covered in freezer.

title: chocolate covered cherries
directions: With your hands, make a very stiff dough of sugar, butter, vanilla and milk.
Place a small piece of dough in the palm of your hand and flatten it.
Place a cherry in the center and wrap. Do this until all cherries have been wrapped.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly and chill for at least 1 hour before serving. Nuts may also be added, if desired.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.

title: one pot cabbage kielbasa
directions: Slice sausage in 1/4-inch slices. Chop potatoes into 1-inch pieces. Chop cabbage into 2-inch strips. Add 2 tablespoons oil to large frying pan or Dutch oven. Heat, then add potatoes. Cook for 5 minutes; add sausage slices. Cook 2 minutes. Add cabbage and beef bouillon cube, dissolved in 1 cup hot water. Add onion and bell pepper and season to taste. Simmer until cabbage is done but not mushy.

title: dorene watts' easy pie dough
directions: Cut Crisco into flour until fine.
Add salt.
Add enough water to make ball.
Roll out on well floured board.

title: best ever lemon pie(ann landers)
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch and pinch of salt together in a heavy pan.
Add 2 cups water.
Combine egg yolks with the lemon juice and beat.
Cook until thick.
Add lemon extract, butter and vinegar.
Stir thoroughly.
Cool slightly and pour into pie shell.
Top with Never Fail Meringue.

title: pecan pie surprise bars
directions: Grease bottom and sides of 13 x 9-inch baking pan. Reserve 2/3 cup dry cake mix for filling. In large mixing bowl, combine remaining dry cake mix, butter and 1 egg; mix until crumbly. Press in prepared pan. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until light golden brown.

title: lime congealed salad
directions: Combine jello and water.
Add other ingredients.
Pour into prepared dish. Cover with wrap and chill.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cut steak into thin strips; dust with flour mixed with salt & pepper.
In large skillet, brown meat in butter.
Add drained mushrooms, onion & garlic; brown lightly.
Stir in beef broth. Cover and cook for 1 hr. or until meat is tender.
Stir occasionally.
When meat is done, gradually stir sour cream into mixture.
Cook over low heat for 5 minutes.
Serve over hot cooked noodles.

title: spanish rice
directions: Cook rice in salted water.
Brown meat.
Saute pepper and onion in bacon grease or in meat drippings.
Add cooked meat and cooked rice.
Stir well.
Blend soup and water; heat thoroughly and add to meat-rice mix.

title: delicious grilled steak
directions: Mix ingredients for marinade well.
Beat steak well.
Put in marinade and soak overnight.
Put steaks on a hot grill.
Cook 10 minutes on each side.
Serves 4.
Marinade can be refrigerated and used again.

title: river farm ginger cookies
directions: Cream shortening; half butter and half lard is recommended. Add sugar and cream well.
Add molasses, eggs and sugar and beat. Add vinegar, extract and dissolved soda.
Add flour until dough is stiff enough to roll.
Roll dough; cut out cookies.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 375°.

title: pasta rapido
directions: Prepare beans; keep warm.
Stack tortillas, wrap in foil and heat in a 350° oven for 15 minutes.

title: chicken divan
directions: Boil chicken breasts for 25 minutes.
Cool and remove bones. Cook chopped broccoli for 25 minutes.
Layer broccoli in greased glass pan.
Put chicken breasts on top of broccoli.
Pour mixture of mayonnaise, chicken soup, curry powder and lemon juice on top of chicken breasts.
Sprinkle cheese on top of mixture.
Sprinkle bread crumbs on top of cheese.
Bake 25 minutes in a 375° oven. Enjoy a quick, delicious meal!
Makes 6 servings.

title: banana wheat quick bread
directions: Grease and flour 9 x 5-inch or 8 x 4-inch pan.
In large bowl, blend all ingredients.
Beat for 3 minutes at medium speed.
Pour into pan.
Bake for 60 to 70 minutes at 350°.
Test with toothpick.
Remove from pan and cool.

title: cranberry-orange muffins
directions: In large bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt. In small bowl, combine corn oil, egg, orange peel and juice.
Stir into flour mixture just until moistened.
Add cranberries.
Spoon into prepared pans.
Sprinkle with walnuts.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes until golden.
Makes 12.

title: seafoam lime mold
directions: Dissolve gelatin in water; add cold water and lemon juice. Gradually add to softened cream cheese, mixing until well blended (use blender).
Chill until almost firm.
Fold in marshmallows, pineapple and nuts.
Pour into a 1-quart mold.
Chill until firm. Serves 4 to 6.

title: harvey wallbanger cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and beat 4 minutes.
Pour batter into well-greased and lightly floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Dust with powdered sugar and frost with the Orange Glaze.

title: shish-kabobs
directions: Combine oil, soy sauce, honey, vinegar, ginger, chopped onion and garlic powder in blender.
Cut peppers, onions, mushrooms and steak in cube sized to fit on shish-kabob sticks.
Put in bowl and pour sauce from blender on ingredients in bowl.
Marinate overnight.
Alternate pieces on shisk-kabob sticks.
Grill on grill.

title: green beans, cream style
directions: Cook beans according to package directions.
Drain.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Blend thoroughly.
Add to beans and heat through.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chicken breast with orange sauce
directions: Melt butter and olive oil in skillet.
Add chicken and cook for 4 minutes each side, remove chicken.
Add flour, scallions, orange juice, brown sugar, ginger and dijon mustard.
Cook until condensed.
Add chicken back in and cook thoroughly.

title: trudy's gumbo
directions: Brown ground beef and onion, drain. In large pan, combine soup, cans of tomatoes with juice, and Veg-all.
Drain carrots, green beans, and corn and pour mixture together.
Drain canned potatoes, wash, and cut into bite size pieces.
Heat until hot.

title: "raw" roast
directions: Preheat oven at 500°.
Bake for 5 minutes per round.
Cut off oven.
Leave for 3 hours.
Do not open door!

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Mix pudding with milk according to package directions.
Then mix in Cool Whip and coconut.
Pour into pie shell.
Spread Cool Whip on top of pudding mixture.
Sprinkle top with coconut.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix instant pudding and milk; beat well.
Stir in Cool Whip and sour cream.
Layer this mixture with layers of bananas and vanilla wafers.

title: christmas chocolate balls
directions: Combine peanut butter, egg, butter, dates, coconut and confectioners sugar in large bowl and mix thoroughly.
If sticky, add more confectioners sugar.
Shape in 1-inch balls and refrigerate while preparing chocolate for coating.
Melt chocolate chips, semi-sweet chocolate and wax in top of a double boiler.
Use spoon or fork and dip balls in melted chocolate.
Place on foil to set.
Store in a cool place in a covered container.

title: triple layer chocolate bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine crumbs, 1/4 cup cocoa, sugar and margarine; press firmly on bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
In mixer bowl, beat remaining ingredients, except nuts and chips. Stir in nuts.
Spread over prepared crust.
Top with chips.
Bake 25 minutes or until set.
Cool.
Store tightly covered.

title: fresh apple walnut cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Mix and sift flour, baking soda, salt, cinnamon and mace.
Add gradually to butter mixture. Stir in vanilla, apples and walnuts.
Batter will be stiff.

title: egg curry
directions: Boil 4 to 5 eggs (depending of number of persons to be served).
Peel and set aside.
In a large saucepan, add oil and chopped onion.
Saute onion until just turning color.
Add curry and salt.
Stir and simmer 2 to 3 minutes.
Add 1 cup warm water and chopped garlic and stir.
Add peeled eggs and spoon curry over eggs to coat.
If the curry starts to become dry, add a little more warm water by tablespoons.
(You want a curry sauce with your eggs.) Cook approximately 10 minutes until eggs are coated with sauce.
Just before serving, add chopped coriander and stir.
Serve immediately with nan or toasted bread.

title: marie's chicken casserole
directions: Mix all and refrigerate overnight.
Top with 1 cup grated cheese, 1/2 cup slivered almonds and 2 cups crushed potato chips before baking.

title: pineapple millionaire pie
directions: Cream together powdered
sugar and butter with electric mixer. Add egg, salt
and
vanilla.
Beat
until
light
and fluffy. Spread mixture evenly into baked pie shell and chill.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Crumble cake into bite size pieces.
In punch bowl, layer in order given down to grated chocolate.
Keep layering until all is used up, ending with whipped topping.
Sprinkle coconut over top. Sprinkle pecans and grated chocolate over coconut.
Refrigerate.

title: pork barbecue
directions: Bake pork roast.
While baking, prepare sauce.
Mix remaining ingredients in a saucepan and simmer 15 minutes until thick.
When roast has baked, cool long enough to handle.
Then cut, chop and scrape all meat from bones.
Place in roasting pan; cover with barbecue sauce until swimming.
Bake at 325° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours. Stir and mash meat into shreds.
(The longer it cooks, the better it shreds.)
Add more sauce if necessary.
Makes enough sauce for a large roast.

title: rhubarb pie(or can use same recipe for cherry pie.)
directions: Combine tapioca, sugar, salt and rhubarb.
Let stand about 15 minutes.
Put in a pie shell and add butter.
Then put top crust on.
Bake at 425° for about 50 minutes.

title: granola bars
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Press into 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool and cut in bars.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Melt oleo and mix all other ingredients.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 45 minutes. Leftovers may be refrigerated or frozen.
Reheat in microwave. Can be baked as muffins.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: Place all ingredients in 1 cup jar with tight fitting lid. Cover and shake well. Serve over fresh fruit.

title: creamy chili dip
directions: In medium bowl, beat at medium speed the cream cheese until smooth and fluffy. Gradually beat in V-8 juice until smooth and well blended. Stir in chilies, olives, red pepper, onion and hot pepper sauce.
Cover; refrigerate at least 4 hours. Serve with chips or fresh vegetables.
Yield: 4 cups.

title: bourbon-basted cornish hens
directions: Saute onions in 4 tablespoons butter.
Cook rice.
Combine onions and rice; add almonds and thyme.
Stuff hens and place in a buttered shallow baking dish.
(Or using halves, place cut side down in buttered dish and when done, place a scoop of stuffing on plate and a hen half over it.)
Baste hens with a mixture of 1/2 cup melted butter, salt, pepper and bourbon.
Roast 30 minutes at 425°, basting three times.
Reduce oven to 350°.
Roast 30 minutes, basting 2 times more.
Turn hens, breast side down and roast 15 minutes.
Turn hens, breast side up.
Baste with melted currant jelly.
Roast 30 minutes.

title: buttermilk pecan chicken
directions: Melt butter in dish.
Mix buttermilk with egg in shallow dish.
Mix flour, ground pecans, paprika, salt, pepper and sesame seed in another dish.
Dip chicken in buttermilk mixture and then in flour mixture.
Place chicken, skin side down, in melted butter, then turn to coat.
Place pecan halves around chicken to bake in moderate oven at 350° for 1 3/4 hours or until chicken is golden brown.
Garnish with tomatoes and parsley.

title: crab spaghetti
directions: Thaw crab and drain.
Cook garlic in hot olive oil and butter for 30 seconds.
Add basil and cook 1 minute.
Add wine, simmer uncovered 5 minutes.
Stir in crabmeat and soy sauce.
Heat through.
Serve over hot pasta.

title: mom's french green beans
directions: Cut bacon into 1-inch pieces.
Fry bacon in small skillet until crisp.
When bacon is just crisp, add onion, separated into rings and saute until a little tender, 1 to 2 minutes.
Add sugar and mix until sugar dissolves, then while stirring over heat, pour in the vinegar.
It will sizzle a little.
You may either pour this mixture over cold green beans or pour beans in skillet and heat through.
It's my favorite!

title: chicken and rice
directions: Saute thighs with oil and garlic.
Turn often (30 minutes). Remove from skillet.
Dice peppers, carrots and onion.
Saute in same skillet with chicken mix.
Pour rice and mix with chicken broth and Sasson.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat (low) for 20 minutes.
Place thighs on top.
Leave stand for 20 minutes. Garnish with peas (cooked or uncooked).

title: dressing for small turkey
directions: Fry onion and celery in 1/2 cup butter or margarine.
Add the bread which has been torn into small pieces.
Add rest of ingredients.
Mix well.

title: scotcharoos
directions: Bring to a boil the sugar and Karo.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter; stir until blended.
Add Rice Krispies.
Mix thoroughly.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt chocolate and butterscotch bits together.
Spread on top of Rice Krispies.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Mix and press the pretzels, sugar and margarine into a 13 x 9 pan.
Bake for 7 minutes at 400° and cool.
Blend the cream cheese, powdered sugar and Cool Whip and spread over crust.
Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add strawberries and pineapple.
Chill slightly, then pour over mixture in pan and chill.

title: chocolate icing
directions: Mix sugar, flour, cocoa and a little milk at a time while stirring.
Then gradually pour rest of milk and 1/2 stick margarine together and heat until thick.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients and pour into pie crust. Next, combine the milk and pudding; mix well.
Add the pumpkin and spices, mixing well, then pour the mixture over the mixture in the pie crust.
Chill for several hours.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into greased pan. (Makes 1 medium loaf or 2 small loaves.)
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.
Time can be decreased with smaller loaves.

title: rigatoni
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and garlic; drain.
Stir in spaghetti sauce and pepper.
Reduce heat, then simmer for 10 minutes.

title: milky way cake
directions: Melt over low heat or in double boiler, candy bars and oleo; set aside.
Cream Crisco with sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time; beat well.
Sift flour, salt and soda.
Add alternately with buttermilk, vanilla and nuts.
Fold in candy mixture and bake in three 8-inch pans at 350° for 30 minutes. Pans are to be greased and floured.

title: hearty chowder
directions: Heat soup, garlic, pepper and flakes and stir.

title: sausage brunch casserole
directions: Butter 9 x 13-inch dish.
Spread stuffing evenly.
Sprinkle cheese over stuffing, then the sausage.
Beat eggs, 2 1/4 cups milk and dry mustard.
Pour over sausage.
Refrigerate overnight. Next morning, mix soup and 1/2 cup milk.
Pour over casserole. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: impossible cheesecake pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease pie plate, 9 x 1 1/4-inch.
Place milk, vanilla, eggs, sugar and Bisquick in blender or food processor.
Cover and blend on high 15 seconds.
Add cream cheese. Cover and blend on high 2 minutes.
Pour into plate.
Bake until center is firm, 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool.
Spread cheesecake topping carefully over top.
Garnish with fruit, if desired.

title: white chocolate fudge
directions: Beat cream cheese, sugar and vanilla until smooth.
In double boiler melt the chocolate.
Fold chocolate into cream cheese mixture with pecans.
Spread into 8-inch dish.
Chill and cut into squares.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in a greased 9 x 12-inch pan at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: lemon blueberry pecan cupcakes
directions: Mix water, eggs, cake mix and oil together. Wash blueberries; drain. Mix pecans. Pour into cupcake pans. Bake at 350° until brown, about 20 to 25 minutes.

title: crab meat on muffins
directions: Beat cream cheese, butter and Cheddar until smooth.
Blend in crab meat.
Spread mixture onto muffins.
Broil for 1 to 1 1/2 minutes.

title: batter for shrimp
directions: Mix all ingredients until smooth.
Let whatever (shrimp, squash, mushrooms, bananas or your choice) be completely dry; dry with paper towel.
Dip in batter to fry.

title: angel fuzz
directions: Mix all together.
Refrigerate as you would to set jello.

title: marshmallow torte
directions: Blend together the powdered sugar and butter.
Add egg yolks, syrup, marshmallows and nuts.
Fold in 3 beaten egg whites.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Refrigerate.

title: apple cake
directions: Pour sugar over apples.
Let stand for 30 minutes.
Mix dry ingredients into apple mixture.
Blend eggs and oil together. Combine all ingredients.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch sheet pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: pineapple bars
directions: Combine all ingredients, except pineapple and orange rind, mixing well.
Stir in crushed pineapple and grated orange rind. Pour batter into 17 x 11-inch jellyroll pan lined with well-greased baker's parchment or brown paper.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 30 minutes or until toothpick inserted in middle comes out clean.
Frost while hot with Nutty Cream Cheese Frosting.
Yields 48 (2-inch) squares.

title: crunchy jumble cookies
directions: Sift together flour, soda and salt. Set aside.
Measure margarine and sugar in a large mixing bowl.
Beat until well blended and smooth.
Add vanilla and egg. Beat well. Add sifted ingredients.
Mix until combined. Stir in Rice Krispies, semi-sweet chocolate chips and raisins. Drop by level teaspoon onto lightly greased baking sheet.

title: oyster crackers snacks
directions: Mix all together and let stand until all the oil soaks up.

title: cobbler
directions: Melt butter in a baking dish.
Add batter.
Place fruit over batter and bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until brown.

title: oreo milkshake
directions: Put ice cream into blender.
Add milk and cookies and blend until smooth.

title: hot peppers
directions: Pack peppers in hot sterile jars.
Bring syrup to a boil and pour over peppers.
Seal.

title: no bake peanut butter pie
directions: Beat together cream cheese and confectioners sugar.
Mix in peanut butter and milk.
Beat until smooth.
Fold in whipped topping.
Spoon into two 9-inch graham cracker pie shells; cover and freeze until firm.
Creamy and delicious - melts in your mouth.
This pie is a real crowd pleaser and it can be reduced fat ingredients.

title: make-ahead mashed potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes in salted water until tender; drain and mash. Add cream cheese, sour cream, salt and pepper, mixing well.
Put in greased 2-quart casserole or may be stored in the refrigerator for several days.

title: pumpkin cake roll
directions: Beat 3 eggs on high speed of mixer for 5 minutes; gradually beat in the sugar.
Stir in pumpkin and lemon juice.
Stir together flour, baking powder, cinnamon, ginger, nutmeg and salt. Fold into pumpkin mixture.
Spread in a greased and floured 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan.
Top with nuts and bake.

title: cheese and ham appetizers
directions: Put first 4 ingredients in a blender container; cover and run on speed 5 (or start on low, then move to high) until smooth.
If necessary, stop blender during processing and push ingredients toward blades with rubber spatula.
Spread mixture 1/8 inch thick; roll each slice as for jelly roll.
Wrap in waxed paper slices. Place slices on small crackers to serve.
Makes 15 to 20 appetizers.

title: jello salad deluxe
directions: Add 1 1/2 cups boiling water to 1 pkg.
Jello.
Stir in cranberries until dissolved:
add crushed pineapple.
Pour into 9 X 13-inch glass dish or large mold until partially set.
This is the first layer.
Pinch off small pieces of cream cheese and roll in chopped nuts to form small balls.
Push these into the partially set Jello and chill thoroughly.
When firm, spread the sour cream over.
This is the second layer.
Chill.
Pour 1 1/4 cups boiling water into second pkg. of Jello.
Stir and add frozen berries. This will thicken Jello.
Pour over sour cream to make a third layer.
YUM!

title: grilled pineapple burgers
directions: Mix ground beef, salad dressing, salt and pepper.
Shape into 8 patties, 3-inch in diameter.
Press pineapple slice into each patty.
Wrap each patty with bacon slice; secure with wooden pick.
Mix barbecue sauce, brown sugar, honey and lemon juice. Place patties in 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish.
Pour barbecue mixture on patties.
Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Grill patties, pineapple sides down 4 inches from hot coals 12 to 15 minutes. Turn, brush with barbecue mixture.
Grill 10 to 15 minutes.
Heat remaining barbecue mixture; serve with patties.
Yield: 8 servings.

title: meat patties with tomatoes
directions: Boil potatoes until cooked. Peel and mash. Set aside.
Combine meat, onion, eggs, mashed potato, salt, pepper, cinnamon, saffron water and turmeric.
Knead until a smooth paste forms.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt 1 stick of butter in pan you are cooking in.
In another bowl, mix the flour, sugar and milk.
Pour all ingredients (flour, sugar, milk) with the butter, but do not stir.
Pour in peaches and do not stir.
Cook 1 hour at 350° to 400°.

title: carrot souffle
directions: Blend together and bake in greased casserole for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: banana split cake
directions: Melt 1 stick margarine and mix with graham cracker crumbs. Press into an oblong pan (10 x 13-inch).
Mix together 2 sticks margarine, sugar, eggs, cream cheese and vanilla.
Heat sugar mixture for 15 minutes.
Pour over graham cracker crumbs.
Slice bananas over sugar mixture (in a layer).
Top with pie filling. Over pie filling, spread whipped topping and sprinkle with nuts. Chill.

title: bran muffins
directions: Combine brans and salt.
Stir in boiling water.
Add buttermilk.
Cool.
In a separate bowl, cream sugar and oleo.
Add eggs.
Beat well.
Stir into bran mixture.
Combine flour and soda.
Add other ingredients and bake at 375°.
Fill greased muffin cups 2/3 full.
Makes approximately 3 dozen muffins. Freezes very well.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Sift all dry ingredients together and add to creamed mixture, alternating with mashed bananas.
Mix in nuts.
Divide into 2 well-greased loaf pans.
Bake at 250° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: butterscotch brownies
directions: Heat oven to 375° and melt butter in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put brown sugar in a large mixer bowl and pour melted butter over it. Cream butter and sugar and beat in eggs.
Mix in flour, baking powder, vanilla and pecans and pour back into already buttered pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until brownies begin to pull away from sides of pan.
When cool, cut in squares.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add sour cream and soda; add 2 eggs. Add flour 1 cup at a time until all is used.
Add flavoring.
Put in greased Bundt pan or big stem pan.
Bake at 325° for about 1 hour.
Let cool in pan for 10 minutes.

title: toasted coconut cake
directions: Blend the cake mix, pudding, eggs, oil, mayonnaise, margarine, baking powder and water; beat at medium speed for 4 minutes.
Stir in coconut.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes, or until it springs back when lightly touched.

title: sensational beef stroganoff
directions: Slice beef across the grain into thin strips.
In skillet over high heat in 1 tablespoon hot margarine, cook 1/2 the beef and 1/2 the onion until beef is no longer pink and onion is tender.
Set aside.
Repeat with remaining margarine, beef and onion.
Return mixture to skillet.
Stir in soup and paprika.
Heat through, stirring occasionally.
Reduce heat to very low.
Stir in sour cream.
Gently heat; serve over noodles.
Garnish with parsley. Preparation time:
10 minutes.
Cook time:
12 minutes.

title: salmon and pasta stuffed tomatoes
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions.
Drain and set aside.
Combine salmon, yogurt, cucumber, carrot, mayonnaise, dill weed, salt and pepper.
Toss with pasta.
Cover.
Chill 4 to 24 hours.

title: oreo pudding
directions: Mix together cream cheese, sugar and margarine.
Mix together instant pudding, milk and Cool Whip.
Mix cream cheese mixture and instant pudding mixture together.

title: strawberry fig jam
directions: Put all ingredients in large pan.
Bring to boil. Stir constantly.
Boil at least 2-3 minutes to dissolve sugar.
Put into freezer boxes and freeze, or put into jelly jars and process 10 minutes in boiling water to seal jars.

title: brownies
directions: Butter 9-inch pan; dust with flour.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: italian wedding soup
directions: Wash spinach and chop in small pieces.
Cook in small amount of water until barely soft.
Drain and press out all water.
Cook pastina.
Heat broth until boiling.

title: ham 'n swiss broccoli quiche
directions: Cut butter and shortening into flour.
Add ice cold water, a tablespoon at a time, until you can form dough into a ball.
Put the pie crust in a 9-inch pie pan.

title: molded cream cheese mints
directions: Mash cream cheese.
Gradually add 1/2 of the powdered sugar. Add flavoring and coloring.
Work in remaining powdered sugar until stiff like pie dough.

title: gramma's pumpkin cookies
directions: Mix brown sugar, pumpkin, oil and vanilla.
Stir dry ingredients together, add to pumpkin mixture and stir until smooth.
Blend in raisins and nuts.
Drop by spoonfuls onto greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 3 to 4 dozen.

title: lasagne gustoso(makes 6 to 8 servings)
directions: Cook noodles as package directs.
Brown beef and onion in butter.
Add 1 can pizza sauce, tomato paste, garlic salt and oregano.
Simmer 10 to 15 minutes.
In a 2-quart buttered shallow baking dish, layer 1/3 of noodles, 1/3 of beef and 1/3 of cheeses. Repeat once.
Then layer remaining noodles and beef.
Spread with second can of pizza sauce and top with remaining cheeses.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 30 minutes.
Allow to stand at room temperature for 10 minutes before cutting into squares for serving.

title: appetizer ham ball
directions: Blend ham, olives and mustard to taste.
Form into ball on serving dish.
Combine cream cheese and milk, frost ham ball. Chill.
Remove from refrigerator 15 minutes before serving.
Trim with parsley.
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Mix together the scallion, radishes, cucumber, cottage cheese and sour cream. Place a few leaves of lettuce on a serving dish and scoop the cottage cheese mixture onto it. Serve. Yield: 1 serving.

title: heath bar dessert
directions: Crush Pecan Sandies and add 1 stick oleo (melted); mix together.
Put crumbs in bottom of 9 x 13-inch dish.
Mix with spoon 2 packages vanilla instant pudding and 1 cup milk.
Stir in 1 quart soft vanilla ice cream.
Put this mixture over the cookie crust.
Let this set in refrigerator for 1 hour.
Put layer of Cool Whip on top of pudding mixture.
Crush 5 Heath bars and put on top of Cool Whip.
Let set for 24 hours.

title: open-face reuben sandwiches
directions: Heat oven to
Spread
toast lightly with mustard and place on
ungreased
cookie sheet.	Cut through sauerkraut with scissors.
Stir
in
corned
beef, cheese and mayonnaise. Spread about 1/3 cup
mixture
on	each
slice of toast.
Bake until sauerkraut mixture is hot and cheese is melted, about 10 minutes. Cut sandwiches in half.
May do in microwave oven.

title: congealed salad
directions: Drain crushed pineapple and heat juice.
Remove from heat and add lemon gelatin.
Set gelatin in pan of ice cubes and begin cooling, but don't let congeal.
When cool, beat in Dream Whip until stiff.
Add cream cheese to whip and mix well.
Add gelatin to mix.
Add chopped pecans and the crushed pineapple. Refrigerate.

title: ham delights
directions: Slice open rolls.
Spread mixture of butter, Worcestershire sauce, poppy seed, mustard and onion on both sides of rolls. Lay ham on one side and top with cheese.
Cover with the other side of rolls.
Set back in original foil roll tray and cut between each roll to divide.
Wrap in foil.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix and whip until a little stiff. Turn into a graham cracker shell and chill.

title: american chop suey
directions: Fry onions, green pepper and celery slightly, then add ground beef and partially cook.
Add cooked macaroni, soup and tomatoes. Use bacon fat for frying and let simmer, this gives a good flavor.

title: better batter rolls
directions: Combine 2
cups
flour,
yeast and salt in mixing bowl. Add water, oil,
honey
and
eggs; beat until smooth.
Beat in remaining flour by
hand.
Cover and let stand until double in size (about
minutes).
Fill
greased muffin pan half full and let rise until double in bulk (about 30 minutes).
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 2 dozen rolls.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Melt margarine in pan.
Add Pet milk and sugar.
Bring to boil and cook 12 minutes.
Take off stove and add peanut butter and marshmallow cream.
Whip until thick.
Pour out on two buttered plates.

title: black walnut pound cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and flour, leaving enough flour to dust walnuts.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat on medium speed.
Fold in walnuts.
Put in tube pan.
Put in cold oven.
Bake 3 hours at 250°.

title: john's sinus cure
directions: Process all ingredients in blender until smooth.
Sip as needed.
Makes 1 1/4 cups.
Try this sinus decongestant or as an early eye opener.

title: flaky prune foldovers
directions: Stir together pie crust mix and sour cream with a fork until well blended.
Form into a ball.
Cover and chill.

title: witches bread
directions: Mix ingredients.
Bake in 2 bread pans at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: light date nut cake(sugarless)
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and mix well.
Add Crisco and blend until mixture resembles coarse corn meal.
Add eggs and milk.
Beat well.
Add dates and nuts; mix.
Spoon into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: dump cake
directions: Sift the first 5 ingredients together.
Add remaining ingredients.
Grease a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pork chop skillet meal
directions: In a large skillet, brown chops in oil.
Drain.
Remove chops.
Combine water, rice, onion and 1/2 teaspoon salt in the skillet.
Place pork chops over rice mixture.
Top with corn and tomatoes.
Sprinkle with pepper and remaining salt.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 20 to 25 minutes or until pork and rice are tender.
Let stand for 5 minutes before serving.
Serves 4.

title: fruity milk shake
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender and blend until smooth, adding 5 ice cubes, one at a time.
Makes 4 servings.

title: melon mousse
directions: In a blender container or a food processor bowl, combine melon and orange juice.
Cover and blend or process until smooth.
In a small saucepan combine sugar and gelatin.
Stir in melon puree. Cook and stir over medium heat until gelatin and sugar are dissolved.
Chill until partially set (the consistency of unbeaten egg whites).

title: frizzled beef in brown milk gravy
directions: Melt the butter in a frying pan.
Add the dried beef, shredded and frizzle lightly.
Sprinkle 3 tablespoons flour over the dried beef.
Stir constantly.
Brown dried beef and flour until almost burnt.
Slowly add milk and stir until mixture boils.
Add dash of pepper.
If too thick, add another 1/2 cup milk.
Serve on toast or potatoes.

title: watergate dessert
directions: Crust:
Mix flour, margarine and sugar together well.
Chop nuts and mix with top three ingredients and pack in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: lemon pie
directions: Separate egg whites from yolks.
Add yolks to milk.
Mix.
Add lemon juice.
Mix until thickened.
Pour into graham cracker pie shell.
Cover with meringue made from egg whites.

title: coconut black walnut pound cake
directions: Combine sugar, oil and eggs; beat well.
Combine dry ingredients and add to sugar mixture with buttermilk.
Beat well. Stir in nuts, coconut and coconut extract.
Beat well again.
Pour into a well-greased and floured tube or Bundt pan.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour and 5 minutes.
Let cool before you remove from pan.

title: potato wedges
directions: Peel potatoes.
Put ingredients in bowl and mix well.
Melt stick of butter.
Dip potatoes in butter, then ingredients.
Put on shallow pan lined with foil.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: johnsonville sausage skillet dinner
directions: In large skillet, brown sausage links.	Remove from pan and cut
into 1/2-inch pieces.	Saute green pepper, onions and mushrooms in
butter.
Remove
from pan.
Add oil to pan; heat until hot.	Add
potatoes.	Brown;	turn
and
spread to cover bottom of pan.
Blend
eggs
and
milk
in small bowl and pour over potatoes.
Reduce
heat to low.
Add sausages and sauteed mixture.
Cover until eggs are set.
Uncover and sprinkle with cheese.
Cover
until
melted
and serve in wedges.
Also good for brunch or breakfast.

title: 7 layer pea salad
directions: Combine the sour cream, mayonnaise and sugar, then set aside. Layer in salad bowl the lettuce, bell pepper, green onion, cauliflower, English peas, radishes and celery, then pour dressing over top.
Then crumble bacon over the dressing.
Then sprinkle with Cheddar cheese.

title: prune filling
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients until tender. Put in processor with cinnamon, cloves and orange rind to taste.
Blend well.

title: nut and raisin cake
directions: Put butter, raisins, sugar, cinnamon and cloves in mixer and mix well. Boil water and add the mixture in the water in a big pan. Boil 1 minute after mixture is added. Add soda and let cool. After it is cool, add nuts and flour and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: scottish scones
directions: To sifted flour, baking powder and sugar, add and cut in shortening.
Add milk to egg to equal 3/4 cup.
Put raisins in flour mix.
Add egg/milk and stir.
Roll out on floured board. Bake at 350°.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together and put in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle with paprika and parsley flakes.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: dorito dip
directions: Using a microwave-safe dish, spread cream cheese on bottom of dish.
Layer chili over cream cheese; layer salsa on top of chili and top with grated cheese.
Cover and microwave until bubbly. Serve with dipping chips of your choice.

title: clam and corn casserole
directions: Drain liquid from clams and measure.
Add enough milk to make 3 cups.
Melt butter.
Add flour and blend until smooth.
Add liquid and cook over slow heat until boiling, stirring constantly.
Add clams and corn.
Season with salt and pepper and onion.
Pour into shallow casserole and cover with crumbs.
Bake in 350° oven about 15 minutes or until bubbly and brown.
Makes 6 servings.

title: low calorie vegetable dish
directions: Cook all together until vegetables are done.

title: ranger cookies
directions: Bake in 400° oven for 13 minutes.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Brown hamburger and onions.
Cook rest of ingredients, stirring often.
Add hamburger and onions.
Simmer for 40 to 45 minutes.
Remove bay leaves and serve.

title: meatball bubble biscuits
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Separate dough into 10 biscuits. Separate each biscuit into 2 layers.
Press each biscuit to form a 2 inch round.
Place 1 meatball half, cut side up and 1 string cheese piece in center of each dough round.
Wrap, pressing edges to seal.
Place seam side down, in single layer, on an ungreased 8 or 9 inch round cake pan.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese, Italian seasoning and garlic powder.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: skillet macaroni and cheese
directions: Melt butter in a skillet; add onion and saute until tender. Stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Add macaroni and milk.
Cover and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes or until macaroni is tender, stirring occasionally.
Add cheese and stir until melted (do not boil).

title: creamy caramel frosting
directions: Boil sugar, butter, syrup, and milk together until it forms soft ball in cold water.
Add other ingredients.
Beat well.

title: doggie oatmeal peanut butter cookies
directions: In mixing bowl combine dry ingredients.
Stir in drippings or safflower oil, eggs, milk, peanut butter and brown sugar or honey. With hands, pat dough out on lightly floured board and cut into biscuits the size suitable for your breed.
Put cut outs on baking sheet and bake in a 350° oven for about 20 minutes.

title: blueberry delight
directions: Mix cream cheese and Cool Whip together until creamy.
Slice cake into 3 layers.
On the bottom layer, spread cream cheese, Cool Whip mixture, then blueberries.
Put the second layer on. Add the cream cheese-Cool Whip mixture and blueberries.
Add the top cake layer; do the same.
Refrigerate.
Serve when ready.

title: japanese fruit cake
directions: Cream butter and 2 cups sugar.
Beat egg yolks and add to creamed mixture.
Sift 3 cups flour with baking powder and spices; add alternately with milk.
Add coconut, pecans and raisins which have been rolled in flour.
Beat egg whites and add.
Bake in moderate 350° oven about 30 minutes or until done.
Make 4 layers. Cool cake.

title: country chicken on a biscuit
directions: In large saucepan, combine 2 cups water and bouillon; heat until bouillon dissolves.
Remove frozen vegetables from pouch and add to broth; heat until thawed.
Combine flour with 1/2 cup water; stir until smooth.
Add to broth-vegetable mix.
Heat, stirring constantly, until thickened and smooth.
Add remaining ingredients; heat through.
Serve over hot baking powder biscuits. Serves 4.

title: taco casserole
directions: Melt cheese, sour cream, peppers and cut up tomatoes in a pan. Brown hamburger and onion in a skillet and drain off grease.
Add taco seasoning.
Have some Doritos broken up.
Mix both steps together.
Layer this mixture and Doritos in a 9 x 12-inch baking dish and brown in oven.
Leftovers will keep in deep freeze.

title: diabetes chocolate souffle
directions: Combine fructose, cornstarch, cocoa powder, instant coffee and cinnamon in a 2-quart saucepan.
Add milk and cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture comes to a boil and thickens.
Add vanilla.
Pour into a 1-quart bowl and cover surface of pudding with waxed paper to prevent "skin" formation. Chill for 1 hour.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold into chocolate mixture until fully incorporated. Spoon into individual 4 ounce dessert dishes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: new world spread
directions: Combine ingredients.
Refrigerate 3 hours to blend flavors. Serve with crackers.

title: bacon wrapped franks
directions: Cut hot dogs into 1/3 pieces (approximately 1-inch in length). Cut bacon slices in halves. Wrap 1/2 slice bacon around hot dog chunk and fasten with toothpick. Bake at 400° until bacon is crisp. Serve with favorite dip or barbecue sauce.

title: beef-olive spread
directions: Soften minced onion in dry sherry.
Blend cream cheese and mayonnaise.
Add the sherry and onion mixture.
Stir in snipped smoked beef and olives.
Serve on assorted crackers.

title: tomato aspic
directions: Heat 2 cups V-8 juice; add to jello to dissolve.
Add remaining 3 cups of juice (cold).
Add and mix all the remaining ingredients.
Pour into mold and chill until firm.

title: cold spaghetti
directions: Can add fresh mushrooms, broccoli, etc.
Be creative.

title: back pack snack
directions: In a large bowl, combine all ingredients.
Store in tightly covered container.
Makes 5 1/2 cups.

title: moma's easy cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in baking pan or dish. Mix sugar, flour, and milk and pour into pan.
Spoon fruit into mix.
Bake at 350 degrees until golden brown. Can use peaches or berries.
Usually a large can of drained slice peaches is best for making
peach cobbler.

title: hot fruit punch
directions: Simmer apple juice and spices 20 minutes.
Add sugar and remaining juices.
Stud oranges with cloves and add to punch. Heat, but do not boil.
Fill heated punch bowl.
Makes about 25 servings.

title: twice-baked potatoes
directions: Scrub potatoes; prick with a fork.
Wrap each in foil.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: mexican fudge
directions: Combine corn syrup, sugars, salt and milk; cook to soft ball stage.
Remove from heat; add marshmallows, margarine and pecans. Beat for about 5 minutes or until candy begins to lose luster. Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.

title: tiger surprises
directions: Spread peanut butter between 2 Ritz crackers.
Melt white chocolate and wax in double boiler over low heat.
Dip crackers in chocolate and cool on wax paper.

title: beef brisket in foil
directions: Put brisket on large piece of heavy duty foil.
Shake onion soup over meat and add water.
Turn up sides of foil and cover tightly.
Place on flat pan and bake at 350° for 2 1/2 hours. Remove foil, cool slightly and slice.
Put sliced beef in a casserole with the juice.
Pour over chili sauce, jelly and mushrooms with juice.
Bake 1/2 hour longer.

title: rosemary lemon roast beef
directions: Preheat oven to 350. Line a roasting pan with aluminum foil. Mix rosemary, garlic, lemon rind and 1/4 tsp pepper. Use narrow knife, make 12 slits 3/4 inch long and 1 inch deep, across the top of the roast. Use a spoon handle to widen the slits and push a rounded 1/4 tsp of mixture into each one, Sprinkle roast with any remaining
mixture, salt, pepper. Place roast on a rack in a roasting pan and roast for 1 hour and 30 minutes. Let stand for 15 minutes before carving.

title: muffulettas
directions: Split bread on round and brush with olive oil. Alternate ham and cheese. Top with Olive Salad and replace top.

title: sour cream hamburger casserole
directions: Brown ground beef, onion, mushrooms and bell pepper.
Drain. Mix soup, sour cream together then add meat, stir together.
In a 9 x 13-inch baking dish, place noodles on the bottom then add meat mixture.
Bake in oven at 350° until mixture is bubbly.

title: far-out fruit salad
directions: Mix ingredients together and chill.
Serve on a bed of crisp lettuce as a salad dish or luncheon platter.

title: beef cheese ball
directions: Cream the cream cheese; add chopped onions and pepper (optional).
Add beef, chopped fine.
Roll in parsley flakes. Chill before serving.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Put sugar, milk and marshmallows in pan, stirring constantly until marshmallows melt.
Boil 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add chocolate and margarine.
Beat until melted.
Add nuts and pour up into platter or cookie sheet.

title: sweet fried onion rings
directions: Mix first five ingredients in mixing bowl.
Cover and let sit at room temperature for 3 hours.
Peel onions and cut in 1/4-inch slices.
Dip onions in batter and deep fry for 3 to 5 minutes. Drain on paper towel; sprinkle with salt while still hot.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: wacky chocolate cake
directions: In an ungreased 9 x 9-inch pan mix the first 5 ingredients together with a fork.
Put 3 holes in batter.
In one hole, put 1 tablespoon vinegar, in second hole put vanilla and in third hole put melted butter.
Pour 1 cup water over all.
Stir with a fork. Bake 25 minutes at 350°.
After baked, while still hot, add 1 cup chocolate chips on the top.
Spread when melted.

title: jello-knox blocks(great for kids, no mess)
directions: Mix Jell-O and unflavored gelatine.
Add boiling water.
Mix thoroughly and pour into long serving dish (9 x 12-inch etc.). Chill until set.
Cut into squares.
Can be left out of refrigerator at room temperature once it is firm.
Kids love to eat "Jell-O" with their hands.
Garnish with Cool Whip.

title: crazy cake
directions: Sift flour, sugar, cocoa, salt and baking soda into 9 x 9-inch pan.
Make 3 holes in the mixture and add vanilla, vinegar and liquid shortening mixture.
Then pour cup of water over entire mixture.
Mix with fork until smooth.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until center springs back.
Serve plain or with whipped cream on top.

title: lemon pudding sauce
directions: Dissolve cornstarch in little cold water.
Add sugar to beaten egg; add cornstarch; stir in boiling water.
Add flavoring.
Cook in double boiler to right consistency and stir mixture.
Ready to go!

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Brown meat and onion together. Add soups and 1 3/4 cans water. Stir in chili powder and cook until thickened. Add
sauce. Put in 13 x 9 casserole dish over spaghetti. Spread soup over meat mixture, sprinkle with cheese. Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: cheddar broccoli salad
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Refrigerate at least 4 hours before serving.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Mix by hand.
Blend all dry ingredients, then add the other ingredients.
Grease and flour 3 cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
When cool, frost.

title: layered enchilada casserole
directions: Heat oil in a 10-inch skillet.
Add beef, onions and garlic and cook until brown, stirring occasionally.
Drain and discard excess fat.
Stir in stewed tomatoes, olives, chili powder, salt and pepper.
Layer half the potatoes in 10 x 2-inch casserole (about 2-quart capacity).
Cover with half the meat mixture. Sprinkle with coarsely crumbled corn chips and 1 cup cheese. Spoon remaining meat mixture over and top with remaining potatoes. Cover with foil.
Bake in a 375° oven for 30 minutes.
Remove foil and sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake, uncovered, 15 minutes longer.
Makes 6 servings.

title: shrimp and cheese cracker spread
directions: Spread softened cream cheese in bottom of serving dish.
Drain shrimp and mix with cocktail sauce in separate bowl.
Spread mixture on top of cream cheese. Cut scallions in small pieces and sprinkle on top of shrimp mixture.
Cover all with shredded Monterey Jack and chill.
Serve with crackers.

title: garlic gnocchi
directions: Peel potatoes and quarter.
Boil with garlic until soft (about 15 minutes).
Drain.

title: fried chicken - dolly's style
directions: Soak chicken in salty water and refrigerate overnight.
Drain well.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Dredge in flour.
Place chicken into milk for 10 minutes. dredge in flour again. Then sprinkle on dressing mix. Place in hot oil (365° to 370°).
Fry until golden brown.

title: date honey crisp tops
directions: Combine honey and butter. Heat until melted and bubbly.
Add dates and cereal.
Mix well.
Turn into buttered 9-inch square pan. When cool, cut in squares and serve with butterscotch ice cream. MMMMMMMMMM!!!!!

title: grandma landeck's coconut cream pie
directions: In a saucepan combine sugar, flour and salt.
Gradually stir in milk. Cook and stir over medium heat until bubbly.
Cook and stir 2 minutes. Remove from heat.

title: microwave cheese quesadillas
directions: Heat flour tortilla in microwave for 10 to 20 seconds to soften.
Slice or grate cheese onto tortilla and add 1 tablespoon of salsa.
Roll up and fold ends.
Heat for
1 minute or until cheese is melted.
Cut into 4 even pieces.

title: hot chicken wings
directions: Heat oil in deep frying pan.
In a bowl, salt and pepper flour as to your taste.
Dip chicken wings in a bowl with buttermilk until covered, then dip wings in the flour.
Repeat. Place wings in hot oil.
Fry until wings are cooked.
Take out of oil and place onto a platter.
With a brush, coat each wing completely with the sauce mixture.
Enjoy with lots of your favorite beverage.

title: nutty graham cracker cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Spread in an 11 x 13-inch pan that has been sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let cool.
Cut in squares and roll in powdered sugar.

title: chess squares
directions: Mix cake mix, margarine and 1 egg and press lightly in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cream cheese and xxx sugar plus 2 eggs.
Pour over first mixture and bake 30 to 35 minutes at 400°.

title: cream cheese bars
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Warm crescent rolls to room temperature.
Unroll 1 package and cover bottom of jelly roll pan. Mix cream cheese, sugar and egg.
Spread cream cheese, sugar and egg mixture on top of crescent rolls.
Spread 2nd package of crescent rolls on top.
Sprinkle with cinnamon, sugar and nutmeg. Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: chocolate-bran raisin jumbos
directions: Beat margarine; gradually add sugar, beating well at medium speed of an electric mixer.
Add cocoa mix, egg substitute and vanilla, beating until well blended.
Combine flour, soda and salt; add to creamed mixture, mixing well.
Stir in cereal.

title: easy sausage balls
directions: Crumble the sausage and mix with cheese. Add biscuit mix one cup at a time. Form into small balls about 1-inch in diameter and place on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in a preheated 350° to 375° oven until light brown (13 to 15 minutes). Makes 7 dozen.

title: banana bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom only of a loaf pan, 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch.
Mix sugar and butter in a 2 1/2-quart bowl. Stir in eggs until blended.
Add bananas and water; beat 30 seconds.
Stir in remaining ingredients except nuts just until moistened; stir in nuts.
Pour into pan.
Bake until a toothpick inserted in center comes out clean, 1 hour to 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes.
Loosen sides of pan and remove.
Cool completely before slicing.

title: old fashioned southern cornbread dressing
directions: Mix breads; add raw eggs and other ingredients.
Mix well. Have dressing soft, about the consistency of cake batter or thick soup.
(This is the secret of good dressing.)
Bake in greased baking dish (13 x 9 1/2-inch) for about 40 minutes, or stuff bird with the uncooked dressing.

title: strawberry jello salad
directions: Mix jello and hot water.
Add strawberries and pineapple. Slice banana in bottom of square pan.
Pour half of gelatin mixture over banana and chill until firm.
Spread evenly with sour cream.
Pour remaining gelatin mixture on top and chill.

title: unforgettable biscuits
directions: Mix warm water, 1 teaspoon of sugar and yeast. Let stand 5 minutes until bubbles.
Mix remaining ingredients in large bowl.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix pudding and pineapple together.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Add chopped nuts.
Refrigerate.

title: glazed fruit salad
directions: Empty into bowl and reserve juices from fruits.
