Add 2 cups juice to one small box of vanilla pudding.
Mix as directed.
Pour over fruit, being sure bananas are covered so will not turn dark.

title: chocolate peanut squares
directions: Microwave 3/4 cup margarine and 2 ozs. chocolate squares on High 1 to 2 minutes or until melted when stirred, stirring every 30 seconds. Stir in crumbs, coconut and peanuts.
Press onto bottom of a 9 x 13 pan, chill 30 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Place chicken in bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Mix soup and pour over chicken.
Dot with butter.
Sprinkle stuffing mix on top.
Pour chicken broth over entire mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pizza bomb for one(microwave)
directions: Place tortilla on a plate.
Spread with sauce and sprinkle with Parmesan and Mozzarella.
Place pineapple and Canadian bacon on top.
Microwave 1 minute on High until cheese starts to melt. Fold over tortilla in half.
Microwave 30 seconds to 1 minute or until filling is hot.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Mix potatoes and 1/2 cup butter with onions, soup, sour cream and cheese.
Pour into greased 9 x 14-inch dish.
Crush croutons and mix with the rest of the melted butter (1/4 cup) and sprinkle over top. Bake for 50 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken breasts supreme
directions: Brown chicken until golden brown.
Place chicken in casserole dish and add pan drippings, soup, sherry, almonds and mushrooms. Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve with rice.

title: deep dish taco squares
directions: Mix Bisquick and water; put on well-greased cookie sheet 1/2 inch up on sides.
Brown hamburger with taco seasoning, pepper and salt.
Stir together the mayonnaise and sour cream.
Put hamburger on crust.
Add vegetables, then top with sour cream mixture.
Put on cheese and paprika last.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chicken pie
directions: Remove skin and bones from chicken; place in a pan.
Mix together broth and soup; pour over chicken.
Mix butter, flour and milk; pour over chicken.
Top with eggs.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: reuben potato casserole
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients.
Use milk to thin mayonnaise.
Add remaining ingredients to mayonnaise mixture; mix well.
Toss this mixture with the first mixture.
Serve immediately or warm up in oven or slow cooker.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cook and drain carrots (still firm).
Add onion and green pepper.
Combine soup, vinegar, oil, sugar and mustard.
Mix well. Pour over carrots, toss lightly.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: hawaiian toast
directions: Place a slice of ham on toast.
Add slice of cheese.
Top with pineapple slice.
Microwave or broil just until cheese begins to melt.
Garnish with maraschino cherry.
Yummy breakfast that kids can prepare.

title: venison steaks in red wine
directions: Add water to wine to cover steaks.
Let stand 4 to 5 hours. Use glass or china bowl.
Remove, dry and roll in flour.
Season to taste.
Fry in cooking oil.
Add sliced fresh mushrooms, marinade and simmer.
Remove meat.
Thicken gravy to serve.

title: king ranch chicken casserole
directions: Combine soups, tomatoes and broth to make a sauce.

title: sliced baked potatoes for microwave
directions: Peel potatoes.
Cut potatoes into thin slices but not all the way through.
Use a handle of a spoon to prevent knife from cutting all the way.
Place potatoes in micro-safe dish.
Sprinkle with melted butter and herbs of your choice.
Microwave at High power for 10 minutes, rearranging the potatoes after 5 minutes. Let rest 5 minutes.

title: fudge
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients for 5 minutes after it comes to a boil.
Turn off and add the last 4 ingredients.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool.

title: italian chocolate cookies
directions: Measure all dry ingredients in large bowl.
Cut in Crisco. Add milk and mix.
Then add nuts and raisins.
Chill dough.
Roll into balls.
Cool and ice.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: candied yams
directions: Heat potatoes on low to medium heat.
Mash them.
Add milk to consistency of mashed potatoes.
Add butter, sugar and vanilla. Mix all ingredients.
Taste until sweet enough.
Pour into greased casserole.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.
Top with marshmallows; bake 5 minutes more.

title: mann's holiday dressing
directions: Mix together in large mixing bowl.
Can add up to 1 cup additional water if needed for moistness.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch lightly greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: marinated vegetable salad
directions: Heat sugar, oil, vinegar, water, salt and pepper and cool.
Mix all ingredients together and marinate overnight.

title: carrots and onions with sauce
directions: Cook carrots in water (enough to cover) with chicken bouillon cube until tender, approximately 10 minutes, reserving stock. Melt butter in medium or large saucepan.
Add onions; cook until tender, stirring occasionally.
Stir in flour, salt, pepper, sugar, lemon juice and water (stock).
Blend and bring to a boil. Add carrots; simmer, uncovered, for 5 to 10 minutes.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Beat cream cheese until soft and smooth.
Add all other ingredients except crab meat.
Mix well.
Add crab.
Place in casserole dish.
Top with 1/2 cup cheese.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Serve with crackers.

title: butter cake squares
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients; pat into a greased 9 x 12-inch pan. Mix the next 3 ingredients and pour over cake mixture.
Top with nuts, if desired.
Bake for 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: low-fat applesauce bran muffins
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients, then stir in egg and applesauce or pineapple.
In large bowl, mix remaining ingredients.
Add Bran mixture to flour mixture; stir just until moistened.
Spoon into 12 muffin cups and bake 18 to 20 minutes at 400°.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake in a greased 9 x 13-inch casserole dish at 350° for 1 hour.

title: five hour beef stew
directions: Put into a casserole dish in order given.
Do not stir.
Cover and bake at 250° for 5 to 5 1/2 hours.
(Can use a small roast, cubed.)

title: banana cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Oil sides and bottoms of 3 (2 pound) loaf pans.
In a large bowl, mix banana cake mix, eggs, water, Puritan oil and a tincture of nutmeg and cinnamon; beat until well blended.
Pour into pans and bake until a toothpick inserted into the center comes out clean.

title: spinach-cottage cheese casserole(six to eight servings)
directions: Cook spinach and drain.
Combine ingredients.
Put in 11 x 7-inch pan.
Bake uncovered 45 minutes at 350°.

title: pam swanner's peanut butter bars
directions: Melt margarine and crunchy peanut butter over low heat.
Add powdered sugar and stir well.
Pour into medium, buttered baking dish (7 1/2 x 12-inch).
Spread and cool.

title: it's wonderful
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Drain.
Cook rice as directed on package.
Mix rest of ingredients together.
Bake in a 9 x 12-inch pan for 1 hour, covered, at 350°.
Sprinkle top with Parmesan cheese.

title: one bowl buttercream frosting
directions: Cream butter in small mixer bowl.
Add cocoa and confectioners sugar alternately with milk.
Beat to spreading consistency (additional tablespoon of milk may be needed).
Blend in vanilla. Yields about two cups frosting.

title: crock-pot pork chops
directions: Season pork chops and batter in flour.
Fry in grease until both sides are brown.
Place 4 to 5 browned pork chops in 1/4 cup water in crock-pot.
Add 1 can cream of celery soup, 1/2 of chopped onion, 1/4 cup celery and 1/4 cup bell pepper.
Repeat with remaining ingredients, adding the Cheddar cheese soup to the top of mixture.
Cover and cook on high 5 to 6 hours.
Cook on low heat if cooking chops overnight.
The chops will fall away from the bone when done.

title: crisp crusted baked chicken
directions: Beat egg.
Add milk in bowl.
In another bowl, mix potatoes, cheese and garlic.
Roll chicken, first in egg then in potato mixture.
Melt butter in shallow, glass baking pan.
Roll coated chicken in butter and arrange in pan.
Bake at 400° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Time may vary depending on size of breasts.
Serves 6.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all together until incorporated and shape into a ball. Roll in 1 package of broken walnuts.

title: philadelphia cream cheese salad
directions: In a medium bowl, place cream cheese and mayonnaise.
Let cream cheese soften.
In another bowl, whip the whipping cream until it peaks.
Leaving whipping cream on beaters, blend cream cheese and mayonnaise until smooth.
Add fruit cocktail, marshmallows and whipping cream to cream cheese.
Stir together with a spoon.
Add red food coloring to color to a delicate shade of pink.
Refrigerate.

title: tabbouleh
directions: Pour boiling water over the wheat to cover generously and let sit for 10 minutes.
Pour off excess liquid.
Add tomatoes, parsley and onions; mix well.
Combine lemon juice, salt, oil, mint and pepper.
Pour over the vegetable mixture.
Toss lightly and refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: crab dish
directions: Saute onion and jalapenos in butter.
Add garlic and mushrooms; saute 5 to 7 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add mustard and sour cream; heat to a boil.
Add crabmeat and heat through. Serve over rice that has been cooked in equal portions of beer and water.

title: onion soup dip
directions: Blend onion soup mix with sour cream and fold in crumbled cheese and nuts.

title: chocolate chip cheese ball
directions: Mix all together.
Refrigerate 2 hours, then roll into ball, then refrigerate.
Roll on chopped pecan before serving.
Delicious with graham crackers.

title: mickey's pasta salad
directions: Add any or all of the following:
carrots, celery, broccoli, cauliflower, 1 can of artichokes, can of sliced mushrooms, 1 package frozen pea pods, black and green olives, onion, garlic, oregano, paprika, red chili pepper.
Prepare and let set in refrigerator 4 hours or overnight.

title: potato salad
directions: Make potatoes like mashed potatoes, just cut the egg white up into the potatoes.
Mix the egg yolks and mustard with mayonnaise together.
Then mix with potatoes; add onions.
Stir all together. Slice leftover eggs; lay on top.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Cut in shortening.
Dissolve yeast in warm water and add with buttermilk to dry mixture.
Mix well; turn out on lightly floured board.
Roll to 1/2-inch thickness.
Bake on cookie sheet at 400° for 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: cheese and crab dip
directions: Combine cheese and milk in a saucepan.
Stir over low heat until cheese melts.
Stir in wine and crabmeat.
Heat through.

title: hot chicken souffle
directions: Place half the bread slices in 9 x 13-inch glass pan.
Mix diced chicken, mayonnaise, onion and celery.
Spread over bread. Place remaining bread over mixture.
Mix eggs and milk together and pour over mixture.
Place, covered with Saran Wrap, in refrigerator overnight.

title: sweet milk biscuits
directions: Mix and sift dry ingredients.
Rub in shortening.
Add milk (enough to make a soft dough).
Roll 1-inch thick and cut into rounds.
Bake in hot oven at 425° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: jellied beet salad
directions: Put together in order given.
Makes 6 individual molds or one mold, as desired.

title: chicken noodle soup
directions: In a pan, add chicken chunks, celery, onion and carrots.
Mix in the chicken broth and cream of chicken.
Add a touch of salt and pepper.
If needed, use water to thin soup.
You may also add a touch of parsley for color.

title: german chocolate upside-down surprise cake
directions: Evenly sprinkle nuts and coconut on bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan.
In a large bowl combine cake mix, water, eggs and oil.
Mix on slow speed until moistened.
Mix 2 minutes longer on high. Pour batter over nuts and coconut.
Combine in another bowl melted margarine, powdered sugar and cream cheese.
Beat until creamy and smooth.
Pour over cake batter to within 1 inch from edge all around pan.
Bake at 375° for 43 to 53 minutes, until toothpick comes out clean in center of cake.
Cool completely.
Cut in squares and invert each square on plate.

title: asparagus and egg casserole
directions: Arrange half of the asparagus in bottom of greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with slices of egg, pepper and salt; sprinkle with cheese.
Spoon in half of white sauce.
Repeat in alternate layers.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for about 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: lemon yum yum
directions: Use 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: conulle cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well (except ladyfingers).
Make 2 days before ready to use.
Line 9-inch spring-form pan on sides and bottom with lady fingers.
Then put half of the Ricotta mixture, another layer of ladyfingers and a second layer of Ricotta mixture over top.
Top with ladyfingers.
Cover with whipped cream on top and sides.

title: chocolate cookie sheet cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar and salt together in large bowl.
In saucepan, bring to boil margarine, shortening, water and cocoa. Pour over flour mixture and mix well.
In another bowl, beat eggs. Add soda, buttermilk and vanilla.
Combine egg mixture with flour mixture, mixing well.
Bake in greased 15 x 16 x 1-inch cookie sheet for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: mexican souffl
directions: Layer ham, cheese and chilies in a 9 x 9 pan.

title: sausage biscuits
directions: Cook sausage, drain and crumble.
Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and baking soda.
Cut shortening into mixture until texture is like cornmeal.
Stir in sausage and buttermilk.
Knead on floured board 10 times.
Roll out to 1/2-inch thick.
Cut with 3/4-inch round biscuit cutter.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Peel and grate potatoes; mix with onion and milk. Mix with salt, egg and flour.
Drop by tablespoon into hot fat in skillet. Brown on both sides.

title: instant gourmet bread
directions: Add herbs to melted butter.
Separate biscuits and cut each in half.
Dip each piece of biscuit in butter-herbs mixture. Stand pieces on the flat edges, side by side, 5 across, in a small loaf pan.
Pour remaining butter mixture over biscuits and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: grandma's english toffee
directions: Combine all ingredients in a heavy pan except nuts and chocolate chips.

Stirring constantly, cook over medium heat until candy thermometer reads 300° or until candy is thick and golden. Spread on buttered cookie sheet, then sprinkle with chocolate chips. Spread chips evenly melted and top is completely covered. Sprinkle with almond pieces and refrigerate to set. Crack into pieces before serving.

title: asparagus vinaigrette
directions: Blend in blender 15 seconds.
Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Shake.
Keeps well.
Yields 1 1/2 cups.

title: chicken and stuffing casserole
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch glass pan with butter.
Line uncooked chicken breast on bottom.
Layer sliced mushrooms on top of chicken.
Layer sliced cheese on top of mushrooms.
Spread and pat down Stove Top stuffing over layer of mushrooms.
Pour undiluted soup over stuffing.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours or until brown.

title: graham cracker cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; stir in egg yolks.
Mix baking powder and flour; add to graham crackers.
Add flour mixture to butter mixture, a little at a time, with milk and water.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Fold in egg whites.
Bake in a 375° oven for 30 to 35 minutes in greased and floured 9-inch pans.

title: creme de menthe brownies
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add beaten eggs and vanilla.
Add and mix well flour, salt and chocolate syrup.
Pour batter into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in a preheated 325° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: bananas foster
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine all the ingredients and blend. Pour into pie crust and bake 45 minutes.
Cool and cut.

title: swedish rice dessert
directions: Cook rice in milk until thick and creamy.
Add salt.
Dissolve gelatine in cold water and add to hot rice.
Let cool until it begins to set.
Whip cream; add sugar and almond flavoring and mix with rice.
Set in mold.
Serve with Crimson Raspberry Sauce.

title: salad supreme
directions: Layer ingredients in large bowl in the order listed (lettuce, peas, cauliflower, green onions).
Sprinkle Bac*Os over top. Sprinkle Salad Supreme spice over top.
Spread mayonnaise over entire top of salad, making sure that it goes from side to side (sealing the salad with mayonnaise).
Sprinkle layer of Parmesan cheese over mayonnaise.
Set overnight or for 25 hours.
After tossing (before serving), croutons may be sprinkled on top.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Mix sweet potatoes, sugar (white), eggs, milk, salt, butter and vanilla together and pour into buttered pan.
Combine the brown sugar, flour, butter and pecans to make a topping.
Crumble over the potato mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes, uncovered.

title: good for you dessert
directions: Break cake into small pieces.
Mix yogurt, Cool Whip and fruit.
Pour over cake; stir and chill.
Makes light, low calorie, low-fat dessert.

title: potato salad with homemade mayonnaise
directions: Cook potatoes and boil 6 eggs.
Strain potatoes and set aside. Take the yolk out of the boiled eggs.
Set whites aside.
Add 3 uncooked yolks to the cooked yolks and mash out lumps.
Add just a little vinegar to the yolks and mix.
Then add 1 cup olive oil to yolks and stir until thick.
Keep adding olive oil until you have enough mayonnaise.
Then add your seasoning; cut up egg whites and add.
Mix with potatoes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients in separate large bowl.
Beat eggs until fluffy.
Add sugar.
Add oil and vanilla; then add zucchini. Gradually stir in flour.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until toothpick comes out clean.
Bake in 2 greased 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/4-inch loaf pans.

title: spicy thai-style chicken and rice
directions: Combine chicken and soy sauce in shallow bowl; set aside. Heat oil in a 10-inch skillet over medium heat.
Add rice and garlic; cook and stir 1 minute.
Stir in broth, water, peanut butter and pepper flakes.
Bring to a boil, stirring until peanut butter is melted.
Place chicken over rice mixture, adding soy sauce to skillet.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes. Stir in pea pods and ginger; sprinkle with pepper strips.
Remove from heat.
Let stand, covered, until all liquid is absorbed, about 5 minutes.
Sprinkle with peanuts, if desired.
Serves 5 to 6.

title: mocha angel food cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on package except stir cocoa into dry cake mix and substitute cold coffee for water.
Bake and cool as directed.
Remove from tube pan but do not turn upside-down. Glaze the crusted top and embellish with walnut halves, if desired.
The glaze ingredients can vary, depending on your choice.
This is a very attractive cake and so easy.
Always a hit and healthy!

title: fish rolls
directions: With paper towels, clean and dry fish fillets.
If wide, cut in half lengthwise.
Combine salt, pepper and basil.
Sprinkle on fish.
Blend stuffing, egg and lemon juice.
Fill fillets with stuffing.
Roll up jelly roll fashion.
Fasten with toothpicks. Combine clam chowder and sour cream.
Pour over rolls.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Drain all vegetables.
Saute celery, onion and peppers first. Mix together with drained vegetables.
Mix butter and almonds. Top casserole with this mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: four layer delight
directions: Cream ingredients together.
Spread into bottom of 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Let cool.

title: miracle icing
directions: Boil water and sugar 3 minutes.
Add boiled mixture to beaten egg whites and beat 5 minutes.
Put cream of tartar in egg whites before you beat them.
Add vanilla.

title: banana walnut cake
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat together bananas and butter until creamy.
Add eggs and water.
Beat well.
Stir in flour, baking powder, soda and cinnamon.
Beat until smooth.
Add chopped walnuts.

title: grove house dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together until well blended. Use immediately or store in refrigerator.

title: curried deviled eggs
directions: Leaving egg whites intact gently remove yolks. In medium bowl, mash yolks with fork.
Stir in mayonnaise, chutney, vinegar and curry powder.
Spoon rounded tablespoon of mixture into each egg white.
Cover with plastic wrap; chill.
Remove from refrigerator 30 minutes before serving.

title: hi-c holiday punch
directions: Mix chilled ingredients over ice. Garnish as desired.
Makes 35 servings.

title: lemon tea cakes
directions: Grease and lightly flour a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan; set aside.

title: in a hurry spoon biscuits
directions: Mix bacon grease or lard in the flour.
Then pour in a little milk to mix into dough in the bowl.
Spoon onto a cookie sheet or cake pan that's metal and use any leftover grease to rub the tops in.
Then bake at 400° until slightly brown on top and eat!

title: taco salad
directions: Mix lettuce, tomato and onion in a large salad bowl.
Add bitters to hamburg and cook meat in skillet until brown and crumbly.
Drain off fat.
Add tomato sauce, chili powder, salt and pepper.
Mix well and cook 5 minutes.
Pour meat mixture over salad, toss well.
Top with Doritos and cheese.
Toss just before serving.
Either Doritos or tortilla chips will do.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Mix cabbage, onion, salt and pepper. Set aside. Melt margarine in Pyrex dish. When melted, add cabbage mixture. Set aside. Mix
milk, mayonnaise and soup. Pour over cabbage mixture. Mix together cheese and cracker crumbs. Sprinkle cheese and crumb mixture over cabbage. Bake at 350° until done.

title: rave reviews cake
directions: Combine cake mix, pudding mix, water, eggs and oil in large bowl.
Blend.
Beat at medium speed 4 minutes. Stir in coconut and nuts. Pour into greased, floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Cool 15 minutes.
Remove from pan. Cool on rack.

title: chicken breasts and rice
directions: Place chicken in a 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Lay cheese over chicken.
Mix celery soup and sherry.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle generously with seasoned croutons and butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: golden summer punch
directions: Add ginger ale just before serving.
Serves 35 to 40 guests.

title: cheesecake brownies
directions: Mix 2 eggs, margarine and cake mix.
Put in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch greased and floured cake pan. Beat 3 eggs.
Add cream cheese and powdered sugar. Beat with mixer 3 minutes.
Pour over first mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes. Turn off oven and let stand in oven for 5 more minutes. Remove from oven. Cool, cut and serve.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix sugars, oleo and
milk
together and cook on medium heat until it forms a hard
ball
stage.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter, marshmallows
and
walnuts.	Put
in square buttered pan and allow to harden.

title: ice cream cake
directions: Crush Oreos with a food processor or with a rolling pin, putting cookies in a bag.
Melt butter.
Mix into cookie crumbs. Press into a 9 x 12-inch pan, sprayed with a non-stick vegetable spray.

title: easy baked beans
directions: Saute bacon until almost crisp, add onions.
Continue to saute until onion is tender.
Drain excess fat.
Combine bacon and onion with beans.
Add remaining ingredients in 1-quart casserole dish. Bake uncovered in 375° oven 50 to 55 minutes or until hot.
Stir occasionally.
Serves 6.

title: yummy cookies
directions: Cream the margarine.
Add sugar until light.
Add eggs and beat.
Add flour, salt and baking soda and stir in rest of ingredients.
Drop by heaping teaspoonful on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 minutes at 375°.

title: lemon bread
directions: Mix lemon juice and 1/3 cup sugar while bread bakes to dissolve sugar well.
Mix butter and sugar; beat in eggs.
Mix together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk to the creamed mixture.
Fold in lemon rind and nuts. Bake in a greased bread tin at 350° for 50 minutes.
As soon as bread is removed from oven, pour lemon juice and sugar over the top of bread.
Cool thoroughly, about 24 hours, before slicing.
Bread freezes well.

title: chocolate cream cheese brownies
directions: Mix by hand the cake mix, 2 eggs and melted margarine.
This will be very thick!
Pour onto greased cookie sheet or 9 x 13 pan. Mix together the cream cheese, sugar and 1 egg.
Pour on top of cake mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: wacky cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together in buttered pan.
Make 3 depressions in sifted ingredients.
In one hole, put melted shortening, in second hole put the vanilla and in third hole, put the vinegar.
Pour the lukewarm water over all and stir well. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: spicy apples and oats(for microwave)
directions: Peel and slice apples.
In 8 or 9-inch round baking dish, layer half the apples.
Combine sugar, nuts, cinnamon and nutmeg; sprinkle half sugar mixture over apples.
Top with remaining apples.
Into remaining sugar mixture, blend in butter, flour and oats.
Sprinkle over apples.
Heat 5 minutes on High in microwave. Let stand 5 minutes.
Serve warm or cold.

title: dump salad
directions: Mix together the pudding mix and Cool Whip.
Then add the pineapple to the cottage cheese.
Mix it all together.

title: french fried onion rings
directions: Dissolve bouillon cube in boiling water and cool.
Beat together pancake mix, egg and oil.
Add cooled water mixture.
Dip onion ring in the liquid mixture.
Drain a minute; fry them in the heated oil.

title: easy corn pudding
directions: Mix eggs and milk together; add corn.
Pour in greased baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until set.

title: "cretons"
directions: Mix all the ingredients.
Bring to a boil slowly, stirring often at the beginning, and simmer for 1 hour.
Mix for 3 minutes with electric mixer and let it cool.

title: polynesian orange balls
directions: Blend sugar and butter.
Add vanilla wafer crumbs and orange juice.
Mix well.
Add chopped pecans.
Roll into balls and roll in coconut.

title: lemon pudding salad
directions: Combine in bowls.
Cool in refrigerator a couple hours.

title: uncle butch's sugar pie
directions: Cook until very thick. Remove from heat and stir in 3 sticks real butter and 3 teaspoons real vanilla. Pour into 2 baked 9-inch pie crusts; bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Dust lightly with cinnamon when done.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together (sift them first).
Add oil, eggs and vanilla and blend well.
Bake in 3 (9-inch) pans at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: crab fettuccine
directions: Cook fettuccine according to package directions; drain.
Heat butter and garlic in skillet on medium until garlic is lightly browned.
Add half and half, crab and pepper; heat about 3 minutes or until bubbling, stirring occasionally.
Add Parmesan cheese and stir 1 minute.
Remove from heat and toss with fettuccine.
Serve with additional Parmesan cheese, if desired.

title: orange carrots
directions: Combine all ingredients in a 1-quart casserole.
Cover; microwave at High (100%) until carrots are tender, 4 to 6 minutes, stirring after half the cooking time.

title: tortillas
directions: Whiz water, oats and seed in blender.
In bowl, add flour and knead.
Roll out into circles.
Bake in hot skillet 1 minute on each side.

title: coconut cake
directions: Mix eggs, sugar and oil well at high speed.
Add buttermilk and mix well.
Add flour and keep mixing for about 3 minutes.
Add vanilla and salt; stir in.
Grease and flour three 8-inch cake pans.
Pour into pans and bake at 350° until done.
Cool in pans before frosting.

title: tomato, okra and corn
directions: Saute onion in fat until brown.
Add okra and saute for 5 minutes.
Add other ingredients until vegetables are tender. Serves 6.

title: pay day bars
directions: Boil for 1 minute, sugar and syrup.
Add peanut butter, then add peanuts and cereal.
Press into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: turkey supreme
directions: Mix all together adding enough liquid (broth) to make moist. Bake at 375° for 1 hour uncovered.

title: zucchini sausage soup
directions: Brown the first 4 ingredients together.
Add next 4 ingredients.
Season with next 3 ingredients.
Cook 1/2 hour.
Add green pepper and cook an additional 1/2 hour.

title: four cheese pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Spray a 12-inch pizza pan with Pam. Unroll pizza dough; press into prepared pan.
Cover with Provolone, Mozzarella and Fontina cheeses.
Cover cheeses with tomatoes.
Sprinkle seasonings over tomatoes.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake until cheeses are bubbly and golden brown, about 10 to 15 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: recipe for a happy home
directions: Toss all ingredients with patience, understanding and forgiveness.
Serve with cheerfulness to God, community and country.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 10-inch tube pan or Bundt pan.
In bowl, sift flour, sugar, soda, salt and cinnamon. Add remaining ingredients.
Stir until well mixed.
Hand mix only. Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes or until cake tester comes clean. Cake will be very moist.
Ice with favorite frosting.

title: monterey green beans
directions: In saucepan, saute onions in butter until tender. Add beans, mushrooms, lemon pepper and salt. Cover and cook over medium heat for 5 minutes or until beans are tender. Sprinkle with cheese; cover and let stand 1 minute.

title: family christmas salad
directions: Mix in large clear bowl.
Layer cranberry, saltine crackers, Cool Whip, etc.
Cool overnight in refrigerator, then serve.

title: layered ice cream dessert
directions: Crumble cookies and mix with melted margarine. Spread on bottom of 9 x 12 dish.
(Tupperware works well.) Spread soft ice cream on top, then drizzle with chocolate syrup. Spread Cool Whip over top and sprinkle nuts over top. Freeze.

title: aunt emma's cocoa fudge
directions: Combine cocoa with sugar and salt.
Add milk and mix well. Bring to a boil, stirring frequently.
Cook to 234° or until mixture forms a soft ball in cold water.
Remove from heat and add butter.
Cool to lukewarm (110°) and add vanilla and beat until mixture thickens.
Pour quickly into buttered pan and cut in squares.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken; save broth.
Tear meat into small pieces; layer evenly in a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
In small bowl, mix cream of chicken soup with 1 cup of broth; pour evenly over chicken. Place whole bag of stuffing evenly on top.
Moisten stuffing thoroughly with broth.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: sour cream sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar and butter together.
Beat eggs and add to mixture.
Add in vanilla and sour cream.
Mix dry ingredients together and mix in with the other mixture.
Stir well. Drop by spoonful on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Cream together oleo and sugar. add eggs and beat well. Fold in sour cream and vanilla. Add flour, salt, and baking powder. Mix together brown sugar, nuts, cinnamon and oleo. Put a little of nut mixture in bottom of pan. Pour half of batter on top. Put rest of nut mixture on top and then finish with rest of batter. Bake in a small bundt pan for 45-50 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: broccoli with soy sauce
directions: Make a sauce by cooking the chicken stock with the cornstarch which has been rubbed smooth in about 2 tablespoons cold water. Cook, stirring, until thickened.
Add the soy sauce.
Wash the broccoli thoroughly and cut off the flowery tops.
Slice the stems at a slant in pieces about 1/2-inch thick.
Measure the oil into a heavy saucepan or skillet.
Add the stems; cook for about 5 minutes, stirring.
Add the tops, cut in small pieces; cook 5 minutes more.
Pour the thickened sauce over the broccoli.
Cover and cook for 2 minutes.
Remove the cover and cook 4 minutes.
Try this with roast pork.

title: ham and fresh vegetable medley(305 calories per serving)
directions: With sharp knife, cut boneless ham into 1/4-inch strips, about 3-inches long.
Cut each tomato into 8 wedges.
Cut green and red peppers into 1/2-inch wide strips.
Cut onion, yellow squash and zucchini into 1/4-inch wide slices.

title: vanilla souffle
directions: Melt butter in pan.
Add flour, milk and sugar.
Boil to thicken.
Beat egg yolks in bowl and add vanilla.
Add to first mixture. Stir until thoroughly mixed.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour into greased baking dish.
Set in pan of hot water and bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until souffle is firm to the touch.
Serve immediately.

title: chicken cordon blue
directions: Beat chicken breasts until flat.
Cube ham and cheese and place on each chicken breast.
Roll up; dip in lemon juice, then dip in croutons.
Place in baking dish.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: grandma reynolds' shortcake dough
directions: Make a nest in the flour and add ingredients.
Knead in bowl until stiff.
Roll out thin.
Poke holes
with
a
fork. Bake in 350° oven until light brown.
Put lots of butter on it as soon as it comes out of the oven.
Crumble	into pieces and cover with strawberries.
We like to eat just the dough.

title: spinach dip in a red cabbage
directions: Cook spinach; drain well and stir in the next 7 ingredients. Chill.

title: dutch raisin apple pie
directions: In
large saucepan, boil raisins and water until liquid is almost
absorbed
to
minutes).
Meanwhile, in small bowl, mix
sugar,
flour, cinnamon and salt.
Stir into raisin mixture with
lemon
juice and apples.
Turn into pastry lined pan.
Cover with
top	crust;	cut
slits in top for steam to escape.	If desired, brush egg and sprinkle with sugar.
Bake in preheated 425° oven for 10 minutes; reduce heat to 350° and bake for	45
to 55 minutes, or until golden brown.	Makes one 9-inch pie.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Press sugar cookie dough onto bottom of large ungreased pizza pan. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until light brown. Cool. Drain pineapple, reserving 1/4 cup juice. Beat cream cheese, sugar, vanilla, and pineapple juice until smooth. Spread over cooled crust. Arrange chopped fruit.

title: apple crunch
directions: Place sliced apples in baking dish.
Combine other ingredients. Spread over apples.
Bake in 350° oven 30 minutes.
Serve with ice cream.

title: macaroni and ham casserole
directions: Prepare macaroni and cheese as directed on package.
Add peas, ham and milk, mixing well.
Spoon into a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle on shredded Cheddar cheese.
Mix crushed crackers with melted butter and sprinkle over all.
Bake in 400° oven for 15 minutes, until heated through and cheese is melted.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Layer all as listed.
Set overnight in refrigerator.

title: green beans au gratin
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Fry bacon until crisp; remove from skillet.
Drain fat, reserving 1 tablespoon.
Cook and stir onions in reserved fat.
Add cubed cheese and milk.
Stir until cheese is melted.
Crumble bacon.
Add bacon, beans and pepper to skillet; mix lightly.
Spoon into 1 1/2-quart casserole; top with cracker crumbs.
Bake 15 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: casserole cookies
directions: Beat eggs well and add sugar slowly, beating until fluffy.
Add all other ingredients.
Put in 5 quart casserole.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Take out and stir.
Cool.
Form into balls.
Roll in granulated sugar.
Cool only until you can handle.
Butter hands to form balls.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream the cream cheese, butter and sugar until creamy, then add eggs, one at a time, along with the flour.
Beat thoroughly and bake for 1 hour in 350° oven.

title: coffee-eggnog pie
directions: Soften gelatin in cold coffee.
Dissolve in hot coffee.
Add sugar, stir to dissolve.
Pour in slowly well-beaten egg yolks. Chill until consistency of unbeaten egg whites.
Add flavoring. Whip cream.
Fold in.
Beat egg whites with salt; fold in.
Spoon into pie shell.
Chill until set.
Garnish with shaved chocolate.

title: easy-do butter cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl; blend.
Mix at a low speed of mixer until a dough forms.
Cover; chill several hours. Shape as desired.
Place on greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: hoe cakes
directions: 1. Mix well - all batter; ingredients.

title: papas chorreadas
directions: Saute onion in butter and oil.
When transparent, add tomatoes, salt and pepper.
Let season a few minutes, then add the flour dissolved in the milk, stirring well until it begins to thicken. Pour this sauce over the cooked potatoes, cutting a cross on top of them.
Pour the cheese, the cilantro and the green onions on top while still hot.
MMMMM!!

title: spring daffodil pie
directions: Soften gelatin in cold water. Combine milk, sugar, salt and egg yolks in a small sauce pan. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture begins to boil. Add gelatin; stir until dissolved. Stir in orange juice, lemon juice, orange rind, and lemon rind. Chill mixture until slightly thickened. Fold whipped cream into gelatin mixture. Turn into pie shell. Chill several hours or until set. If you wish garnish with puffs of whipped cream and pastel candy mints. Makes 6-8 servings.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Preheat oven 350°.
Dice and saute the onions in olive oil or butter.
Mix onions, garlic salt, chili powder, cheese, rotel, cream of chicken soup, and drained canned chicken in a bowl and salt and pepper to taste. (Add more cheese and chili powder also, if desired.)
Grease a casserole dish and line the bottom and sides with torn up corn tortillas.
Pour the chicken mixture into dish. Top with more torn up corn tortillas and more cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 min.

title: plum-wine chicken
directions: Place seasoned breasts in greased baking dish or skillet.
Mix all other ingredients.
Pour over chicken.
Cover and bake for 30 minutes at 420° or until chicken is tender.

title: tea cakes
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cream butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Add flour, 1 cup at a time.
Mix well, roll out and cut.
Bake on top rack in oven for 6 to 7 minutes or until light brown.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream
together margarine, sugar and vanilla.
Add nuts and potato chips, then add flour.
Form into small balls using about 1 tablespoon of dough.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and press flat with a glass dipped in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: salmon spread
directions: Clean the salmon of all bones and skin.
If you wish you may mash the bones in with the salmon for the calcium they provide. Place the cottage cheese in a strainer and place under running water to clean off all milk.
Pat the cottage cheese curds dry with a paper towel.
Combine all ingredients in a bowl and mash until smooth and creamy.
Chill in the serving bowl.
Serve with crackers, toast point, or slices of cucumber and other fresh vegetables.

title: chicken corn soup
directions: Cook all vegetables until tender.
Add 1 can cream style corn. Add fine egg noodles to soup.
Cook 5 minutes or until tender.

title: chili
directions: In a large pot, brown the meat and drain well. I always rinse and drain meat well. Put in your package of chili mix and add tomato juice and chili beans. I always diced the onion while I'm browning the meat and cook the meat and onion together. Let the chili cook on low or simmer for 1 hour. You may add spaghetti if you want.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients for 2 minutes.
Add the oats and vanilla; stir until thick.
Drop on wax paper.
Refrigerate until cool.

title: baked rice
directions: Hard-boil 2 eggs; dice and set aside.
Make 2 to 4 cups of rice, depending on size of casserole dish.
Add together the rice, eggs, tomato sauce and water.
Bake, covered, at 325° for 1/2 hour.
Add strips of cheese to top and cook until melted (5 minutes).

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix everything together lightly.
Refrigerate several hours.

title: wok beef
directions: Heat wok.
Add oil until hot enough to fry.
Stir-fry ingredients until almost tender.
Serve with rice and eat with chop sticks.

title: sicilian pizza dough
directions: Grease a 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch jelly roll pan.
In a large bowl, mix flour mixture and yeast in foil packet from hot roll mix; stir in salad oil and 1 1/4 cups hot tap water to form soft dough.
On lightly floured surface, with floured hands, knead dough until smooth and elastic, about 5 minutes.
Pat dough onto bottom of jelly roll pan.
Cover and let rise at room temperature 15 minutes.

title: cheesy green beans
directions: Reserve 1/4 cup bacon drippings.
Cook green beans and drain. Add mushrooms and onion to bacon drippings; cook for 10 minutes. Drain.
Add bacon, green beans, mushrooms and onion mixture and black pepper; mix lightly.
Spoon into a 2-quart casserole. Microwave Cheez Whiz and pour over green bean mixture.

title: onion egg rolls
directions: This makes 10 rolls.
Mix egg yolk and a little milk.
Just before baking, brush with egg yolk-milk mixture.
Put dried onion on and brush again with liquid.
If you don't brush over the onion, they will burn.
Bake at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes.

title: mint tea
directions: Squeeze lemons and reserve rinds.
If juice does not measure 1 cup, add frozen lemon juice.
Put water in a large boiler and bring to boil.
Turn heat off.
Add lemon rinds, tea bags and mint.
Let the tea steep for 1 to 2 hours.

title: yummy ham rolls
directions: Cut onion in small pieces and mix with ham.
Place on bottom half of rolls.
Spread cheese across the top of this.
Mix other remaining ingredients and pour over top.
Place top half of roll in place.
Bake for 20 minutes at 375°.

title: ham and potato bake
directions: Butter 2 (6-cup) casseroles.
Saute onion and pepper until soft, not brown.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Add milk; simmer until thickened, stirring, approximately 2 minutes.
Stir in 1 cup cheese and mustard.
Cook, stirring until cheese is melted.
Remove from heat.
Fold in potatoes, carrots and ham. Pour into casserole.
Cover each with foil.
Bake in preheated hot oven (425°) for 30 minutes.
Remove foil; sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake, uncovered, 15 minutes more.
Serves 8 to 12, or use 1 and freeze the other for later.

title: salmon cakes
directions: Remove back bone from salmon and drain.
Add all ingredients. Mold into cakes.
Saute 3 minutes each side in 1/4 cup shortening.

title: pickled peach halves
directions: Drain and stuff peach halves with whole cloves.
Save syrup. Bring peach syrup, vinegar, cinnamon and sugar to a boil.
Simmer 3 to 4 minutes.
Cool.
Pour over peach halves.
Refrigerate.

title: caesar salad
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients in small bowl.
Pour over romaine lettuce and add croutons.
Top with Parmesan cheese.

title: garden pea salad
directions: Cook peas until tender, about 15 minutes.
Chop eggs and mix. Add grated onion and mayonnaise.
Serve chilled.

title: chicken sauté with broccoli
directions: Place garlic cloves in small saucepan and cover with water. Bring to a boil. Cook for 5 minutes. Drain; slip off skins. Set aside. Place broccoli in a steamer and steam until tender, 4 to 5 minutes. Remove from steamer. Set aside. In a shallow dish, combine flour, salt and pepper. Dredge chicken in mixture, shaking off excess. In a large skillet, heat oil over medium-high heat. Add the chicken and cook, turning until browned on all sides, 4 to 5 minutes. Transfer chicken to a plate and set aside.

title: incredible french fries
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In large bowl, whisk together egg white, chili powder, salt and garlic and onion powder until frothy.
Add potatoes; toss to coat well.
Using slotted spoon, transfer potatoes to nonstick baking sheet.
Spread to make single layer. Bake until golden brown and crisp, about 20 minutes, stirring once during baking.
Makes 4 servings.

title: jello cottage cheese salad
directions: Mix cottage
cheese
and
dry jello until jello is completely dissolved.
Stir
in
pineapple, mixing well.
Fold in whip cream. Chill before serving.
Can lower fat by using all low-fat and lite ingredients.

title: "ricardo's changua" (for two)
directions: To begin:
Set tortillas aside (for room temperature).
Rinse out beans.
Put in crock-pot.
Fill with water to top of beans. Cover and cook all day on low.
Drain.
Put in a large pot.
Mash. Add 1/3 cup of grated cheese, 2 tablespoons of olive oil and water to moisten.
Cook on low until steaming hot.
Crumble meat; add cracked pepper and pinch of salt and cook on low.
Stir occasionally until well done.
After removing skin and seed from avocados, put both in bowl and mash.
Add salt, pepper and 1/2 teaspoon garlic powder.
Add cottage cheese and sour cream and mix with fork until all blended; refrigerate.

title: picnic chicken
directions: Melt butter in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix flour and spices.
Mix buttermilk and egg.
Coat chicken with milk and egg mixture, then coat with flour mixture.
Put in pan and coat each side in the melted butter.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: raisin glaze
directions: In saucepan, mix brown sugar and cornstarch.
Stir in water. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until clear and thickened.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Remove from heat. Spoon glaze over ham surface during last 30 minutes of baking.

title: homemade shake and bake
directions: Dip chicken in several beaten eggs.
Put on cookie sheet; turn every 1/2 hour.
Bake 2 hours.

title: spoon bread
directions: Cook corn meal and 2 cups milk until consistency of mush. Remove from heat; add salt, baking powder, oil and 1 cup milk. Add egg yolks and fold in egg whites.
Bake in greased 2-quart baking dish in slow oven at 325° for 1 hour.
Spoon into warm dish; top with butter.
Serves 8.

title: dressing or stuffing
directions: Season to taste with salt, pepper, sage and celery.
Mix well.
Add the melted butter.
Moisten with water or milk or with broth from cooked fowl.
Oysters may be added, if desired.
Put in pan and bake in moderate oven at 350° approximately 30 minutes.

title: chris' salmon-cheese spread
directions: Mix the salmon and cream cheese in mixer or processor.
Can also add a little lemon juice and a dash of dill, if desired. Cover and refrigerate.
Can roll in nuts and cover form with Saran Wrap.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Serve with crackers or vegetables.

title: liver and onion patties
directions: Put liver, onion and crackers through food chopper; chop fine. Add eggs, milk and seasonings.
In a skillet, heat some lard or bacon drippings and into this, drop meat mixture by tablespoons. Fry each side until brown and crisp.
Makes 4 large servings.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Combine butter and grated Parmesan cheese.
Spread on both sides of six 1 inch slices French bread.
Sprinkle bread on both sides with poppy seeds.
Place on baking sheet and toast at 350 degrees about 12 minutes, turning once.

title: grandma's buttermilk waffles
directions: Mix together flour, baking powder, salt and baking soda. Add eggs, buttermilk and butter; mix well. Pour batter into a preheated waffle iron and cook until crisp and golden.

title: 1-2-3 biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In large bowl with fork or spoon, mix flour, baking powder and salt until well blended.
Add milk and salad oil all at once.
Stir until dough forms a ball.
With hand, knead dough in bowl ten times or until smooth.
Roll dough between sheets of waxed paper into 6-inch square, about 1-inch thick.
Cut into 9 biscuits.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes until golden.
Makes 9 biscuits.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Put bottom crust in pan.
Put can of crushed pineapple in crust.
Mix sugar and flour.
Sprinkle over pineapple.
Dot butter over this.
Put on top of crust.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: little bits
directions: Butter 1 1/2-inch muffin tins and coat generously with graham cracker crumbs; set aside.
Cream the egg yolks, sugar and cream cheese until fluffy.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into cream mixture.
Spoon cream cheese mixture into muffin tins.
Fill about 3/4 full.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool 10 to 15 minutes (centers will fall, foamy and indented).
Carefully remove from muffin tins.
Spoon 1 teaspoon Sour Cream Filling into center indention.
Store in refrigerator.
Makes 48 servings.

title: best-ever chocolate cake
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease and flour 13 x 9-inch pan.
In medium bowl, combine flour, soda and sugar; set aside.
In large saucepan, combine butter, water and cocoa; bring to a boil. Remove from heat.
Add flour mixture, buttermilk, eggs and vanilla.
Use electric mixer, beat 2 minutes at medium speed. Bake at 375° for 20 to 30 minutes, until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool.
Frost with Buttercream Frosting. Makes 12 servings.

title: turnip casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter or margarine.
Combine all ingredients. Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until hot. Serves 6.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in a jar and shake.
This will keep refrigerated for up to 1 week.
Tear lettuce and combine with cheese, strawberries and nuts.
Pour dressing on just before serving.
This is a great summertime salad.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Blend all ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 450° for 10 minutes (preheated).
Reduce temperature to 350° and bake 45 minutes.

title: angel cake
directions: Beat egg whites, water, salt and vanilla until foamy.
Add cream of tartar and beat until it stands in peaks.
Mix in rest of ingredients.
Bake in ungreased tube pan.

title: no peek chicken
directions: Put 1 cup rice on bottom of pan (uncooked).
Cover with cream soup and place dried onion soup on top of cream soup.
Lay chicken on top of onion soup.
Cook with lid 1 1/2 hours at 425°.
No need to check until finished.

title: old-fashioned beef stew
directions: Cook the beef until tender.
Add potatoes and cook until they are tender.
Add other ingredients.
Boil 15 minutes more.

title: barbecue beans
directions: Brown meat and onion in a small amount of fat in a skillet. Add beans, barbecue sauce and ketchup.
Also add brown sugar and chili powder, if used.
Turn into a 2-quart casserole; sprinkle with chopped bell pepper and bake in a 350° oven until it bubbles all over.
Sometimes I use a heavy iron skillet to brown the onions and meat.
Add the chopped pepper also to this and combine everything; then simmer on top of stove, until heated through. Saves time and easier on cooling system in summer.

title: oven barbecue chicken
directions: In hot oil, cook chicken a few pieces at a time until browned on all sides.
Remove chicken to roasting pan.
Keep 1 tablespoon of fat in the skillet.
Over medium-high heat, cook onion until tender.
Stir in tomato sauce, brown sugar, mustard, Worcestershire sauce, vinegar, salt and 1/4 cup water.
Heat this to boiling.
Pour sauce over chicken in roasting pan.
Bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes or until chicken is fork-tender.
Can occasionally brush chicken with sauce.

title: baking powder biscuits
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Blend milk and shortening together, then add to dry ingredients.
Stir, then knead 20 seconds.
Break into 12 portions.
Fold dough portions in on themselves.
Dip tops in milk and place on a greased baking sheet or iron skillet.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 450°.
Sticks to the ol' gut!
Serves 12.

title: shrimp party sandwiches
directions: Mash cream cheese and add lemon juice, onion, celery and salt. Stir in shrimp which has been broken into tiny pieces or mashed well.
Let stand at least 1 hour before spreading between buttered rounds.
Yield: 25 servings.

title: somemores
directions: Split the graham cracker in half.
Put the chocolate on one piece of the cracker.
Toast the marshmallow.
Put it on the chocolate, then put the other cracker on it.
Makes 1 serving.

title: creamed chicken
directions: Melt oleo over low heat in 1 1/2-quart saucepan.
Blend in flour; add milk and bring to a boil.
I use a whisk to make sure it doesn't get lumpy.
Boil 2 minutes until thick, stirring constantly.
Add remaining ingredients and heat, uncovered, for 15 minutes over low heat.

title: skillet pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Melt butter in a 9 inch cast iron skillet.
Spread brown sugar evenly over bottom of skillet.
Drain pineapple, reserving 1/4 cup juice; set juice aside.
Arrange pineapple slices in a single layer over brown sugar mixture and place a cherry in center of each pineapple ring.
Set skillet aside.

title: easy cherry chocolate cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour rectangular pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inches.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add baking powder, flavoring and Crisco.
Add flour alternately with the milk, starting and ending with flour.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 300° to 325°.
Heat too high causes cake to crack on top.
Baking too long causes cake to be dry.

title: chocolate cream pie
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch, cocoa and salt together in saucepan. Gradually stir in milk.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickens and boils.
Boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Gradually stir at least half of hot mixture into egg yolks. Then blend into hot mixture in saucepan.
Boil 1 minute more, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Blend in butter and vanilla.
Pour immediately into 9-inch cooked pie shell.
Serve with sweetened whipped cream.
Whip the whipping cream and powdered sugar together until fluffy and stiff.
Dot over pie when it is cool.

title: best chocolate cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Cream butter flavored Crisco, brown sugar, milk and vanilla in large bowl.
Blend until creamy.
Blend in egg. Combine flour, salt and baking soda.
Add to creamed mixture gradually.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop rounded teaspoonfuls 3 inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool on baking sheet 2 minutes.
Remove to cooling rack.

title: microwave potato cheese casserole
directions: Cut potatoes into small cubes.
Add chopped onion and potato cubes to casserole dish.
Cut butter over top.
Microwave 45 minutes.
Add slices of cheese to the top and microwave 15 more minutes.

title: pudding cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl until well moistened.
Drop dough by teaspoonfuls about 2 inches apart onto greased baking sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until edges are light brown in 350° oven.
Makes about 4 dozen cookies.

title: sour cream-chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; beat in eggs.
Add vanilla and sour cream.
Sift together dry ingredients; blend in.
Add chocolate chips and nuts.
(Also good when Heath chips are used instead of chocolate chips.)
Shape as desired.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Yields 5 to 6 dozen.

title: bea cauley's brunswick stew
directions: Boil chicken, pork, garlic and celery together in a large stew pot filled with water.
Cover and simmer 1 hour or until meat is very done and tender.
Cool and skim off fat.
Reserve broth to add later.
Pull meat off bones and shred by hand or in food processor.
Place shredded meat in large stew pot on top of stove and add tomatoes, corn, lemon juice, catsup, Worcestershire sauce and chili powder.
Add as much of broth as desired for preferred thickness.
Stir often while simmering on stove top.
Crumble 1 piece of dry toast to thicken.
Can be made ahead and frozen. Fresh or frozen vegetables may be used in lieu of canned.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook spaghetti; drain, then stir butter into hot spaghetti. Stir in Parmesan cheese and egg to form mixture.
Press into buttered pan to form crust.
Put cottage cheese into crust.

title: best ever cake
directions: Prepare cake mix per box instructions and bake in a 9 x 12-inch cake pan.
While cake is still warm, poke 12 to 15 holes with the end of a wooden spoon.
Pour sweetened condensed milk into holes. Spread caramel topping over cake.
Thaw Cool Whip and spread over cooled cake.
Sprinkle crushed candy bars over Cool Whip.
Chill overnight.

title: dieter's delight
directions: Prepare pudding using skim milk.
Pour thin layer into pie crust.
Slice 1/2 of banana into thin slices and spread over pudding.
Add another layer of pudding over bananas.
Sprinkle crushed graham cracker crumbs over this.
Slice other 1/2 of banana over crumbs.
Add rest of pudding over all.
Chill thoroughly; top with Cool Whip.
At serving time, put tablespoon (or two) of crushed strawberries over each serving.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown meat with onion, mushrooms and green peppers; drain. Stir in tomato juice, basil and oregano.
Put 1/2 mixture in a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish sprayed with nonstick cooking spray. Cover with layer of cheese.
Add remaining mixture and cover with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in a saucepan and heat until it comes to a boil.
(Great when added to chipped ham!)

title: crunchy salad
directions: Combine the uncooked noodles (crunched up), cole slaw mix and almonds and sunflower seeds.
Make dressing of the oil, vinegar, sugar and contents of seasoning packets from noodles.

title: swiss asparagus casserole
directions: Melt two tablespoons of the butter in a large skillet.
Saute asparagus for two to three minutes or until barely tender.
Remove and reserve.

title: quiche jo-anne
directions: Combine cheeses, spices, onion, green pepper, mushrooms, eggs and milk in large bowl.
Mix thoroughly.
Divide evenly into 2 pastry lined pie plates.
Crumble bacon over top.
Bake at 350° about 50 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving (can freeze before baking).

title: candace's snickerdoodles
directions: Mix shortening, sugar and eggs, then add flour, soda and salt. Mix well.
Roll mixture into balls, then roll balls into cinnamon and sugar mixture.
Place cookies on cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: tomato, cheese 'n bacon broil
directions: Partially cook bacon.
Place a slice of cheese on each slice of toast.
Spread with soup; cover edges completely.
Top with bacon.
Broil about 4-inches from heat until cheese melts.
Makes 8 open-faced sandwiches.

title: lime pickles
directions: Soak the first 3 ingredients for 24 hours.
Drain and rinse well, then cover with clear water for 1 hour.
Drain.
Mix remaining ingredients together.
Pour mixture over chunked cucumbers and bring to a boil.
Add a little green food coloring for looks.
Reduce heat and simmer for 30 minutes.
Remove from heat and pack in sterilized jars and seal.

title: vegetable rice skillet
directions: Heat broth and margarine to boiling in 10 inch skillet. Stir in vegetables, rice and contents of seasoning packet. Heat to boiling; reduce heat to low. Cover and simmer 5 to 6 minutes or until vegetables and rice are tender. Sprinkle with cheese.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Mix condensed milk, lemonade, Cool Whip and lemon juice.
Pour into pie crust.
Refrigerate 1 hour or longer.
Suitable for freezing.

title: rum balls
directions: Mix all together.
Shape into balls.
Roll in extra powdered sugar.

title: brussels sprouts and bacon
directions: Steam sprouts 5 minutes or until tender.
In small skillet, fry bacon crisp, drain and crumble.
Add onion to drippings in skillet, saute 5 minutes until tender, add remaining ingredients to skillet, cook, stirring until mixture boils.
Stir in bacon. Pour over Brussels sprouts.

title: date pecan balls
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add vanilla and mix.
Add flour and mix.
Blend in pecans and dates.
Roll teaspoonfuls of dough into balls.
Refrigerate balls for 1 to 2 hours.
Bake at 350°
on a greased cookie sheet for approximately 20 minutes.
Remove from oven and roll balls into powdered sugar.
Sprinkle them again with powdered sugar after cookies have cooled.
Store in an airtight container.
They keep well.

title: sour cream raisin bars
directions: Cook all ingredients together stirring constantly until mixture thickens. Add cooled raisins and 1 teaspoon vanilla. Pour mixture on baked crust and top with remaining 1/2. Bake 30 minutes at 350°. Cut when cool. Refrigerate or freeze.

title: peach and cream cheese pie
directions: Beat 1st seven ingredients. Pour into 10 inch pie pan which has been sprayed with Pam. Put peaches on top of batter. Beat 8 oz. cream cheese,1/2 cup sugar, and 3 Tbsp.
of peach juice. Spoon over peaches, leaving a 1 inch space around the edge. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes. Does not look to good but is it delicious!

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine eggs and milk and beat until well blended.
Add cracker crumbs; set aside until all liquid is absorbed.
Add remaining ingredients (except cheese) to crumb mixture.
Spoon into greased 1-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Top with cheese.

title: kevin's nasty bars
directions: Mix sugar, milk and butter; boil for 1 minute. Add rest of ingredients and mix. Pour into 9 x 13 pan. Let cool. Sprinkle with powdered sugar and cut into bars.

title: bayberry's meat loaf
directions: Place meat in bowl.
Add eggs (slightly beaten) and bread crumbs; mix well.
Place green pepper, carrots and celery in food processor or blender until very fine.
Mix vegetables with meat. Add parsley and pepper.
Add water as you go, using only as much as needed and no more.
Mixture should be moist, but firm enough to shape with your hands.
Mold meat into loaf so it is firm and holds together.
Grease bottom of flat baking pan and place loaf in pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Yields 6 servings.

title: roast turkey in foil
directions: Rub turkey cavity with salt and pepper; rub skin with butter. Fill turkey loosely with stuffing.
Place turkey on large sheet of foil in roasting pan.
Combine wine, brandy, thyme and basil; mix well.
Pour over turkey; seal foil tightly.
Bake at 400° for 3 hours and 30 minutes; fold foil back.
Bake for 30 minutes longer or until turkey is browned.

title: ham stuffed rolls
directions: Combine ham with eggs, onions, peppers, mustard, relish and mayonnaise.
Cut off tops of rolls; scoop out.
Fill with the ham mixture.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Place in 7 1/2 x 12-inch baking dish.
Place in microwave for 2 or 3 minutes.

title: low-fat 1 serving lasagna casserole
directions: Cut strip of cooked lasagna into 3 pieces.
Alternately add the following ingredients in layers in a 10 ounce casserole: 1 tablespoon spaghetti sauce, one piece lasagna, bits of cheese and cottage cheese and green pepper.
Continue this procedure, ending with the sauce.
Save a few pieces of cheese to top the mixture. Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: mom's carrot casserole(serves 8)
directions: Place carrots in a saucepan and cover with water; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer until tender, about 10 minutes.
Drain; place in a greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
In a small saucepan, melt 1/4 cup butter and cheese, stirring often. Stir in dill.
Pour over the carrots.
Toss with saltines and remaining butter; sprinkle over carrots.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly browned and bubbly.

title: peanut butter trail mix bar
directions: Combine cereal, raisins, sunflower nuts (and chocolate chips) in a large bowl.
Combine honey and sugar in a medium pan; heat over medium heat 2 to 5 minutes or until mixture comes to a boil. Boil 1 minute.
Add peanut butter and vanilla; stir until peanut butter is melted.
Pour over cereal mixture; mix well.
Press mixture into greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan.
When cool, cut into 1 1/2-inch squares.
Makes 5 dozen bars.

title: hominy casserole
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients together and place in a greased casserole.	Sprinkle
crushed flakes over the top and dot with butter.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour. Serve with barbecued meat or ham.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Pour mixture over chicken and rice.
Top with 1/2 cup shredded cheese, then crushed potato chips and 1/2 cup sliced almonds. Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: old-fashioned chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and cocoa together until well blended. Separate eggs.
Beat egg yolks, adding milk and vanilla.
Add to dry ingredients and mix well.
Add butter and cook in microwave until thick.
Pour into baked crust.
Top with meringue and bake at 350°.

title: apple dessert sauce(club member: christy hosey)
directions: Place all ingredients in medium saucepan. Cook and stir over medium heat for 5 minutes or until sauce is somewhat thickened. Serve hot over apple cake. Can be reheated to serve later.

title: skillet barbecue chicken
directions: Put cola in skillet and add catsup.
Stir together; then add the drained chicken pieces into skillet.
Cover and cook 30 minutes on one side; then turn chicken and cook 30 minutes on other side.
Be sure to check the heat and reduce as it cooks.

title: baked cod with mayo and dill
directions: Spread the mayonnaise evenly on top of the cod fillet. Sprinkle dill on the top of the cod fillet.

Place cod in a baking dish, uncovered, and bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes. When the mayonnaise turns golden brown, it's finished. Serve with a vegetable or tossed salad. Bust out the wine and "let's eat!"

title: sweet potato on pineapple ring
directions: Mix and place on pineapple ring using ice cream scoop.
Top with marshmallow and cherries.
Bake 10 minutes at 400°.

title: rice pilaf
directions: Heat skillet with oil; add rice and chopped onion.
Saute until rice starts to brown.
Add tomato juice; stir while it is sizzling.
Add bouillon cube, salt, pepper and mushrooms.
Cover with about 3 cups water.
Cover; reduce heat and simmer on low for about 30 minutes.
May have to add water.
Taste test for doneness.

title: hamburger hash
directions: Combine all the ingredients except the noodles and put in a 3-quart casserole dish. Cover and bake for 1 1/2 hours at 350°. Sprinkle noodles over top of the casserole and bake an additional 10 to 15 minutes.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: irish potato puffs
directions: Beat yolks of eggs until creamy.
Add potatoes.
Sift flour, salt and pepper; add to yolks.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold egg yolk-flour mixture into egg whites.
Drop by teaspoon into hot fat.
Fry until golden brown.
Drain and serve hot.

title: yeast rolls
directions: In a large bowl, whisk yeast and sugar together in warm water until dissolved.
Set aside for 15 minutes.
This mixture will rise and become foamy.
After 15 minutes, whisk salt and melted butter into yeast mixture.
Add flour, 1 cup at a time, beating well after each addition.
The last few cups will be hard to incorporate; stir in as much as you can, then transfer to floured surface and knead in the rest of the flour.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix all.
Bake in 13 x 9-inch pan at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: herbed tomatoes
directions: Combine parsley, chives, oil, vinegar, pepper and thyme; mix well.
Place tomatoes in a shallow container; pour dressing over tomatoes.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Drain tomatoes, reserving dressing.
Arrange tomatoes on lettuce-lined serving plates; spoon dressing over tomatoes.
Yields 12 servings.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar on high speed until fluffy.
With spoon, gradually add flour, vanilla, chips and nuts.
Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten with fork.
Bake at 350° for 16 to 20 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar while still hot.
Cool.

title: christmas salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add ice cubes.
When it starts to gel, remove ice cubes.
Add remaining ingredients, except whipping cream.
Before serving, whip the whipping cream and fold into jello mix.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and cook until thick.
Add next three ingredients.
Pour into uncooked pie shell.
Cook at 350° until pie is very thick and knife comes out clean.
Cover with meringue and let brown.

title: celery casserole
directions: Cook celery 5 minutes; drain.
Put in buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Next pour on chestnuts.
Thin soup a little and pour over chestnuts.
Top with crackers, then melted oleo, then almonds.

title: hamburger noodle bake
directions: Blend in cream cheese, milk, lemon juice, garlic salt and Worcestershire sauce.
Blend into the cooked noodles.
Pour in a greased 11 x 7-inch baking pan or dish.
Cook onion and green pepper in butter until tender.
Add beef and stir until brown. Stir in tomato sauce and catsup; cook over medium heat until thickened (about 8 minutes).
Spread over noodles.
Bake in a 375° oven about 10 minutes, until bubbly hot.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: bean dip
directions: Pour chili in a saucepan and partially mash the beans.
Add remaining ingredients; simmer 5 minutes.
Keep hot and serve with taco chips, crackers, chips or large Fritos.

title: scottish scones
directions: In a bowl, stir together flour, baking powder and salt.
Cut in shortening until mixture has texture of bread crumbs.
Make a well in center and add enough milk to make a very soft dough. (The softer the dough is the higher the scones will rise.)
Turn dough onto well floured board and pat into 3/4-inch thick round. Using a 1 1/2-inch cutter, cut and place scones onto ungreased and floured baking sheet.
Bake at 475° for 12 to 15 minutes, until lightly browned.
Makes 15 to 18.

title: mississippi caviar
directions: Rinse black-eyed peas and drain.
Layer peas with onion slices in	bowl,
sprinkling
each
layer with cracked pepper. Process vinegar,
salt, garlic and vegetable oil in blender at high speed for
minutes, or until well blended.
Pour over peas and onions.
Chill
for
hours
or
weeks.
Flavor improves after several days.
Yields 50 servings.

title: heinz catsup
directions: Boil tomatoes and onions until soft.
Put in sacks.
Drain the bags after 2 hours.
After draining, run through sieve.
Pour juice (from draining) away.
Put it through the blender.
Add sugar, salt, cloves, cinnamon, dry mustard and vinegar to the pulp.
Boil 10 minutes.
Put clear jell in to thicken.

title: stir fruit cake
directions: Mix butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Mix dry ingredients. Roll fruit in flour mixture.
This is a stiff batter.
Cook in same pan you mixed it in.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Stir every 15 minutes.
Pack in pan while hot.
You may pour small amount of sherry over top if desired.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Sift 1 1/2 cups flour with 3 tablespoons of sugar.
By hand, combine margarine, salt and vinegar and add to flour.
Press dough into bottom and sides (to a height of 1-inch) of greased spring-form pan.
Fill pan with blueberries (reserving 1 cup), 1/2 cup sugar, 2 tablespoons flour and cinnamon.
Bake for 50 minutes at 400°.
When cool, add reserved cup of berries and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: snack crackers
directions: Mix dry ingredients with oil.
Pour over crackers.
Put in large container and shake several times a day.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Bake at 350° for 1 hour in a greased tube pan.

title: hot cocoa mix
directions: Mix. Store in covered, sealed container.
Add 2 spoonfuls per cup of hot water.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Spread crescent roll dough on a cookie sheet, covering bottom and halfway up sides to form a rim.
Bake 11 minutes at the temperature indicated on the package.
Cool.

title: chocolate peanut clusters
directions: Melt chips, peanut butter and paraffin.
Add nuts, stirring well.
Dip out and drop by teaspoonfuls on wax paper.

title: lemon bars
directions: Blend until smooth; pour over dough.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Cut in squares.

title: angel salad
directions: Mix well and refrigerate to set.

title: cranberry delight
directions: Grind cranberries into bowl.
Add remaining ingredients and chill.

title: mookie scallops
directions: Clean and drain scallops.
Add lemon juice; allow to drain. Larger scallops should be cut into bite size pieces.
Cut the red pepper into short, thin slices; place on the side.
Cut the green pepper into short, thin slices; place on the side.
Cut the ginger root into short, very thin slices (about 1 tablespoon).
Avoid using the outer skin of the root.
Place these on the side.
Break 2 tablespoons of walnuts into medium size chunks; place on the side.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix sour cream and cream cheese.
Spread mixture on bottom of square dish.
Layer on top of mixture the lettuce, onion, pepper, tomatoes and cheese.
Pour salsa lightly over top.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: broccoli puff casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed. Drain.
Beat everything together except broccoli and cheese with hand beater until smooth.
Then stir in broccoli and cheese.
Pour into casserole and bake at 350° until knife inserted between center and edge comes out clean, about one hour.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: dirty rice
directions: Mix above ingredients together.
Place in casserole, cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cherry dessert
directions: Mix together and pat into 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 325° for 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned.
Let cool.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in casserole dish. Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 225°.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cook zucchini, carrots and onion until tender; do not add water.
Drain.
Combine soup, cheese and 4 tablespoons of margarine.
Add vegetables.
Stir together gently.
Pour into baking dish.
Cover with cracker crumbs and 2 tablespoons of margarine.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Place chicken in casserole dish.
Put mixed vegetables on top of the chicken.
Mix soups and chicken stock together and pour over top of the chicken and vegetables.
Put stuffing mix on top. Bake at 325° for approximately 30 minutes.

title: yummy stewed potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes cut into 1/2 inch slices place in bowl and wash.
Put potatoes in 3 quart pan of boiling water.
Cook until potatoes are tender.
Turn heat down on medium and add a one and a half stick of butter.
Stir frequently until thick remove from heat and serve.

title: hot mexican dip
directions: In saucepan, combine soup and cheese.
Stir in sour cream, onion and Tabasco.
Sprinkle with chili powder.
Serve hot with corn chips.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Layer rhubarb, sugar and jello in bottom of a 9 X 13 pan.
Top with marshmallows.
Prepare cake mix and pour on top.
Bake 50-55 minutes at 350°.
Cool 5 minutes.
Turn upside down.
Serve with whipped cream.
Note:
Can use huckleberries with lemon jello or peaches with orange jello.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients; slowly add hot milk.
Add beaten egg yolks and cook until thick.
Then add butter and vanilla.
Pour into baked pie crust and top with whipped cream.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix sugar and peanut butter into crumbs.
Divide into three parts.
Put 1/3 of the crumbs on bottom of pie shell.
Pour the instant pudding that has been mixed per directions.
Let set 5 minutes.
Pour another part of the crumbs over the pudding, sprinkling evenly.
Cover with a small carton of Cool Whip. Sprinkle remainder of the crumbs over the Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Stir
in
a
bowl the macaroni (cold), green peas, ham, cucumber
and mayonnaise.
Pour in a serving dish and decorate with slices of hard egg and chopped parsley.

title: tuna salad
directions: Prepare macaroni and cheese dinner as directed on box.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix lightly and chill.
Add additional salad dressing before serving, if desired.

title: porcupine meatballs
directions: Blend beef, rice, green pepper, onion, salt and pepper thoroughly.
Shape meat into balls, about the size of a walnut. Arrange balls in a large heavy skillet.
Pour tomato soup, water and melted fat over meatballs.
Cook on high heat until steaming. Turn to low and cook 45 minutes.

title: luscious lemon bars
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add flour; mix until formed in a soft dough.
Put mixture evenly into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish which has been sprayed with Pam.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: salsa
directions: Cook peppers and onion for 1/2 hour in nonstick frypan.
In a large kettle, add everything and simmer until thickened (several hours).
Salsa can be frozen or processed.

title: crab cakes
directions: Pick through crabmeat and remove shells.
Try not to break up lumps of meat. Add all ingredients to crabmeat and mix well.
Form into 6 or 8 cakes.
Either fry or broil until browned on both sides.

title: white salad
directions: Grease bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: 3 pepper-olive frittata
directions: Whisk together eggs, water, basil, dill weed and salt; set aside.
Heat oil in 10-inch saute pan.
Saute peppers, garlic and onion 3 minutes.
Sprinkle olives over mixture.
Whisk egg mixture and pour over the vegetables; cook over medium-high heat 5 minutes.
Sprinkle cheese over eggs and place in skillet in oven 3 to 4 minutes or until top is set and cheese is melted.
Cut into 6 wedges and serve at once.

title: matt's chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream together butter, margarine and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla and cream more.
Add flour, soda and salt and mix well. Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Chill.
Drop dough by spoonful onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: moo-goo-mi-pan
directions: Cut chicken into cubes; sprinkle with salt and cornstarch. Stir-fry in hot oil in skillet for two minutes.
Add celery and cook another two minutes.
Stir in remaining ingredients and cook for 8 minutes.
Serve with rice if desired.

title: calico bean bake
directions: Cut bacon in 1 inch pieces and brown in skillet with onions. Remove from pan with slotted spoon, then brown ground beef; drain. Add bacon and onions to ground beef.
Mix all ingredients together in a large casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: matt's potato soup
directions: Put potatoes and onion into 3-quart saucepan and barely cover with cold water.
Add salt.
Cover tightly and heat to boiling. Reduce heat and simmer for 10 minutes or until potatoes are perfectly tender.
Mash potatoes in their liquid.
Add butter and enough milk to give desired thickness.
Reheat to scalding, then remove from heat.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar.
Cut broccoli off stems and mix with remaining ingredients.
Let set in refrigerator overnight.

title: peanut clusters
directions: Combine peanut butter and chocolate morsels in a heavy saucepan.
Cook over low heat, stirring frequently, until morsels melt.
Remove from heat.
Add peanuts, stirring to coat.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto wax paper.
Cool completely and store covered.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix dry stuffing mix with margarine.
Combine all other ingredients.
Add 1/2 of stuffing mixture.
Fill lightly greased shallow baking dish with squash mixture.
Cover with other half of stuffing mix.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: old time beef stew
directions: Heat oil in Dutch oven.
Add beef stew; cook over medium heat about 20 minutes, turning often to brown.
Stir in next 14 ingredients.
Cover and simmer 1 1/2 hours, stirring occasionally. Add carrots, onions and potatoes.
Cover and cook 45 minutes longer.

title: blondies
directions: Mix together like pie dough; this will make the First Layer.

title: soda cracker pie
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add sugar slowly.
Mix all ingredients together and put in a well-greased pie tin.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
