This is much better if you let this stand in refrigerator for 24 hours before serving.
Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.
Serves 6.

title: pink cloud salad
directions: Bring pineapple to slow boil.
Pour in dry jello.
Mix thoroughly and let cool.
Mix remaining ingredients and add to pineapple.
Refrigerate.

title: creamy chicken and bows
directions: Melt margarine.
Stir in chicken and pepper.
Cook 3 minutes. Add peas, cheese, garlic powder and soup.
Blend in milk.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Toss in with hot bows and serve.

title: shortcut frozen salad
directions: Prepare pudding mix according to directions.
Blend in whipped topping, mayonnaise, and lemon juice.
Fold in remaining ingredients.
Turn into 5X5X3 baking pan and freeze till firm. Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: black walnut cake
directions: Combine cake mix with eggs, Crisco, water, milk, 1/2 of nuts and flavorings.
Bake in two layers for 35 minutes at 350°.

title: double chocolate brownies
directions: Cream together first 3 ingredients until fluffy; add syrup and continue creaming.
Beat in eggs and chocolate.
Sift together dry ingredients; stir into batter.
Fold in chocolate pieces and walnuts.
Spread in greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan; bake in moderate oven (350°) about 25 minutes.
Cut into squares or bars.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Combine apples, marshmallows, celery and walnuts.
Toss lightly.
Chill.
Add additional salad dressing and garnish with sliced apples before serving, if desired.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: buttermilk fried chicken
directions: Combine buttermilk, salt and pepper.
Stir well.
Skin chicken, if desired.
Place chicken in a shallow container and pour mixture over top.
Cover and let stand 20 minutes, turning once.
Remove chicken.
Dredge chicken in flour, coating well. Cook in hot oil (350°) until browned, turning to brown both sides. Reduce heat to 275°, cover and cook 25 minutes.
Uncover and cook 5 minutes longer.
Drain on paper towel.

title: broccoli-corn casserole
directions: Mix ingredients, except butter and crackers, together and pour into a buttered casserole dish.
Mix crackers and melted butter together and sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: double the milk hot chocolate
directions: Use blender to combine nonfat dry milk and milk, adding 1 tablespoon chocolate syrup.
Heat in a pan on stove for about 2 minutes, stirring occasionally; do not boil.
Stir in vanilla.

title: green bean supreme
directions: In small saucepan melt butter and saute onion until tender. Add flour, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Carefully blend in sour cream and heat thoroughly.
Do not boil.
Stir in beans and turn into casserole dish.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: venison chili
directions: Fry in saucepan over medium gas flame (325° to 350° dial setting on controlled burner) 1/2 pound suet.
Remove cracklings. Add and cook until soft, stirring frequently, onions and garlic. Mix in paper bag the flour, chili powder and cumin.
Add venison cubes, a few at a time, and shake until each cube is coated with seasoned flour.
Add meat to onion and cook until brown.
Add tomato sauce, tomatoes and salt.
Reduce flame to simmer (200° to 225° dial setting on controlled burner) and continue cooking 4 to 5 hours, stirring occasionally and adding water as needed.
Makes approximately 10 cups.

title: fat-free brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Sift dry ingredients together in medium bowl.
Beat egg whites slightly, then mix the other wet ingredients in larger bowl.
Add dry ingredients to wet and stir just until blended.

title: chocolate classic brownies
directions: Grease	an
8-inch
square baking pan.	Preheat oven to 350°. In	2 quart saucepan, melt chocolate and margarine over low
heat; remove from heat.	Gradually beat in sugar;
blend in
eggs;
add flour, vanilla and baking powder.
Fold in nuts and spread	batter in
greased pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until brownies begin to pull away from sides of pan.
Cool and cut into squares.
Makes about 16.

title: ginger pudding
directions: Beat eggs (whole) until light.
Add brown sugar, ginger and melted butter.
Stir in molasses, sour milk, soda and flour.
Mix well.
Beat until all ingredients are thoroughly mixed.
Grease and flour a pan and bake in moderately hot oven.
Serve with any sauce you prefer.
Sauce For Gingerbread is a good one.

title: tabasco pickles(delicious)
directions: Drain vinegar from pickles and discard. Wash pickles in cold water and cut into 1 to 2-inch chunks. Layer into original jar the pickle chunks, sugar and Tabasco. Screw cap on jar tightly. Store jar in refrigerator. First position is upside-down. Turn twice a day for 5 days, alternating position (upside-down, right side up, etc.).

title: hula dip
directions: Combine in saucepan.
Stir over low heat until melted.
Or microwave 2 to 4 minutes.
Makes 1 cup.

title: cheesy hominy
directions: Melt margarine in frying pan on medium heat.
Drain hominy. Grate cheese.
Put hominy in melted margarine and heat until hot. Sprinkle cheese over hominy.
Cook until cheese is melted.

title: marinade and kabobs
directions: Put all ingredients except meat and vegetables in blender; mix well.
Pour over meat.
Let marinate for 4 hours or longer.
Put on skewers with assorted vegetables.
Brush with marinade.
Grill over medium-hot coals, turning and basting often for 15 to 20 minutes, or until meat and vegetables are done.
Serve with rice.

title: brisket rub
directions: Mix all ingredients together and rub on all sides of brisket. Place in plastic bag and refrigerate overnight, turning meat once. Wrap brisket in foil and place in deep pan.
Bake 3 hours (or until tender) at 300°.
Brown on grill.

title: cheese twist
directions: Sprinkle salt over dough after it has been rolled out.
Cut into any desired shape or strip and twist.
Bake for 15 minutes in a 425° oven.

title: chocolate sop
directions: Mix cocoa, sugar and flour.
Add vanilla and water.
Boil until thickens.
Serve with hot biscuits.

title: pasta and broccoli
directions: Cook pasta according to directions on package.
Blanch broccoli.
Toss broccoli and pasta with remaining ingredients. Can be served warm or cold.

title: ginger cake
directions: Sift flour once and measure; add baking soda, salt and spices. Sift together 3 times.
Pour boiling water over butter; stir until blended.
Add molasses, then beaten eggs and flour mixture.
Stir until blended.
Pour into greased and floured pan.
Bake 40 or 50 minutes until done.

title: granny's favorite recipe
directions: Toss all, except Granny, straight up in the air. Drop into squeaking rocking chair.
Fold in grandmother's outstretched arms. Tuck Teddy and blanket around small child's arms.
Open fairy tale book to very first page.
Begin by saying, "Now when I was your age".

Mix stories of bunnies, bears, piggies and soup. Repeat bedtime stories until child's eyelids droop. When the cookie has crumbled and child starts to yawn, place child, Teddy and blanket in warm bed until dawn.
Yields 2 happy persons!

title: funny cake
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients and put in bottom of rectangular pan.

title: top of the stove rice pudding
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch and salt in a 2-quart saucepan.
Combine the milk and egg.
Gradually stir into sugar mixture.
Add rice. Cook over medium heat until thick and bubbly.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Remove from heat and stir in butter or margarine and vanilla.
Pour into a bowl or custard cups.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Grease and flour 4 small loaf pans.
Mix all ingredients well and place in loaf pans.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: purple passion
directions: Drain pineapple mix with cottage cheese.
Then put in dry jello and mix again.
Add Cool Whip.
Refrigerate until ready to serve. Will serve 18 to 20 people.

title: apple pudding(this apple pudding is filled with goodies.)
directions: In a large bowl, mix all ingredients together, then pour into a lightly greased baking dish.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
When done, pour Special Sauce on top.

title: cottage potatoes
directions: Combine first eight ingredients in a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Mix melted margarine.
Add milk.
Pour over potato mixture.
Sprinkle with cornflakes.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Butter Bundt pan and line bottom with rolls.
Sprinkle nuts over rolls.
Combine pudding and brown sugar and sprinkle over rolls.
Slice butter and lay over pudding mixture.
Let raise overnight or 6 to 8 hours.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: bacon wraps
directions: Rub both sides of bacon with brown sugar.
Wrap slice of bacon around cracker tightly (crosswise).
Place on a baking rack with a drip pan underneath to catch the grease.
Bake at 250° for 2 hours.

title: easy kraut
directions: Scald and peel tomatoes.
Squeeze the seeds and juice from tomatoes by hand.
Put pulp in large cooker.
Add 2 cups sugar to 1 cup tomatoes, with very little juice.
Add lemon which has been sliced thin and cut into half moons.
Cook as for jelly.
Pour into jars, add 1/2 stick of cinnamon.
Seal with lid.
Water bath 5 minutes.

title: frozen cucumber pickles
directions: Sprinkle salt over sliced cucumbers and let set for 2 hours. Drain off water.
Combine sugar and vinegar, pour over cucumbers and let stand for 10 minutes.
Stir and put in freezer containers. Thaw at room temperature, and then store in refrigerator.

title: pecan pie
directions: In large bowl, stir eggs, corn syrup, sugar, butter and vanilla until well blended.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into pastry shell.
Top mixture with more pecans (not chopped), if desired.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes or until knife inserted in middle comes out clean.

title: north carolina barbecue sauce
directions: Combine ingredients and allow flavors to meld several hours or overnight.
Use to season slow-cooked, chopped or shredded Boston butt pork meat.
Makes 2 cups.

title: light fettuccine alfredo
directions: In a medium saucepan over high heat, whisk milk, garlic, flour and cream cheese.
Bring to boil, whisking constantly.
Reduce heat and simmer for 2 minutes or until thickened.
Add Parmesan; whisk until blended.
Remove from heat; stir in Molly McButter.
Pour sauce over hot fettuccine.
Sprinkle with parsley and pepper, if desired.
Serves 4. Per serving:
5 grams fat and 310 calories.

title: good barbecued ribs
directions: Prepare ribs and bake in shallow dish for 30 minutes at 350°. Meanwhile, saute onion in fat for 5 minutes, add remaining ingredients.
Mix well and simmer 5 minutes more.
Pour over ribs and bake for 1 hour.

title: potato pancakes
directions: In mixing bowl, gently combine potatoes and eggs.
Combine dry ingredients and onion.
Stir in potato mixture.
Drop by tablespoon into preheated greased skillet.
Brown lightly on both sides.

title: bombay salad
directions: Combine coconut, chicken, rice, and relish.
toss well till blended.

title: peanut butter krispies snack
directions: Mix corn syrup and sugar in bowl; in microwave heat until hot. Then add peanut butter.
Then add Rice Krispies.
Put in cookie pan.
Heat chips in microwave.
Spread on the top, then cut into bars.

title: hard rock candy
directions: In a medium size saucepan, mix together sugar, water and Karo syrup.
Put over medium heat, stirring constantly until it comes to a full rolling boil.
Put in candy thermometer.
Let boil; do not stir until it reaches hard crack.
Remove from heat.
Add flavored oil; add drops of food coloring to make color.
Stir and pour into a buttered cookie sheet.
Let set until hard, then crack with a hammer.
Can coat with powdered sugar, if desired.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown meat slowly; spoon off excess fat.
Add next 6 ingredients to meat.
Simmer, uncovered, for 45 minutes to 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Cook noodles in boiling salt water until tender; drain and rinse in cold water.
Combine cottage cheese with next 5 ingredients.
Place half of noodles in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Spread half of cottage cheese mixture over noodles. Add half of Mozzarella cheese and half of meat mixture.
Repeat layers.
Bake in moderate oven (375°) for 30 minutes.
Let stand 10 to 15 minutes.

title: golden string beans
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In casserole, empty and pour off bean juice.
Mix cream of mushroom soup to beans and place onion rings on top of bean mixture.
Brown in oven for about 30 minutes. Delicious.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Arrange alternate layers of thin sliced potatoes and onions. Sprinkle each layer with flour, salt and pepper and dot with butter.
Pour milk over the casserole and bake at 400° for 1 hour. Last 15 minutes sprinkle with grated cheese.

title: quiche lorraine(6 to 8 servings)
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Line pie plate with pastry and bake 5 minutes.
Cook bacon until crisp; remove from skillet.
Cook onion in remaining fat until transparent.
Crumble bacon and sprinkle bacon, onion and cheese over pastry.
Combine eggs, cream, nutmeg, salt and pepper.
Pour over ingredients in shell.
Bake 15 minutes at 450°, then reduce heat to 350° and bake until a knife inserted an inch from edge of pastry comes out clean.
Leave in oven 10 minutes longer.
Serve immediately as hors d'oeuvres or main course.

title: golden catfish fillets
directions: In a shallow bowl, beat eggs until foamy.
In another shallow bowl, combine flour, cornmeal, seasonings and a little salt.
Dip fillets in eggs, then coat with cornmeal mixture.
Heat 1/4-inch oil in a large skillet; fry fish over medium-high heat for about 4 minutes on each side or until fish flakes easily with a fork.

title: cracker pie
directions: Pour filling in unbaked crust and dot with butter.
Cover with top crust.
Bake at 425°
for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Drain pineapple; keep 3 tablespoons juice.
Combine juice, sugar and flour.
Add cheese and pineapple chunks.
Mix well. Combine margarine and cracker crumbs.
Spoon over pineapple mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cheese and pepper spread
directions: Put everything through grinder and add dressing.

title: old fashioned cheese cake
directions: Mix together.
Press into an 8 or 9-inch spring-form pan; reserve 3/4 cup of mixture to sprinkle on top.

title: apple cake
directions: In one bowl, combine apples, cinnamon and 5 tablespoons sugar. In another bowl, combine the remaining ingredients.
In a greased and floured tube pan, pour in some of the batter, then sprinkle on some of the seasoned apples.
Cover with more batter and repeat the process until all batter and apples are gone.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Add milk to sugar, flour and cocoa and stir constantly.
When thickened, add egg yolks, margarine and vanilla.

title: old-fashioned stack cake
directions: Crumble shortening in flour.
Add other dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Add eggs and mix again.
Add milk and blend well.
Divide in 5 portions and roll out as for pastry; cut to fit a 9-inch cake pan or heavy skillet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
(It will be thin like a cookie.)

title: tex-mex dip
directions: Spread bean dip on large platter.
Mix sour cream, mayonnaise and taco seasoning.
Spread over bean dip.
Mash avocados and lemon juice together and spread over sour cream.
Sprinkle other ingredients in layers over top of this.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Add soup and water.
Add vinegar, salt and pepper to taste.
Cut cabbage coarse; add and bring to a boil. Simmer 25 minutes.
Place in casserole; cover with bread crumbs. Bake for 15 minutes at 400°.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix ingredients.
Bake at 350° until done.
Bake in loaf pans.

title: cornflake candy
directions: Place sugar and Karo into pot.
Bring to boil.
Boil about 1 minute.
Add peanut butter and stir.
Add cornflakes.
Mix thoroughly until flakes are coated.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.

title: blueberry tea cake
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease and flour 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.

title: pecan pie
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350°.
Bake 30 minutes.

title: chicken rolls
directions: Heat milk,
soup and 1/2 cup grated cheese until cheese melts and is hot.
Pour
in
casserole
dish.
Roll
chicken, which is seasoned with
black pepper and sauteed onions, and 1 tablespoon grated
cheese
in	each
triangle.
Place	rolled crescents on top of sauce and bake, uncovered, until rolls are brown in a 350° oven (about 30 minutes).

title: quick corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients; turn into a buttered 1 1/2 quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: low-fat cabbage and...
directions: Rinse and cut cabbage into 2-inch strips.
Immerse in water while preparing other veggies.
Scrape carrots.
Cut into 2-inch diagonals.
Remove seeds from pepper.
Cut into 1/4-inch strips. If potatoes are used, peel and slice into 1/2-inch thick slices.

title: special chicken
directions: Dip pieces of chicken in oil and place in casserole dish. Cover with slices of bacon.
Sprinkle with oregano and thyme. Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour at 350°.
Place under broiler to brown.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: sprits
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add beaten egg yolks, almond extract and flour.
Use sprit form or these can also be rolled out and cut with fancy cookie cutter. Bake in a hot oven until light brown.

title: 7-up bread
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in a greased bread loaf pan.
Cool before slicing.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Break cauliflower into small florets.
Add chopped onions and celery.
Mix with dressing.
Right before serving, add lettuce and bacon bits.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling salted water.
When soft, rub through strainer or use 2 1/2 cups mashed potatoes.
Scald milk with onion.
Remove onion and add milk slowly to potatoes, using a whisk.
Melt half the butter; add dry ingredients.
Stir until well mixed, then stir into hot soup.
Boil 1 minute.
Strain.
Add remaining butter and sprinkle with parsley.

title: creamy pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
In a large bowl, combine pumpkin, milk, eggs and spices.
Mix well. Turn into shell and bake 15 minutes. Reduce heat to 350° and continue baking for 40 minutes. Cool. Garnish with Cool Whip and chopped nuts.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Mix 1/4 cup soup and remaining ingredients.
Make patties and brown. Blend the rest of the soup with 1/3 cup water.
Pour over patties and simmer 20 minutes.

title: rosemary's cream cheese shrimp dip
directions: Soften cheese; add seasoned salt, onion and Worcestershire. Mix well.
Spread on dish to 1/4-inch thick.
Cover generously with cocktail sauce, then cover with the shrimp.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Refrigerate for at least 3 hours.
Can be made the day before and kept in refrigerator overnight.
Serve with Ritz type crackers or with Triscuits.

title: egg custard(makes its own crust.)
directions: Grease a large pie plate.
Mix all ingredients and pour into pie plate.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: strawberry angel food cake
directions: Dissolve one small package strawberry jello in 1 cup hot water.
Add strawberries.
Let thicken in refrigerator.
Add 1 cup Cool Whip and mix well.
Cut angel food cake into three layers. Put filling between each layer.
Top with more Cool Whip as an icing.
Refrigerate before serving.

title: cranberry sauce muffins
directions: Combine cereal and milk, let stand for 5 minutes.
Add eggs and oil, mix well.
Combine dry ingredients, stir into cereal mixture just until moistened.
Fold in cranberry sauce.
Coat muffin cups with nonstick cooking spray, fill 2/3 full with mixture.
Bake at 400 degrees for 15 to 20 minutes or until a toothpick comes out clean.
Cool 5 minutes, remove from pan to a wire rack.
Yield:
1 dozen muffins.

title: geraldine's pie
directions: Begin by layering each ingredient in a 9 x 13-inch pan, beginning with pie filling.
End by slicing 2 sticks of butter and layering over entire dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together and let sit overnight. Next day, mix the marshmallows, walnuts and whipping cream or Cool Whip.
Fold this with the other ingredients.
Refrigerate.

title: giant polka dot cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. In a large mixing bowl, thoroughly cream shortening, sugars and vanilla. Beat in eggs, then water. In separate bowl, sift together flour, soda and salt. Add to the creamed mixture, blending well. Stir in rolled oats. On a greased cookie sheet, for each cookie, spread 1/4 cup of cookie dough into a 3 1/2-inch circle. Make circles 2 1/2-inches apart. Press M&M's in the top. Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes. Switch the cookie sheets after 4 minutes for more even baking. Makes 20 giant cookies.

title: veggie hamburger rice skillet
directions: In a large skillet, brown ground beef and onion.
Drain.

Add water, rice, frozen vegetables, garlic powder and seasoned salt. Mix well. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat to low and simmer uncovered for 6 to 8 minutes or until rice and vegetables are tender. Stir in soup and tomato sauce.
Cook 5 minutes or until thoroughly heated and of desired consistency. Sprinkle with cheese. Cover and let stand 2 to 3 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: chicken diable
directions: Wash chicken pieces; pat dry.
Remove skin if you wish.
Melt margarine in shallow baking dish.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Roll chicken in this mixture to coat both sides, then arrange meaty side up in a single layer in the same pan.
Bake in moderate oven at 375° for 1 hour or until the chicken is tender and richly glazed.

title: jean's rice rotel
directions: Combine all ingredients in sauce pan and cook on low until heated.

title: green chili enchiladas
directions: Break chips and place in bottom of baking dish.
Brown hamburger and onion.
Combine soups, chilies and evaporated milk in pan.
Heat.
Layer hamburger, soup mixture and cheese in a dish.
Bake at 400° until cheese melts.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Melt stick of butter in pan.
Sprinkle with stuffing mix. Cover with chicken and 1 can of mushroom soup.
Add another layer of stuffing mix. Cover with cream of chicken soup and 1 can of water.
Cover with more stuffing mix on top.
Bake at 400° until done and brown on top.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Combine all ingredients, drop by tablespoons onto hot, well-greased griddle or skillet.
Brown on both sides.
Makes 12.

title: spicy oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients, add oats, raisins and nuts last.
Bake on greased cookie sheet in 375 F oven 8-10 minutes.
Makes approx. 40 cookies.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sift first 6 ingredients.
Combine last 5 ingredients.
Mix well.
Use four 1 pound coffee cans.
Spray inside of can liberally with cooking or baking spray (Pam).
Fill cans 1/2 full only.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: amanda maultsby's merry christmas cookies
directions: Mix in usual manner.
Drop spoonfuls on cookie sheet.
Bake at 300° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: texas caviar
directions: Mix all ingredients. Refrigerate for at least an hour before serving. But it's still good even if you can't wait that long! Serve with tortilla chips. Makes a BIG bowl of dip!

title: pam's chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Cream the margarine, oil, sugar, eggs, vanilla and milk together.
Add the remaining ingredients except the zucchini, nuts, and chocolate chips; mix together. Add zucchini; mix well. Place in a greased 9 x 13 pan.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips and chopped nuts, if desired.
Bake at 325° for 40-45 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: cheesy artichoke heart appetizers
directions: Unroll dough into rectangles and press into bottom and sides of 10 x 15-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Combine remaining ingredients; mix well.
Spread over crust and bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes and cut.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: lipton onion meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine ingredients.
Form into loaf in meat loaf pan.
Bake for 45 to 50 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: chef salad dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Allow to season for desired taste.

title: jezebel sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients except cream cheese in blender. Pour over cream cheese bar. Serve with crackers.

title: cheese ball
directions: Core large kosher dill pickles.
Stuff with deviled ham mixed with enough mayonnaise for good consistency.
Chill and slice.

title: potato dumplings
directions: Boil potatoes until soft, peel and rice or mash.
Add fried bread, spices, eggs and flour.
Mix well, you may need to use your hands.
Form into balls about the size of a golf ball and roll in flour.
Place on floured surface, not touching, for several hours. Drop into boiling watter, a few at a time, and cook no more than 10 minutes.
Dumplings will float when done.
Serve with sauerbraten and gingersnap gravy.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix together and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: mini cheese cakes
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Line cup cake pan with liners.
Place vanilla wafer in each.
Mix cream cheese, vanilla and sugar on medium speed until well blended.
Add eggs, mix well.
Pour over wafers, filling 3/4 full.
Bake 30 minutes.
Remove from pan. Cool on wire rack, chill thoroughly.
Add topping.
Enjoy!

title: zucchini pie
directions: Toss all ingredients together. Put into unbaked pastry shell. Do not add water as it will make its own juice.
Top with second crust.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: hungarian goulash
directions: Brown meat in 1 tablespoon shortening.
Add onion soup mix, tomato paste and water.
Cover and simmer 1 1/2 hours.
Serve over noodles.
(Use 6 ounces tomato paste when doubling recipe.)

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti according to package directions; drain.
Put in refrigerator to chill.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well. Chill for 2 to 4 hours before serving.
Amount of ingredients varies according to number of people to feed.

title: pineapple bars
directions: Add melted butter into sugar and beat.
Add eggs into mixture and beat until foamy.
Add flour, salt and soda.
Mix well.
Add drained pineapple and nuts.
Pour into a greased 10 1/2 x 15 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
When done, sprinkle with 10xxx sugar.

title: pace chicken chimichangas(chi-mee-chon-gahs)
directions: Combine chicken, picante sauce, onion, cumin, oregano and salt in saucepan; simmer 5 minutes or until most of the liquid has evaporated.
Brush 1 side of tortillas with butter.
Spoon 1/3 cup chicken mixture onto center of unbuttered sides, top with 2 tablespoons cheese.
Fold 2 sides over filling; fold sides down. Place seam sides down.
Bake in preheated oven at 475° about 13 minutes until brown.
Top with guacamole and picante sauce to serve.
Makes 4 servings.

title: taffy apple salad
directions: Combine flour, sugar, pineapple juice, egg and vinegar in small pan; cook until thickened and cool.
Fold Cool Whip, apples, pineapple and 2/3 cup nuts into the cooled mixture.
Spread remaining nuts on top.

title: cajun skillet beans
directions: In a heavy saucepan or skillet, saut the onions and garlic in the oil over medium heat.

Add the chopped celery and peppers to the pan and continue to saut for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally. Add the thyme, basil, oregano, black pepper, cayenne and salt. Cover and cook for 5 minutes or until the onions are golden, stirring once or twice.
Add the tomatoes, honey and mustard and simmer for 5 more minutes.
Add the beans.
Cover.
Stir occasionally until thoroughly heated.
Serve topped with chopped scallions and/or grated Cheddar cheese.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into large baked pie shell.
Cook for 1 hour at 300°.

title: ginger cakes
directions: Cream shortening; add sugar, then molasses.
Finally, add the boiling water.
Add sifted dry ingredients, stirring all well after each addition.
Add the well beaten eggs.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
(This recipe is over 150 years old.
Given by Mrs. Reaford McCarter.)

title: scallops parisienne
directions: If using sea scallops, cut into 2 or 3 pieces.
In saucepan, combine scallops with wine, water, herbs and peppercorns.
Simmer 2 to 3 minutes.
Strain, reserving liquid (about 1 1/2 cups).

title: louisiana pepper steak
directions: In an 8-inch round microproof casserole dish, combine steak and broth.
Use Cook cycle and cook 13 minutes in microwave or until steak is tender.
Add green peppers; cover with plastic wrap.
Use Cook cycle and cook 5 minutes.
Combine water, cornstarch and steak sauce; stir to dissolve cornstarch.
Add to steak and peppers.
Arrange tomato wedges on top.
Use Cook cycle and cook 2 minutes.

title: tropical chicken, "fruity rice" and stewed french-style green beans
directions: Wash and skin chicken pieces.
Pat dry.
Season well.
Let stand for several hours in refrigerator.

title: tomato bread
directions: Cut bread in two lengthwise.
Brush with melted butter. Sprinkle with garlic salt and onion salt.
Add tomatoes and sprinkle with salt, pepper, oregano and cover with grated cheese. Sprinkle with parsley and add pepperoni slices if you wish. Bake at 350° until cheese is melted.
Delicious!

title: impossible pie
directions: Blend all ingredients in a blender.
Pour into a large (10-inch) greased pie pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350° or until set. Serves 8.

title: baked chicken sandwich
directions: Cut crusts off bread.
Butter slices and line large cookie sheet.
Spoon mixture over 1 bread layer.
Cover with another bread layer.
Top with mixture of sour cream and creamed chicken soup.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake 30 minutes in 350° oven which was preheated.
Serves 6.

title: hobos
directions: Tear off 2 large squares of aluminum foil.
Bake 2 patties of the ground beef and place each in the middle of the foil squares. Place cheese on hamburger patties, then potatoes, carrots and onions.

title: beef crepes mexicana
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet and pour off drippings.
Combine flour, chili powder, salt, cumin, oregano and garlic powder. Sprinkle over meat.
Add tomato sauce, chilies and water.
Stir to combine.
Place 2 tablespoons of meat mixture across center of each crepe.
Overlap opposite sides on top to enclose filling.
Place in 11 X 7 baking dish.
When all crepes are filled, place remaining meat mixture on top.
Cover tightly with foil and bake at 375 degrees for 15 minutes Remove cover, sprinkle with cheese.
Bake ten minutes more or until cheese is melted.
Makes 4 servings of 2 crepes each.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Spread out rolls on cookie sheet or pizza pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool crust.
Mix together cream cheese, mayonnaise and dry dressing mix.
Spread over baked rolls.
Spread vegetables over top and chill.

title: oven crusted chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In medium bowl, combine margarine, flour and spices.
Dip chicken in margarine mixture.
Roll in cereal to coat.
Place on rack in shallow baking pan.
Bake 55 to 60 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 6 servings.

title: blueberry pie(makes 2 pies)
directions: Press pecan pieces into bottom of thawed pie shells and bake at 350°
until
brown;
cool.
Mix
cream cheese, egg and sugar until smooth;
spread on bottom of pie shells.
Top with berry filling.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: mashed spinach potatoes
directions: Baking Temperature: 400°.
Baking Time: 20 minutes.

title: zucchini fritters
directions: In a bowl, stir together the biscuit mix, Parmesan cheese and pepper.
Stir in beaten eggs.
Fold in zucchini.
In a large, heavy skillet, melt butter.
Use 2 tablespoons of mixture for each fritter.
Cook until brown on each side.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients except butter.
Melt butter in skillet. Pour mixture into skillet.
Bake at 350° approximately 45 minutes. Let cool 10 minutes before cutting.

title: ripe olive dip
directions: Mix; chill 1 hour and serve with chips.

title: bourbon slushy
directions: Add tea bags to boiling water; let steep 5 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Freeze.

title: lemon pecan biscotti
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Spray cookie sheets with no-stick cooking spray.
In small mixer bowl combine sugar, lemon juice, eggs, egg white, lemon peel and vanilla.
Beat at medium speed, scraping bowl often, until well mixed (1 to 2 minutes).
By hand, stir in all remaining ingredients except 1 tablespoon flour.
Sprinkle large piece of aluminum foil with 1 tablespoon flour.
With floured hands, shape dough into 2 (12 x 2-inch) logs on prepared foil. Place logs on prepared cookie sheets 4 inches apart.
Flatten logs slightly.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes or until lightly browned and firm to the touch.
Cool on wire cooling rack about 10 minutes.

title: macaroni and cheese bake
directions: Cook macaroni as directed.
Stir in sliced frankfurters and onion.
Pour into buttered 10 x 6-inch baking dish.
Arrange tomato slices on top with cornflake crumbs.
Bake in a 350° oven for 25 minutes.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into pie crust.
Refrigerate and let chill 1 hour.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Sift dry ingredients together. Cut in shortening.
Add yeast to buttermilk and stir into other ingredients.
Knead lightly.
This keeps well for 3 or 4 days in refrigerator.
Roll out, cut and bake in hot oven at 450° until desired brownness.

title: starlight mint surprise cookies
directions: Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Cream butter (half shortening may be used) and add gradually sugar and
brown sugar, creaming well.
Blend in eggs, water and vanilla.
Beat well.
Add dry ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Place layer of potatoes, onions and green beans.
Pour can of mushroom soup over mixture.
Cook at 375° for 45 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Place hamburger on top.
Place into oven.
Cook 15 to 20 minutes until done.

title: oven baked beans
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cook bacon to crisp; drain.
Crumble bacon.

In a 1-quart casserole, combine bacon, pork and beans, onion, ketchup, molasses, brown sugar, mustard and Worcestershire. Bake, uncovered, 30 to 35 minutes or until thickened and bubbly, stirring every 15 minutes.
Makes about 4 servings.

title: macaroni, pizza style
directions: Brown crumbled beef and onion together and drain.
Place in two 9-inch pie plates.
Top with macaroni, then 1 1/2 cans tomato sauce, water and seasonings.
Toss.
Top with cheese and toppings. Pour on rest of sauce.
Bake for 15 minutes at 375°.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in ice cream freezer.

title: orange carrot cake
directions: Beat oil and sugars well, then add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Whisk flour with baking powder, baking soda, salt and cinnamon, then blend gradually into sugar mixture. Stir in carrots, zest and extract. Divide batter among three 9-inch greased and floured cake pans. Bake in center of preheated 325° oven for 35 minutes or until wooden pick comes out clean. Cool 10 minutes, then turn out of pans and cool on racks. Frost with Creamy Orange Frosting.

title: walking taco dip
directions: Layer the preceding ingredients in the order in which they are given.
Top with chopped onions, tomatoes and black olives.

title: cherry delight
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.
Quick, easy and delicious.

title: cole slaw
directions: Shred the first 3 ingredients and mix with the celery seed, sugar, salt and pepper. Add this to raw vegetables.
Mix together the remaining ingredients.
Mix all this together.
It tastes better when made a few hours or more before eating.

title: swiss roll cake
directions: Mix cake as directed.
Grease and flour 9 x 15 x 1/2-inch cookie sheet.
Pour 1/3 of cake mix in pan and bake 10 to 12 minutes, until done.
Cool in pan (10 minutes), then turn onto a dish towel, covered with powdered sugar.
Cover cake bottom with powdered sugar, then roll up with towel until completely cool.
Do the same with remaining 2 cakes.
Unroll and spread Cool Whip on cake and re-roll.
Place on serving pan and frost with icing. Freeze until ready to eat.
Slice and serve.

title: white fudge
directions: Combine sugar, sour cream, milk, butter, corn syrup and salt in a heavy 2-quart saucepan.
Stir over moderate heat until sugar is dissolved and mixture reaches a boil.
Boil over medium heat 9 to 10 minutes to 238° or soft ball stage.
Remove from heat and allow to stand until lukewarm, 110°, about 1 hour.
Add vanilla and beat until mixture just begins to lose its gloss and hold its shape.
(Requires very little beating).
Quickly stir in nuts and cherries and turn into oiled pan.
Let stand until firm before cutting.
Makes 1 1/2 pounds.
Size and shape of pan determines the thickness.

title: sweet tomato chutney
directions: Mix together garlic, ginger, 1/2 cup vinegar and tomatoes. Blend on high speed until smooth.
Put all the blended ingredients in a pan and cook over medium heat.
Add sugar, pepper and cumin powder.
Bring to a boil and then lower the heat.

title: sour cream raisin pie
directions: Separate the yolks and whites of the eggs.
Beat yolks until creamy.
Add sugar, raisins, sour cream and cloves; place in double boiler and cook until thick and creamy.
Place in baked pie crust; set in oven a few minutes.
Remove from oven; cover with a meringue.

title: carrot cake
directions: In large bowl, blend oil and sugars on low until well mixed. Add vanilla.
Beat in eggs, one at a time, blending well after each addition.
Stir together dry ingredients and add to egg mixture until well blended.
Stir in walnuts and carrots by hand.

title: south western fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit and reserve 2 cups liquid.
Mix liquid with pudding and cook over low heat till thickened.
Pour over drained fruit.
Garnish with cherries.
Chill.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix in large paper bag.
Store in tightly covered container. Use 1/3 cup mix to 1 cup hot water.

title: english burgers
directions: Combine horseradish sauce, tomato and bacon.
Place a grilled burger on each muffin half. Spoon an equal amount of horseradish sauce mixture over each patty. Cover with remaining muffin half. Makes 4 servings.

title: lemon bisque
directions: Dissolve 1 package of lemon gelatin into 1 cup boiling water. Add 1/3 cup honey, juice and grated rind of 2 lemons.
Stir for one minute and let cool until it begins to set.

title: christmas cranberries
directions: Chop cranberries (blender).
Mix sugar and allow to drain overnight.
Mix cranberries with pineapple.
Add red grapes and nuts.
Blend in Cool Whip.
Store in refrigerator.

title: chicken broccoli cordon blue
directions: Place chicken between 2 pieces of plastic wrap and pound chicken to 1/4 inch thickness.
Place ham slice and cheese slice on each breast half.
Roll up chicken from narrow end, jelly-roll fashion.
Tuck in ham and cheese, if necessary secure with wooden toothpick.
In a 10-inch skillet over medium heat, heat oil and cook chicken 10 minutes or until browned on all sides.
Spoon off fat.
Stir in soup, milk, onions and thyme.
Reduce heat to low, cover and simmer 10 minutes or until chicken is fork-tender. Garnish with parsley

title: yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in the warm milk and water.
Add sugar, shortening, salt and eggs.
Add 5 cups flour, mixing thoroughly. Place in warm place to rise 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Punch down dough and place on a floured board.
Roll out; cut in the size you like. Dip rolls in the melted oleo, fold rolls over and place in bread pan.
Let rise again for 1 hour.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: cheese meatballs with noodles
directions: Place egg, garlic powder, salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper in a bowl and beat well.
Add beef and bread crumbs; mix thoroughly. Roll 2 tablespoons beef mixture around a cheese cube for each hamburger ball.
Heat oil in 4-quart saucepan; brown half the meatballs at a time in saucepan.
Remove meatballs; set aside. Saute onions in pan drippings until golden brown.
Add tomato juice, bring to a boil.
Add uncooked noodles so that liquid continues to boil.
Stir in meatballs and remaining pepper; cover. Simmer for 10 minutes.
Serve immediately.

title: zucchini bread-reduced fat
directions: Sift together flour, salt, baking powder, cinnamon and nutmeg. Set aside for later.
Beat eggs until frothy.
Add canola or olive oil, applesauce, sugar, vanilla extract, zucchini and chopped walnuts or pecans.
Combine wet and dry ingredients.
Grease and flour a medium and a small loaf pan.
Put 2/3 batter in medium pan and 1/3 of it in small pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool bread in pans lying on their sides for 10 minutes (on a rack).
Then turn over and slide bread out.
Slice and enjoy.

title: spinning mini-pinwheels(kids cooking)
directions: Will also need a rolling pin.

title: garden sauce
directions: In saucepan, cook onion in butter until tender.
Add remaining ingredients.
Heat, stirring occasionally.
Makes about 1 1/2 cups.
Serve over cooked vegetables.

title: dump cake
directions: Put in pan in order given.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Dissolve 1 package of lime jello in 1 cup water.
Add vinegar; let cool.
Add cucumber, onion, celery and pepper.
Stir in cream cheese until fairly well dissolved.
Place in individual molds; serve on a lettuce leaf with mayonnaise.

title: pizza sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Simmer.
Heat thoroughly to blend flavors.
Makes approximately 1 cup of sauce.

title: oat bran muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into lined muffin tins and bake at 425° for about 12 minutes.
Makes 24 muffins.

title: "hot spicy sauce"
directions: Clean green pepper, onion and celery.
Dice into medium size pieces.
Melt 1 stick oleo; saute green pepper, onion and celery at slow heat.
Put 6 chops in frying pan; bring to boil.
Turn over; bring to boil.
Open tomato soup and tomato paste.
Empty into large enough container with added water (when thickened, add more water).
Put on slow heat, checking on sauteed veggies.
Empty water from pork chops; add 1 stick oleo.
Melt and fry slowly. Increase heat on tomato soup and paste and sauteed pepper, onion and celery.

title: russian rocks or snowballs
directions: Cream shortening.
Add sugar gradually and cream thoroughly. Add remaining ingredients and blend.
Shape in 1-inch balls.
Bake in 400° oven for 15 minutes.
While still warm, roll in confectioners sugar.

title: potato kugel
directions: Grate potatoes; add remaining ingredients.
Bake in well-greased casserole at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes until well browned.

title: jam cake
directions: Grease and lightly flour three 9 x 1 1/2-inch round baking pans.
Set aside.
Separate eggs into two small mixer bowls.
Beat egg whites until stiff peaks form; set aside.
Beat egg yolks; set aside.
In large mixer bowl, cream butter and sugar.
Add blackberry jam and beat well.
Beat in egg yolks.
Stir together flour, soda, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk, beating after each addition. Stir in raisins.
Gently fold in stiff-beaten egg whites.
Pour into prepared pans.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350° or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool cake in pans on wire racks for 10 minutes.
Remove from pans.
Cool thoroughly.	Fill and frost top with cream or fudge frosting.
Makes 12 servings.

title: simple stir-fry chicken
directions: Boil chicken breasts for 20 minutes. Let cool and remove meat from bones, using your fingers. Chop celery sticks into small pieces. Chop green peppers into small pieces. Stir-fry chicken pieces, celery and green pepper in a little vegetable oil until soft. Add the cans of soup to the veggies and chicken. Stir and simmer for a bit. Serve over white rice.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add buttermilk and vanilla.
Combine sugar and flour.
Add to egg mixture.
Add melted butter and mix well. Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° until set (about 30 minutes).

title: ambrosia(five by five salad)
directions: Drain juice off of fruits.
Place fruits into bowl with coconut and marshmallows.
Pour in sour cream; mix thoroughly. Put in mold; chill overnight.

title: janet and etta's pineapple cookies
directions: Cream together first 3 ingredients.
Beat eggs.
Add all other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: baked cinnamon raisin apples
directions: Cut bottom off of apples and core.
Stuff the center of apples with raisins.
Mix melted butter with cinnamon and brown sugar. Pour into holes.
Bake at 350° in a baking dish sprayed with Pam.

title: tyler's homemade banana ice cream
directions: You will need rock salt and ice for freezing.

title: chili tomorrow
directions: Bring to a boil the water, bouillon cubes and ground round; simmer for 15 minutes.
Remove from heat and chill well so you can skim off all the fat, then return to the stove.
Add all but the green beans and simmer for 1 hour.
Just before serving, add the beans, undrained if you like, and heat through.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook vermicelli 6 to 8 minutes.
Drain; do not rinse.
Mix ReaLemon and oil with vermicelli.
Toss and cover.
Refrigerate overnight.
Dice olives, peppers, celery and onions real fine; add pimentos.
Mix with garlic salt and Accent.
Cover and refrigerate in separate bowl overnight.
Next day, mix vermicelli and veggies with Miracle Whip, salt and pepper.

title: pink lemonade icebox pie
directions: Mix Eagle Brand milk and lemonade together; fold in Dream Whip.
Pour in pie crust and refrigerate for 2 or 3 hours.

title: pepperoni bread
directions: Thaw 1 loaf of dough according to package.
Sprinkle area with flour and roll out to large square; divide in two.
Layer slices of pepperoni, then cheese on dough.
Roll up and fold down ends under. Place rolls on cookie sheets and cut 2 slits in top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: holiday ambrosia
directions: In glass compote or serving dish, arrange alternate layers of orange slices, dates and coconut; chill.
Combine sour cream, sugar and 1 teaspoon orange peel; chill.
Serve over fruit, sprinkled with remaining orange peel.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: curried chicken
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in medium saucepan; cover and cook until onions are tender. Add soup, milk and parsley. Stir well to combine. Add chicken and simmer 10 minutes. Reduce heat to low. Stir in yogurt. Cook, stirring gently, until thoroughly heated. May be served over cooked rice. If so, add rice calorie count to dish. Serves 8 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: spicy chicken and corn
directions: In a skillet in hot butter, cook 1/2 chicken until browned, stirring often.
Remove; set aside.
Cook remaining chicken.

title: rice krispies candy
directions: In a large pot melt margarine and marshmallows over low heat. Add Rice Krispies, nuts and raisins; mix well.
Press into an 8 x 12-inch greased pan.
Let cool.
Cut into squares.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: In a large mixing bowl beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Beat in milk and peanut butter.
Stir in vanilla and lemon.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into the two crusts.
Refrigerate for 4 hours or until set.

title: parmesan chicken, vegetables and pasta
directions: Cook pasta according to directions. Cut each tender in half lengthwise and half again.

title: lasagna
directions: Saute ground beef and onion until brown.
Add tomato paste, tomato sauce, water and spaghetti mix; mix well.
Combine cottage cheese and cream cheese.
Prepare noodles according to package directions; drain.
Layer 1/3 of the noodles in bottom of baking dish.
Add 1/3 of meat mixture.
Top with 1/3 cheese mixture. Repeat layers twice, ending with cheese mixture.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for about 20 minutes.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix and ready to use 2 teaspoons to a cup of hot water.

title: silver white cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan or 2 round pans.
Beat flour, sugar, baking powder, salt, shortening, milk and vanilla in large mixer bowl on low speed, scraping constantly.
Add egg whites; beat on high, scraping occasionally. Bake until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean in 9 x 13-inch pan; bake 35 to 40 minutes; in round pans bake 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool and frost.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Mix cocoa and sugar.
Add milk and syrup and put on heat. Bring to a boil.
When it forms a soft ball in cold water, remove from heat and add butter and flavoring; beat until thickens.
Pour into buttered pan.

title: stuffed french bread
directions: Cut ends off bread and hollow out center with knife, saving the crumbs.
Brown hamburger with onion soup mix and any other spices you like.
Drain the grease and pour meat into big mixing bowl. After meat cools, add cheeses and bread crumbs from center torn into small pieces.
Put mixture inside opening of loaf.
Pack the burger in tight.
Turn the loaf over and pack from other end also. The bread should be about to burst when you are done.
Put ends of bread back on and wrap in aluminum foil.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes to a half hour depending on thickness.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: Put half can Hormel chili in an 8-inch square glass dish. Slice cream cheese over chili.
Put remaining chili over cream cheese.
Put shredded cheese on top.
Place in microwave 5 to 10 minutes until cheese melts.

title: molasses sugar cookies
directions: Melt shortening in saucepan over low heat.
Cool.
Add sugar, molasses and egg.
Beat well.
Sift together flour, soda, spices and salt.
Add to first mixture.
Mix well.
Chill overnight. Form into one-inch balls.
Roll in sugar.
Place 2 or 2 1/2-inches apart on cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 5 to 8 minutes.

title: cucumber and potato salad
directions: Peel cucumbers completely.
Slice fine with slicer.
Drain off juice.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and caraway seed.
Peel and dice soft-boiled potato.
Mix with cucumbers.
Pour oil and vinegar over mixture.
Sprinkle with a touch of garlic.
Chill.

title: pineapple delight
directions: Combine crumbs, sugar and butter.
Press in long pan; chill. Beat cream cheese, sugar and milk until smooth.
Fold in 1 small Cool Whip; spread over crust.
Next, layer drained pineapple. Using 3 1/2 cups cold milk, prepare pudding.
Pour over pineapple. Chill.
Before serving, add 1 small Cool Whip on top.
A real good summertime dessert.

title: beefy mushroom rice soup
directions: In a large saucepan heat oil.
Brown meat on all sides.
Add onion and carrots, saute for 5 minutes.
Stir in water, tomatoes, bouillon, marjoram and pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat. Simmer, covered, 1 hour.
Skim fat.
Add mushrooms and rice. Simmer 30 minutes longer.
Remove meat from bones and cut into bite size pieces.
Return meat to soup.
Add parsley.
Heat until hot. Makes 3 quarts.

title: delicious shrimp salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, being careful not to break shrimp into small pieces.
Serve on lettuce with tomato wedges.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: shrimp "green goddess" sauce
directions: All ingredients should be mixed together and served on lettuce over small shrimp.

title: boston cream pie(being married to a yankee, i had to learn this one.)
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Separate eggs and beat whites until stiff, gradually beating in half of the sugar.
Beat egg yolks with the remaining sugar until thick.
Add vanilla and lemon juice.
Slowly add water.
Fold in egg whites, dry ingredients and butter just to blend.
Bake in a greased, floured pan at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes before removing.

title: creamed tortillas
directions: Brown meat and onion seasoned with salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Drain.
Add Ro-Tel, soup and milk.
Heat.
Spray 9 x 13-inch baking dish with Pam cooking spray.
Cut or break tortillas into bite size pieces and lay in baking dish.
Pour half of mixture over tortillas and sprinkle with grated cheese.
Repeat for another layer.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: lasagna
directions: Grease a
x	13 x 2-inch pan.
Brown meat and drain. Add dry
spaghetti
mix,
tomato
paste and water.
Bring to a boil; turn
off
burner.	Cook
lasagna noodles.	Mix cottage cheese, Mozzarella	cheese	and egg.
Place in pan as follows: noodles, meat sauce and cheese mixture.
Repeat.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: layered pistachio dessert
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix baking mix, brown sugar and margarine until crumbly.
Stir in nuts.
Press in ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake until light brown 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: can't fail divinity
directions: Boil sugar, water and salt to hard-boil stage (248° to 250°) on thermometer. Place marshmallow cream in large bowl and stir in hot syrup.
Continue stirring until slightly stiff. Fold in vanilla and fruit/nuts. Pour into buttered 8 x 8 pan or drop by teaspoon on tray lined with wax paper.
Let cool. Enjoy!!

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together, adding only half of tomato sauce.
Mold into loaf pan or baking dish.
Add remaining sauce over top and bake approximately 1 hour.

title: oreo delight
directions: Let ice cream soften, then mix all together.
Put in freezer until ready to serve, then cut into little squares.

title: hot pineapple salad
directions: Mix sugar, flour and juice.
Add pineapple and cheese.
Pour into casserole.
Butter crumbs and sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes until browned.

title: tomato dumplins
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Add sliced onions and fry without browning, stirring constantly.
Add cooked tomatoes and bring to a boil.
Add salt, soda and scalded milk to tomatoes seasoned with salt and pepper.
When it comes to a boil, add dumplins made from the recipe following.

title: tomato butter
directions: Peel tomatoes.
Core and cut into slices or small pieces. Combine all ingredients in large, heavy kettle.
Heat to boiling. Cook; stir frequently until mixture thickens (about an hour). Cool; stir and place in hot, sterilized glasses.
(Can be frozen, if desired.)
Good with all meat dishes.

title: oatmeal cookies - no sugar
directions: Cream butter and Crisco together.
Mix the rest of the ingredients.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on a cookie sheet.
Bake in a 375° oven for 15 minutes or until brown.
These cookies are made without sugar; instead applesauce with fruit is used.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine corn flakes and melted butter.
Set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients together.
Spoon mixture into casserole pan and sprinkle with topping.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: boiled custard
directions: Scald milk. Beat eggs; add sugar and milk.
Add scalded milk slowly.
Place mixture in a double boiler and cook until thick as cream, or until it coats a spoon.
Add vanilla.
Serve with whipped cream or whipped topping, if desired.
Serves 20 to 24 inches.
This recipe may be cut in half.

title: marge's beans
directions: Mix all together, except bacon, in Pyrex baking dish.
Arrange bacon on top.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into a large casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Crush small box of Ritz crackers. Melt 1 stick of butter and mix with crushed crackers.
Spoon on top of casserole.
Bake for 20 minutes more.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Combine ingredients in order given, folding in egg whites last.
Place mixture in well-greased pan and bake in a moderately hot oven.
Serve with white sauce.

title: cheery cherry cream cheesecake
directions: Whip cream cheese until fluffy.
Gradually add milk, continuing to beat until well blended.
Add lemon juice and vanilla.
Blend well.
Pour filling into crust.
Chill for 2 to 3 hours.
Top with cherry pie filling.

title: fried chicken, cuban style
directions: Remove skin and fat from chicken pieces.
Pierce meat in several places with long fork prongs, and place chicken in a bowl. Combine garlic, oregano, onion, orange juice, wine and salt. Pour mixture over chicken.
Cover and marinate in the refrigerator for about 1 hour.

title: fine chili sauce
directions: Chop all ingredients fine. Cook until thick over low heat, stirring often (about 1 1/2 hours). Seal while hot.

title: gooey butter cake
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt butter.
Combine with dry cake mix and 2 eggs.
Press in pan.
Combine 2 eggs, softened cream cheese, vanilla and powdered sugar.
Pour over base.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Cool and dust with powdered sugar.

title: rice heavenly hash
directions: Combine rice, milk and sugar.
Cook until thick and creamy, about 10 to 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Cool and fold in remaining ingredients.
Spoon into serving dishes.
Chill.
Makes 12 servings, about 1/2 cup each.
Add cherries on top if desired.

title: jerky
directions: Slice lean meat in 1/4-inch slices.
Season with salt and pepper.
Place in oven, draped over bar.
Put a cookie sheet under to catch drips.
Bake at 120° for 8 hours; leave door open 1-inch.

title: beef and cabbage soup
directions: Cook meat, onion and celery until meat is browned. Place meat mixture and remaining ingredients in a large pot. Cook approximately 1 hour. Freezes well, also.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Sprinkle Sugar Twin over bananas and stir until dissolved. Beat eggs well and blend into bananas.
Sift dry ingredients; add nuts and coconut and blend into banana mixture until just mixed. Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Lower heat to 300° and bake approximately another 25 minutes.
Cake should be moist, but springy to touch.

title: stir-fry sauce
directions: Combine ingredients; cook until thick, stirring constantly. Excellent with ham.

title: microwave chicken green chili casserole(potluck)
directions: Mix together the first 4 ingredients.
Layer half of the chips, half of the chicken, half of the tomatoes, half of the soup and half of the cheese; repeat procedures.
Microwave on High. Cook 8 to 10 minutes on Full power.
Let stand 3 minutes.

title: milk chocolate kahlua truffles(gourmet magazine, december 1988)
directions: In a large saucepan, combine all ingredients.
Heat the mixture over moderately low heat, stirring until it is smooth. Transfer to a bowl, cover and chill for 4 hours or until firm. Roll in balls.
Roll in cocoa powder.
Press a chocolate coffee bean half into each truffle.
Chill on baking sheet for 1 hour. Keep in airtight container in refrigerator for 2 weeks.
Yields about 35 outrageously good truffles.
These are wonderful!

title: yabba-dabba-doo squares
directions: *Add 1/3 cup creamy peanut butter with the margarine if using Cocoa Pebbles.

title: fruit and angel dessert
directions: Break cake into bite size pieces (about 8 cups).
Arrange half the cake pieces in bottom of an oblong baking dish.
Top with half of the undrained fruit and the chopped cherries.
Spread half the whipped toping over all and top with coconut.
Repeat layers. Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Yield:
12 servings.

title: mom taylor's curry
directions: Cut onions finely; brown in butter.
Stir in curry powder and simmer 2 or 3 minutes.
Add hot water or meat stock and boil for 5 minutes, stirring often.
Add jam, vinegar and milk and bring to a boil.
Add meat.
Cut into small pieces and allow to simmer until required for table (about 1/2 hour).

title: homemade onion rings
directions: Mix flour and beer.
Let stand for 3 hours.
Slice onions and separate into rings.
Deep-fry until golden brown.
Enjoy!

title: steak marinade
directions: Mix together the 4 ingredients.
Brush on steak and marinate overnight.
Broil.
Especially good for flank steak!

title: cranberry horseradish sauce
directions: Melt cranberry sauce in saucepan.
Dissolve gelatin in a little cold water and add to hot sauce.
Cool.
Stir in horseradish and salt.
Pour into a 1 1/2-quart mold.
Chill. Unmold and serve with turkey, ham, venison or other game.

title: russian tea
directions: Bring water, cinnamon, tea bags and cloves to a boil and simmer for 10 minutes. Add remaining ingredients. Serve hot.

title: easy overnight casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and set in refrigerator overnight.
In morning, top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake 1 hour at 350°. Serves 4.

title: honan beef
directions: Slice beef paper thin into long strips.
In a bowl, mix beef, soy sauce, sherry and garlic; let stand at room temperature for 1 hour.
In a large skillet, heat oil until it sizzles; remove beef from bowl and stir-fry in skillet for 2 to 3 minutes or until brown.
Add marinade from beef and remaining ingredients (add pepper flakes, a little at a time, to taste) and stir-fry over high heat for 4 to 5 minutes or until vegetables are tender but still crisp.
Serve over hot rice.

title: angel delight
directions: In a large, deep, non-plastic bowl, dissolve gelatin in cold water.
Add boiling water & stir until cool.
Add pineapple and juice.
Fold in dry cake mix and watch it rise.
When double in size, add whipped topping.	Pour into 9 x 13 inch pan and top with nuts.
Refrigerate.
Cut into squares when cold.

title: fresh peach pies(2)
directions: Cook sugar, cornstarch, water and Karo until clear and thick, stirring all the time. Add jello and stir until dissolved. Cool until thick as pie filling. Fold in peaches. Pour into pie crusts. Chill and top with Cool Whip or blender ice cream.

title: creamy turkey with pasta plus
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a 5-quart saucepot, cook spaghetti according to package directions; drain and reserve.
In the 5-quart saucepot, melt butter.
Add onion and mushrooms.
Cook briskly, stirring often, until just wilted.
Stir in flour.
Off heat, gradually stir in broth and half and half, keeping smooth. Cook over moderately low heat, stirring occasionally, until thickened and boiling.
Off heat, stir in sherry, Swiss cheese, turkey, reserved spaghetti and salt and pepper.

title: salmon spread
directions: Combine salmon, softened cream cheese, horseradish, lemon juice and liquid smoke.
Mix until well blended.
Form into ball and refrigerate for several hours.
Roll in nuts and parsley and serve with crackers or party rye bread.

title: braised cabbage
directions: In skillet, heat butter until foamy.
Add chives and saute until tender.
Add shredded cabbage and carrots.
Saute over high heat until tender but crisp, about 4 minutes.
Add vinegar, salt and pepper to taste.
Makes 4 servings.

title: lemonade tea
directions: Add enough water to make 1 gallon.

title: overnight buns
directions: Start at 5 p.m.
Knead down every hour.
About 9 p.m., shape into buns and put on well-greased cookie sheet.
Let rise overnight.
Bake in the morning at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix ingredients well and put in buttered dish.

title: tiramisu
directions: Dip each biscuit into Espresso; place in a single layer on bottom and around side of glass or ceramic baking dish, about 8-inch square or similar capacity. Combine water and powdered egg whites in a large stainless steel bowl, stirring until the powder dissolves (3 to 4 minutes). With an electric mixer, beat at medium-high speed until stiff peaks form, 5 to 7 minutes.

title: chicken casserole(recipe from cousin adeline)
directions: Cook chicken breasts; cool, bone and dice.
Cut crust from bread; retain this.
Combine chicken, breast crusts, celery and 1 3/4 cups of cheese.
Spread over bottom of glass Pyrex dish (13 x 9 x 2-inch).
Cover with bread, cut diagonally; overlap.
Mix eggs, seasonings and milk; blend or mix very well.
Pour over bread and mixture.
Spread remaining cheese on top of this. Refrigerate overnight or 2 hours.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: mexicali chicken
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients in a large skillet.
Cook, uncovered, over medium-high heat 20 minutes.
Cook pasta according to package directions, omitting salt and fat; drain.
Add pasta and remaining ingredients to tomato mixture.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer 20 minutes.

title: caramel corn
directions: Combine brown sugar, Karo, butter and water.
Boil to soft ball stage.
Pour over 1 gallon prepopped corn.
Bake at 200° for 1 hour.

title: crock-pot enchiladas
directions: Alternate ingredients in layers.
Cook in crock-pot about 3 hours.

title: hawaiian pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour; add pineapple and juice.
Cook over medium heat until it comes to a boil.
Let cool.
Slice bananas and arrange in pie crust.
Add nuts and pineapple mixture.
Top with Cool Whip and coconut which have been mixed together.
Can be placed in refrigerator overnight and topped with Cool Whip and coconut the next day.

title: basic pie crust
directions: Mix flour and salt. Cut in shortening with a pastry cutter; don't use hands. Add ice water with a fork. Gather the dough into a ball and roll out into a 4 inch wide disk. Wrap in plastic and chill for 30 minutes.

title: watergate salad
directions: Fold dry pudding mix into topping.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Refrigerate several hours.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Mix butter, shortening, sugar, eggs, flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt.
Form into pizza pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Cool.
Combine cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Spread on crust. Top with fruit.

title: fried squash
directions: Slice squash 1/2-inch thick.
Dip in milk and coat in the remaining ingredients (all mixed together).
Fry until golden brown.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Boil sugar, milk and dash of salt for 10 minutes, then add butter and boil until soft ball is formed.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter and vanilla and beat until thick.
Pour into buttered pan and let cool.

title: cheesy corn bake
directions: Combine the first six ingredients.
Pour into a greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until center is done.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Cut apples in half (8 halves). Peel and remove core from halves.
Divide each crust into fourths and wrap apple halves so that round edges are drawn into the core of each apple half.
(For added flavor, sprinkle cinnamon and sugar and place a sliver of margarine into core of apple halves before wrapping.)

title: fruit 'n nut spread
directions: In blender or food processor container, combine cottage cheese, lemon juice and rind.
Blend until smooth and creamy.
Coarsely chop orange sections.
Stir chopped oranges and almonds into mixture.
Chill at least an hour.
Serve spread with Triscuit wafers.

title: nasturtium sandwiches
directions: Wash the nasturtium flowers in ice water. Dry. Spread 1 slice of bread with mayonnaise.
Place a thick layer of nasturtium petals on top.
Place a slice of buttered bread on top. Cut the sandwiches into triangles and serve on a large platter with blossoms strewn over the top.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients and cook in the microwave for 10 minutes on High.

title: easy refrigerator pickles
directions: In a large jar, alternately layer the sliced cukes and onions. In a medium saucepan, combine sugar, vinegar, celery seed, salt, mustard seed and turmeric.
Bring to boil, stirring just until sugar is dissolved.
Pour over cukes and onions.
Cover tightly and refrigerate for 24 hours.
Store up to one month.
Makes up to 7 cups; really crispy and delicious.

title: fried rice
directions: Saute meat in 1/2 to 1 stick oleo.
Add carrots.
Cook 3 minutes.
Add pepper, cook 3 minutes.
Add onion and cook 3 minutes.
Add eggs, rice and seasonings to taste.
Cook just until heated.
Do not overcook!

title: banana split pie
directions: Line bottom crust with bananas.
Cover with ice cream and freeze for 2 hours or until firm.
Top with fudge sauce and sprinkle peanuts on top.
Top with whipped topping.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Cut shortening into flour and salt until crumbly.
Combine eggs, water and vinegar.
Pour all of the liquids into flour mixture at once.
Blend with fork until flour is moist. Roll out with more flour.
Makes 3 crusts.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream thoroughly the first 3 ingredients.
Add next 2 ingredients.
Beat thoroughly.
Blend or sift together next 3 ingredients and add to creamed mixture. Combine well.
Fold in last 2 ingredients.
Drop from a teaspoon onto greased baking sheets.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.
Yield:
About 2 dozen cookies.

title: fat-free spice cake
directions: Spray 9-inch square baking pan with cooking spray.
In a large bowl, combine flour, cornstarch, baking powder, salt, cinnamon, ginger and nutmeg.
In medium bowl, using a fork or wire whisk, stir sugar and milk until sugar is almost dissolved.
Add egg whites, corn syrup and vanilla; stir until blended.
Gradually add to flour mixture; stir until smooth.
Pour into prepared pan. Bake in 350° oven 30 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan on wire rack.

title: spareribs and sauerkraut
directions: Cut
ribs into small portions, pack in large kettle and cover with
water.
Cook	until
tender,	about
1 hour.	Add kraut; cook
minutes or until most of liquid is gone.	Put sugar in to	take out some of the sourness of kraut.
Makes 5 servings.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream the margarine and sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in vanilla.
Combine flour and potato chips.
Add them gradually to margarine mixture, stirring until all traces of flour are mixed into batter.

title: 1,000 calorie pie
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together but fold in Cool Whip last. Place in a pie crust and chill 30 minutes to 1 hour.

title: cheese cake
directions: Dissolve lemon jello in boiling water; chill until thickens. Mix together crushed graham crackers, 2 teaspoons sugar and melted oleo.
Put 1/2 in 9 x 12-inch dish and pat down.
Save the balance for top.

title: mock pecan pie
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour or until set.

title: white fluffy icing
directions: Combine all ingredients together and beat at high speed for 15 minutes.

title: autumn pork chops
directions: Combine coriander and celery seed.
Apply to both sides of chops.
Core and slice apple.
Put butter in electric skillet and melt.
Place chops and apples in skillet.
Sprinkle brown sugar on apples.
Put about 1 inch of water in skillet.
Cook at approximately 250° for 8 to 10 minutes on each side.
Add more water if needed.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine sugars, milk, and butter.
Cook to soft ball, 235 degrees.
Add remaining ingredients, stir until marshmallows melt. Pour into buttered 8 in. sq. pan.
Cool. May be doubled.

title: zucchini crusted pizza(4 to 6 servings)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Salt zucchini lightly and let stand 15 minutes in colander.
Squeeze out excess moisture.
Combine crust ingredients and spread on oiled 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes until surface is dry and firm.
Brush top with oil and broil under moderate heat for 5 minutes.
Top however you like. Heat for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: pistachio pudding
directions: Combine pudding and pineapple (undrained).
Add mandarin oranges (drained), coconut and marshmallows (cut in half).
Mix in Cool Whip.
Chill to set overnight.

title: one step salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 2 cups boiling water.
Mix the orange sherbet into jello (this will cause jello to thicken).
Add the oranges, bananas and pineapple.
Stir and mold.

title: iced tea syrup
directions: Bring water and sugar to boil for 5 minutes.
Add tea bags and simmer for 15 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Use 3 tablespoons syrup for each glass.
Will make 1 1/2 gallons.

title: carolina barbecue
directions: Place beef, water, liquid smoke, 1/2 teaspoon garlic salt and pepper in a Dutch oven.
Cover tightly; cook over low heat for 2 hours.

title: southern biscuit muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease 12 (2 1/2-inch) muffin cups (do not use paper liners).
In a large bowl, combine flour, sugar and baking powder.
Cut in butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Stir in milk just until flour mixture is moistened.
Spoon into muffin cups.
Bake 20 minutes or until golden.

title: hawaiian meatballs
directions: Mix hamburg, bread cubes, onion, egg and milk.
Make 3 to 4 dozen meatballs.
Mix and pour over meatballs pineapple chunks, 2 tablespoons soy sauce, 1 tablespoon vinegar, brown sugar, cornstarch and chicken broth.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until done.

title: fried okra
directions: Mix flour, meal, salt and pepper.
Roll okra in mixture.
Fry in heavy frypan that has 1/2 inch hot oil.
Add okra and turn heat to medium.
Watch closely as will burn easily.
When brown, remove and serve.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Put popped corn into large mixing bowl.
Combine sugar, syrup and water in large saucepan; bring to a boil.
When it boils it will expand in the pan.
When the mixture receeds after boiling a few minutes, it will be almost ready to remove from heat but continue to boil until it reaches a reasonably firm ball tested in cup of cold water.
Remove from heat; add butter and vanilla. Drizzle over the popped corn being careful to stir until all corn is covered with syrup thoroughly.
Wet hands with water and form into balls being careful not to pack too tightly.
Place balls on waxed paper until ready to serve.
Keeps at room temperature for several days.

title: lemon whipper snaps
directions: Grease cookie sheet.
Combine cake mix, Cool Whip and egg in large bowl.
Stir until well mixed.
Roll in powdered sugar.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Let the first 5 ingredients stand in plastic container overnight.
Drain well next morning, then add remaining ingredients.
Mix together; let boil.
Then simmer 45 minutes and can.

title: stuffed peppers in tomato sauce
directions: Start tomato sauce in fairly large pot to prevent from overcooking.
In 1/4 cup oil, brown flour.
Slowly add while stirring 1/2 gallon canned and sifted through tomatoes.
Add 1 teaspoon salt, 2 tablespoons sugar or according to your taste. Turn flame very low.
Take green bell peppers, wash and cut the top off to remove seeds so they can be filled.
Mix the pork, rice, egg, red pepper, salt and black pepper.
Mix in bowl with spoon. Add which flavor you like according to taste.
First, fill the pepper and the remaining ground meat mixture; make into 2-inch balls.
Put them all into tomato sauce and on low heat, cook for about 2 to 2 1/2 hours.
Stir once in a while very carefully so it won't stick to bottom of pot.

title: ham asparagus roll-ups
directions: Spread soft cream cheese over ham slices.
Place asparagus spear on ham and roll.
Chill and slice into 1/2-inch slices.

title: scrambled eggs for 50 people(recipe may be halved, if desired.)
directions: Use a large roasting pan.
Melt margarine in pan and let pan cool.
Beat eggs, milk and salt together.
Bake in a 325° oven for 30 minutes.
Stir after 15 minutes.
At 30 minutes, increase temperature to 350°.
Stir and bake another 5 to 10 minutes or to desired consistency. Stir and serve.

title: chili tomato sauce
directions: Chop tomatoes, onions, peppers; salt and pepper to taste. Heat vinegar; add sugar and spices.
Stir well until melted.
Add chopped food and cook until tender, about 2 hours.
Makes 7 quarts.

title: harvard beets
directions: Drain beets, saving liquid.
Melt butter.
Blend in flour. Slowly add beet liquid and stir constantly over direct heat until sauce boils and thickens.
Add remaining ingredients and the beets and continue heating slowly until beets are hot through.
Serve at once.
Makes 5 servings.

title: overnight casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fettucini alfredo
directions: Cook noodles according to directions; make sure not to overcook.
Drain and return to pot.
Add butter and cream and mix well.
Add cheese and toss lightly.
Spoon into serving dish, which can be warmed.
Serve with freshly ground pepper.
Serves 8.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: In large bowl, beat eggs until foamy; beat in flour, sugar and brown sugar.
Blend in melted butter.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: nut rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in milk and add 1 tablespoon sugar.
Combine the flour, butter, salt, sugar, canned milk, eggs and yeast mixture.
Blend well.

title: maypo cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat margarine, sugar, egg and vanilla until light and fluffy. Add flour, baking soda, cinnamon and nutmeg, mixing until thoroughly combined. Stir in Maypo, raisins and walnuts.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until desired brownness.
Allow cookies to cool 1 minute on cookie sheet. Remove to wire rack to cool completely.
Makes 4 1/2 dozen.

title: sandwich filling
directions: Mix all together and spread on top of round bread.

title: icebox rolls
directions: Combine milk, lard and sugar; scald.
Cool to lukewarm. Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup lukewarm water.
Add enough flour to make of cake batter consistency.
Let rise until doubled in bulk. Add soda, baking powder, salt and enough flour to make stiff dough. Make into roll; let rise.
Bake at 425° until slightly browned.

title: poached dried fruit compote
directions: Combine all ingredients in saucepan.
Boil over high heat. Reduce heat; simmer 15 minutes until fruit is tender.
Cool. Discard cinnamon sticks and cloves.
Serve warm.

title: seafood pasta salad(low-fat)
directions: Mix in order as given. Add seasoning to salad. Chill overnight or 6 to 8 hours.
Makes 8 servings.

title: parsnip potatoes mashed(low calorie)
directions: In stockpot or Dutch oven bring the potatoes and parsnips broth and water to a boil.
Cook covered until vegetables are tender about 25 minutes.

title: beef stroganoff(from betty crocker)
directions: Cut meat across the grain into 1/2-inch strips, about 1 1/2-inches long.
Melt butter in large skillet.
Add mushrooms and onion.
Cook until tender and remove.
Brown meat in same skillet.

title: pineapple-orange dish
directions: Drain orange slices and cut into small pieces.
Add pineapple and orange slices together in a bowl.
Add cottage cheese and stir gently.
Sprinkle jello over the mixture and stir gently.
Add the Cool Whip and mix.
It's ready to eat.

title: miss baker's chocolate chip and m&m cookies
directions: Whip butter together.
Mix in sugars, then eggs and vanilla. Then mix in dry ingredients except oatmeal.
The oatmeal needs to be put in blender and made to be powder like.
Then stir in oatmeal, chips and M&M's.
Bake golf ball size cookies at 375° for 6 to 8 minutes.

title: beef stew '57
directions: Brown meat with salt, sugar and pepper in shortening.
Add 2 cups water, beef bouillon cubes and cover.
Simmer 1 hour or until meat is tender.
Stir in Heinz 57 sauce and vegetables.
Cover and simmer an additional hour or until vegetables are tender.
Thicken with the flour and water.

title: baked apples
directions: Core as many apples as desired and place in a shallow baking dish.
Fill the cavities in the apples with brown sugar, raisins or nuts and a small piece of butter.
Add boiling water to about 1/2 inch depth and bake uncovered in a 375 degree oven until the apples are tender.
Serve warm or cold.

title: potatoes supreme
